(133, 12, 17, 102, '0f91243f-2db8-53b5-b395-8c928ec62a06', 'In Jessica Au’s prizewinning novel “Cold Enough for Snow,” two generations communicate with words and what’s left unsaid.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/books/review/jessica-au-cold-enough-for-snow.html', 'COLD ENOUGH FOR SNOWBy Jessica Au', 'The New York Times', '01GREY-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709605', '1683923365'),
(134, 24, 0, 103, '59c63ff7-c072-50bd-ac8e-83b8defb40c9', 'Only use guides who lead rather than follow you. At the top of the run, ask them for a play-by-play so you know what’s coming.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/magazine/how-to-ski-blind.html', '“You need a guide,” says Mike May, 68, who was blinded at age 3 in a calcium-carbide chemical explosion. May started skiing at 27, on a bunny slope, holding onto a guide’s poles — in what he calls “horse and buggy style.” Within days, he was unattached and following his guide’s voice down the hill. “It was extremely liberating,” says May, who went on to win multiple medals in the world competitions now known as the Paralympics, and hit 65 miles per hour to set the world record for speed skiing by a completely blind skier.', 'The New York Times', '06mag-tip-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709605', '1683923366'),
(135, 12, 0, 104, '703700c4-2e52-5268-a471-384b0caacc70', 'The prolific cultural obsessive turns his attention to the twilight of a millennium, when Generation X reluctantly took center stage.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/books/review-nineties-chuck-klosterman.html', 'They’re baaack.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709605', '1683923367'),
