(146, 18, 0, 44, '8c1811fd-b728-5cb7-be1e-67155dd6682c', 'A new interactive tool developed by The New York Times’s Graphics desk lets readers put their congressional-district-drawing skills to the test.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/insider/ready-set-gerrymander.html', 'On Thanksgiving, three journalists on The New York Times’s Graphics team headed into their family dinners with an unusual mission: They wanted to talk politics with their families.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709610', '1683923378'),
(148, 24, 0, 114, 'f041f89c-cb8f-5681-9629-ebaaa9fa5f5f', 'The magazine’s Ethicist columnist on when disclosing a secret is a betrayal — and more.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/magazine/adultery-ethics.html', 'Our dad died a year ago, and our mom recently told my sister and me that she cheated on him for the last 10 years of their marriage. I don’t think our dad ever knew; he wore his heart on his sleeve, so he couldn’t have hidden that sort of thing.', 'The New York Times', '06mag-ethicist-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709610', '1683923380'),
(150, 13, 0, 116, '24aa5bde-9e15-51b5-b210-f7b9de7991b8', 'To the extent that Biden has been open about the politics and the optics of this nomination, I think he’s done a service for the public.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/opinion/biden-breyer-supreme-court.html', 'A new vacancy on the Supreme Court means a new round of political theater over the beliefs and qualifications of the president’s eventual nominee.', 'The New York Times', '01bouie-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709613', '1683923382'),
(151, 9, 0, 117, '3898649b-f93a-5181-9c64-0ca1b3664728', 'You may not spend a lot of time there, but if you’ve got a staircase, it shouldn’t be ‘tired and dull.’ Here’s how to give it some personality.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/realestate/staircase-repair-fix-improve.html', 'Your staircase may not get as much attention as other spaces in your home, like your kitchen and living room, but it should. A beautiful stairwell can tie your home together and make moving from one level to another a pleasure.', 'The New York Times', 'oakImage-1643643671026-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709614', '1683923385'),
(152, 22, 0, 118, '774ced7a-c959-5017-8f75-710e7f707530', 'From her New Orleans restaurant, Melissa Martin sees the environmental damage that could end the region’s rich culture of food and fishing.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/dining/louisiana-seafood-climate-change-melissa-martin.html', 'NEW ORLEANS — Days before Hurricane Ida hit last August, Maxine and Lanny Martin bought 150 pounds of shrimp in Chauvin, the coastal Louisiana town where they live. The shrimp came from fishers along Bayou Petit Caillou, which runs a few blocks from the house where the Martins raised six children, including Melissa Martin, a chef and cookbook author in New Orleans.', 'The New York Times', '01louisiana-seafood1-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709615', '1683923386'),
(153, 13, 0, 97, 'e1a19a8b-668b-5e79-a91a-765128f1692f', 'American agriculture is ravaging the air, soil and water. But a powerful lobby has cleverly concealed its damage.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/opinion/climate-sustainability-agriculture-lobby.html', '“We’re Cooked” is an Opinion Video series about our broken food system and the three chances you get to help fix it — and save the planet — every day.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709615', '1683923387'),
(154, 25, 0, 119, '3fbfb662-078f-51f3-8399-4edd779840d2', 'After the Ascutney ski resort in Vermont closed because of erratic snowfall and mismanagement, it threatened to take with it the nearby town of West Windsor. The community took the situation into its own hands.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/travel/ascutney-cross-country.html', 'Jim Lyall briskly skied up Mount Ascutney, eagerly pointing out the view. We were skinning up a ski area in southern Vermont, but the chairlifts are long gone. At the top of the mountain we arrived at an abandoned ski patrol cabin and lift station. A cold breeze whipped through the deserted structures. It had a ghostly, post-apocalyptic feel.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709617', '1683923387'),
(155, 2, 0, 74, '4e34b5f6-672f-5c89-b13d-5e242f756267', 'Only about a quarter of the funding went to jobs that would have been lost, new research found. A big chunk lined bosses’ pockets.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/paycheck-protection-program-costs.html', 'Hanging over the $800 billion Paycheck Protection Program, one of the government’s most expensive pandemic relief efforts, is a simple question.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200859954_d1e95bb5-75ec-4923-ba33-d53d2ffcdb33-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709618', '1683923388'),
(156, 13, 0, 120, '6e639990-d455-570e-9b6d-4f8a114e1103', '“Stakeholder capitalism” does not offer a real alternative to broad political mobilizations that would benefit most Americans. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/opinion/corporations-democracy.html', 'When Larry Fink, the chief executive of the asset management company BlackRock, wrote in his 2022 annual letter to corporate America that prioritizing environmental sustainability, racial justice and other social goals is not “woke” and “not about politics,” he articulated anew a longstanding hope that business can be a driver for social change.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709618', '1683923389'),
(157, 8, 6, 121, '03be4863-c7ac-5328-9156-f81f8244a43e', 'The United States and its allies have trained and helped equip the Ukrainian army. But it has little resemblance to the kind of sophisticated, contemporary military that distinguishes NATO members.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/europe/ukraine-army-nato-russia.html', 'POPASNA, Ukraine — The soldiers live in dugout bunkers, and cook all their own meals. They dry their wet socks on clotheslines underground. Many of their weapons are remnants of the Soviet era, half a century old.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709619', '1683923390'),
(158, 26, 0, 122, '42d691a5-c58d-5065-b9ab-e3537866a6d8', 'After navigating the treacherous waters of celebrity, the superstar is betting on “Marry Me,” a movie that sounds a lot like her personal life.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/movies/jennifer-lopez-marry-me.html', 'LOS ANGELES — Of course the fireplace is lit at Jennifer Lopez’s house. It’s a rainy day just a week before Christmas, and her Spanish-style Bel-Air estate is decorated as you would expect: pine garland strewn around the mantel, orange roses on the coffee table, a professionally trimmed Christmas tree in the living room.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200932224_f44969bf-ae17-45bd-ab99-41b8c28a7b78-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709619', '1683923391'),
(159, 2, 11, 123, '796c1601-3b5e-5217-ba9b-819f21fe5b27', 'The pandemic has supposedly given service workers leverage. But many still have unstable hours and incomes because employers like the flexibility.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/economy/part-time-work.html', 'Over the past two months, Brenda Garcia, who works at a Chipotle in Queens, has struggled to land more than 20 hours per week, making it difficult to keep up with her expenses. When she confronts her manager, he vows to try to find her more work, but the problem invariably persists. In one recent week, the store scheduled her for a single 6.25-hour shift.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_201026652_a0724b38-27c7-402a-9a6d-ec3cb367671d-articleLarge.jpg', '1643709620', '1683923392'),
(160, 8, 18, 124, 'cb421998-7f6c-5255-baed-59e8c8db8890', 'China is expanding its ties to Middle Eastern states with vast infrastructure investments and cooperation on technology and security.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/middleeast/china-middle-east.html', 'BEIRUT, Lebanon — In January alone, five senior officials from oil-rich Arab monarchies visited China to discuss cooperation on energy and infrastructure. Turkey’s top diplomat flew in to talk about opportunities for economic collaboration, and Iran’s foreign minister pressed for progress on $400 billion of investment that China has promised his country.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643709620', '1683923394'),
(161, 1, 19, 125, '01e0ffd6-1bbe-5b53-a9b8-4dde2a6b142d', 'Meyers Taylor and her U.S. teammate Josh Williamson joined a growing list of Olympians with the coronavirus. The schedule may allow them enough time to recover and compete.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/sports/olympics/elana-meyers-taylor-coronavirus-olympics.html', 'Elana Meyers Taylor, a three-time Olympic medalist and one of the most decorated American bobsledders in history, said Tuesday that she had tested positive for the coronavirus shortly after arriving in Beijing for the Winter Olympics.', 'The New York Times', '01oly-positives-articleLarge.jpg', '1643710507', '1683923396'),
(162, 6, 0, 0, '75f74635-4b55-504b-b6ac-21e4c12599fc', 'Quotation of the Day for Tuesday, February 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/todayspaper/quotation-of-the-day-taking-on-everest-at-its-very-coldest-and-at-its-toughest.html', '“You have to be able to suffer. It’s the art of suffering.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643710981', '1683923396'),
(163, 12, 0, 26, '58a0e1f4-0b7b-5638-be4f-d815c59252dc', 'Dillon Helbig, a second-grader from Idaho, wrote an 81-page book about his “Crismis” adventures. Now other children want to write stories.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/books/crismis-book-school-library.html', 'During his Christmas break, Dillon Helbig, an 8-year-old boy from Boise, Idaho, wrote a book that he wanted everyone to read.', 'The New York Times', '01xp-book-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1643711409', '1683923397'),
(164, 10, 0, 126, 'e93633fb-41b2-50f8-8fb4-83c44d979097', 'Missouri and Illinois announced emergency plans. New Mexico, Texas and other areas unaccustomed to snow and freezing wind chills are bracing for days of frigid weather.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/us/snow-winter-storm.html', 'A blustery winter storm is expected to sweep through nearly 2,000 miles of the central United States starting on Tuesday evening, bringing a mix of freezing temperatures, heavy snow and potentially hazardous traveling conditions from parts of New Mexico and Texas up through Illinois and Michigan, weather officials said.', 'The New York Times', '01xp-storm-articleLarge.jpg', '1643711410', '1683923398'),
(165, 27, 20, 127, '600f4d4b-2da8-566a-bce0-23112ca940d8', 'Higher prices are imperiling the party’s chances of holding on to power in Washington. How much have Democrats’ own policies contributed to the problem?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/podcasts/the-daily/inflation-pandemic-biden-economy.html', 'Inflation in the United States has been getting worse. In December, prices were up 7 percent from the previous year — the fastest rise in 40 years. ', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643713206', '1683923399'),
(166, 12, 0, 128, '5c075fb1-8c56-53fe-b421-9e8891187ef2', 'Ambo Anthos Publishers said it would delay printing more copies. HarperCollins, the book’s publisher in the United States, declined to comment.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/books/anne-frank-the-betrayal.html', 'AMSTERDAM — The Dutch publisher of “The Betrayal of Anne Frank,” a new book scholars have criticized for putting forward inconclusive findings, apologized for “offending anyone” in an email sent to its authors, and said it would delay printing more copies of the book until further notice.', 'The New York Times', '01anne-frank-articleLarge.jpg', '1643713291', '1683923400'),
(167, 19, 0, 129, '683eadae-bd2a-528e-a2ed-9c04b8c70dfa', 'Inflation is up, and Americans are mad. But it’s not a simple story.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/briefing/inflation-anger-us-covid.html', 'Paul Krugman, the economist and Times Opinion columnist, asked an intriguing question last week: Why are Americans so upset about inflation?', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_198990033_6d15ec27-d022-4c6c-87d0-047fd99c1bcb-articleLarge.jpg', '1643714428', '1683923401'),
(168, 8, 6, 130, 'd6e57c11-cb68-5511-b799-f3a024e78d9c', 'On a friendly visit to Moscow, Prime Minister Viktor Orban of Hungary diverged sharply from his NATO and European Union allies.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/europe/orban-putin-moscow-ukraine.html', 'MOSCOW — Splitting sharply from his NATO allies, Prime Minister Viktor Orban of Hungary said on Tuesday that proposed sanctions against Russia if it takes military action against Ukraine would be “doomed to failure” and that Russian security demands were reasonable.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643714961', '1683923402');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(170, 20, 0, 0, 'c58ca3dc-3bb2-5ec5-8cd0-531ec75a412e', 'A reporter covering online disinformation takes you through how she debunks false information with the help of data, advice from experts and a little detective work.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/learning/annotated-by-the-author-covid-test-misinformation-spikes-along-with-spread-of-omicron.html', 'As a resource for both our annual STEM-writing contest and our news literacy series, we asked Davey Alba, a technology reporter covering online disinformation and its global harms, to contribute to our Annotated by the Author series.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643716560', '1683923405'),
(171, 20, 21, 0, 'ddf4f13c-2233-52ac-b782-78f89a637c48', 'In this lesson, students will consider viral Covid misinformation they may have seen, learn about how and why it spreads, and consider how to combat it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/learning/lesson-plans/lesson-of-the-day-covid-test-misinformation-spikes-along-with-spread-of-omicron.html', 'Featured Article: “Covid Test Misinformation Spikes Along With Spread of Omicron”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_199874343_2f528f64-a863-4d76-846f-269f9387444c-articleLarge.jpg', '1643716574', '1683923406'),
(172, 26, 0, 131, 'bfab35d2-4504-56d1-b297-71d2e795a0bd', 'This film wants to spotlight a story of friendship and childhood innocence during the Holocaust, but feels quaint and misguided.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/movies/my-best-friend-anne-frank-review.html', 'Anne Frank once lamented that she might survive the war and her friend, Hannah Goslar, probably would not. It’s a haunting perspective to remember when watching “My Best Friend Anne Frank,” a Dutch film told from the point of view of Hannah. Ben Sombogaart’s costume drama shuttles between Nazi-occupied Amsterdam, where Hannah and Anne are fast friends, and the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp, where they were later imprisoned separately.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_201131271_5df18234-c18f-42cd-b1b5-28cb7c1cce94-articleLarge.jpg', '1643716803', '1683923407'),
(173, 1, 22, 1, '0b71e8fa-4e5e-50e3-9c25-d4921970a051', 'At Iona, Pitino doesn’t have the “bells and whistles” of Louisville, which he left amid scandal. But he has a team undefeated in conference play and looking to return to the N.C.A.A. tournament.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/sports/basketball/rick-pitino-iona-800-wins.html', 'NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. — Sunday was not unfolding as planned for the Iona College men’s basketball team. Visiting St. Peter’s was playing rough-and-tumble ball, which had landed Iona in foul trouble and out of sorts. The frustration was evident when Nelly Junior Joseph, a sophomore center for Iona, tussled fiercely enough over a held ball with St. Peter’s Hassan Drame that both players drew technical fouls in an incident that nearly precipitated a brawl.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_201143934_a5bf1c09-1925-4d0e-aea0-092b502f454a-articleLarge.jpg', '1643716806', '1683923408'),
(174, 1, 23, 132, 'f7b09739-fd26-5160-bf72-152d8461a931', 'Baseball’s players may be locked out, but Dusty Baker, at 72, is hard at work in his vineyards, trusting advice from Willie Stargell and paying tribute to Henry Aaron.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/sports/baseball/dusty-baker-wine.html', 'SACRAMENTO — “Be right back,” Dusty Baker said on a chilly, recent Saturday morning at his home here. The veteran manager had made some final cuts earlier in the week and now it was time to pick up the pieces.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200451735_0cf0f618-2041-4c49-9390-ac3596f11a86-articleLarge.jpg', '1643716951', '1683923409'),
(175, 8, 18, 133, '4d5417af-00ce-59d0-a77f-782d47571c3b', 'Three Israeli military commanders have been reprimanded and reassigned after an investigation into the death of a 78-year-old man after he was detained.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/middleeast/israel-commanders-palestinian-man.html', 'JERUSALEM — Three Israeli military commanders have been disciplined after an investigation into the death of a 78-year-old Palestinian-American man who was detained, gagged and handcuffed by Israeli soldiers in a night raid on his village last month.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643717203', '1683923410'),
(176, 2, 24, 134, 'b22a88ad-1ede-5a11-b043-fb42e13b71be', 'Companies are wrestling with an array of state rules that makes designing pandemic policies tricky.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/dealbook/florida-texas-vaccine-mandates.html', 'Now that the Biden administration’s nationwide coronavirus vaccine mandate for large companies has been overturned by the Supreme Court, employers are left to navigate a thicket of state and local rules. In New York, that means private employers have to require vaccines. In Florida and Texas, laws limit the pandemic protocols they can put in place.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643718817', '1683923411'),
(177, 20, 0, 135, '6967b810-16fa-5318-b28e-6039a7810b73', 'Have you been paying attention to the news recently? See how many of these 10 questions you can get right.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/02/01/learning/01Student-News-Quiz.html', 'Have you been paying attention to the news recently? See how many of these 10 questions you can get right.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643721599', '1683923413'),
(178, 2, 0, 136, '3d40adc1-6d6b-56c5-9572-f9ac891c01a8', 'The oil and gas giant said it would resume its stock buyback program by repurchasing $10 billion in shares over the next two years.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/exxon-earnings-4q-2021.html', 'HOUSTON — Exxon Mobil, the largest American oil company, reported its most robust earnings in seven years on Tuesday as it rode a wave of climbing oil and natural gas prices.', 'The New York Times', '01econ-brf-exxon-articleLarge.jpg', '1643723056', '1683923414'),
(179, 8, 6, 137, '21f4a2bc-d614-5d69-ae50-27cb4afc2f9d', 'The Ukrainian military is training civilians to help defend against a possible Russian invasion and occupation. Our cameras went inside a training center in the southeastern city of Mariupol.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/video/world/europe/100000008182235/ukraine-civilians-training-russia.html', 'The Ukrainian military is training civilians to help defend against a possible Russian invasion and occupation. Our cameras went inside a training center in the southeastern city of Mariupol.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643723598', '1683923415'),
(180, 2, 0, 138, '28dd80f8-41f8-5ebd-a0ef-422cc7ec430c', 'Recent commercial real estate transactions in New York.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/new-york-commercial-real-estate.html', '$1.765 MILLION', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643724007', '1683923416'),
(181, 2, 0, 139, 'bf9ee965-3a69-52e3-af57-61c38ab48a16', 'Logistics firms are finding new options to deal with a scarcity of storage, including building multistory facilities and choosing locations farther from coastal ports.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/warehouses-supply-chain.html', 'As retailers and logistics companies try to stockpile goods to hedge against supply chain problems, they are facing a new challenge: In many parts of the United States, there is little to no space available to stash the merchandise.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200486643_6a3b68bb-3a99-4f49-8a65-5e25b91a6e18-articleLarge.jpg', '1643724015', '1683923417'),
(182, 10, 0, 140, 'd7bccfa8-c5ba-5a06-8c9b-c0e5973206d9', 'An unscientific guide to the tracks that evoke the Golden State.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/us/california-songs.html', 'With its dreamy landscapes and near year-round sunshine, California is the kind of place you could write songs about — and so many people have.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643724073', '1683923418'),
(183, 10, 0, 141, '53f65496-d4ac-5d01-b63a-2bc6dac868e4', 'Lloyd J. Austin’s rejection of the governors’ request to exempt their states’ troops from the national military coronavirus vaccine mandate sets the stage for a possible court fight.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/us/national-guard-vaccine-mandate.html', 'Lloyd J. Austin III, the defense secretary, has written a letter to seven Republican governors, rejecting their requests for exemptions from coronavirus vaccination mandates for their states’ National Guard troops.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643727104', '1683923419'),
(184, 2, 0, 142, '73c11952-c094-55d0-9619-df86d06536df', 'Narendra Modi’s plan calls for a big increase in infrastructure spending. Some say more must be done to create jobs for the country’s young work force.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/india-budget.html', 'NEW DELHI — India’s government on Tuesday unveiled its annual budget, which proposed a significant spending increase for highways, road and airports, but a smaller increase for rural development and employment.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200994498_4dd618af-bd88-490d-aac8-8b7df6efe717-articleLarge.jpg', '1643727257', '1683923420'),
(185, 23, 0, 143, '397ec298-3af9-58a0-81bb-ba38a4c6e479', 'The production, which was canceled at the start of the pandemic, will try again, this time starring Alfie Allen of “Game of Thrones” fame.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/theater/hangmen-broadway.html', '“Hangmen” has been saved from the executioner.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_170330877_654c61ba-1791-4319-bcfb-4a2ff3c9ee87-articleLarge.jpg', '1643727609', '1683923421'),
(186, 27, 0, 0, '94579bd5-6b92-5342-9fae-d2295bf8e369', 'A conversation with the co-founder of Run for Something', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/podcasts/transcript-ezra-klein-interviews-amanda-litman.html', 'Every Tuesday and Friday, Ezra Klein invites you into a conversation about something that matters, like today’s episode with Amanda Litman. Listen wherever you get your podcasts.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643728187', '1683923422'),
(187, 8, 8, 144, '08e4aba5-e6b8-590c-a2e2-fbfd2c30c3e1', 'To find the faithful, preachers in some areas of the Democratic Republic of Congo hold church where the crowds are, on boats traveling the country’s water highway.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/africa/congo-river-pastors.html', 'MBANDAKA, Democratic Republic of Congo — The ebullient soukous music had been blasting from speakers since before dawn, but at 8 a.m., someone aboard the brightly painted boat docked along the Congo River pressed pause, and a pastor picked up a microphone and began preaching at a volume easily heard on shore.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643729028', '1683923423'),
(188, 2, 11, 48, '34c80e61-3617-5649-86c5-3472a08f5f39', 'Employers posted 10.9 million job openings in the last month of 2021, a rise from November but shy of the record set in July.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/economy/job-openings-omicron.html', 'The Omicron variant of the coronavirus has disrupted business and kept millions of people home from work. But in December, at least, it did little to cool off the red-hot job market.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643729364', '1683923423'),
(189, 1, 9, 145, 'f30a18e7-97c2-55e3-88d9-33ec6172686d', 'With seven Super Bowl titles, his first two decades ago at age 24, Brady redefined success for N.F.L. quarterbacks.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/sports/football/tom-brady-goat.html', 'So many details of Tom Brady’s career seem fanciful enough to sound apocryphal.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643729566', '1683923426'),
(190, 3, 15, 107, '028317d7-e03b-58e7-b147-40c22be080b4', 'Mirga Gražinytė-Tyla is a leading contender for top posts at American orchestras. But that doesn’t mean she’s interested.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/arts/music/mirga-grazinyte-tyla-conductor.html', 'MUNICH — Let’s get this out of the way: Don’t expect Mirga Gražinytė-Tyla to be the music director of a major American orchestra any time soon.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643730040', '1683923426'),
(191, 10, 0, 146, '533746f5-bc07-5d98-9f8d-63e991994670', 'A proposed California law would make it easier to hunt feral swine, the voracious “super invaders” that are the bane of some East Bay suburbs.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/us/pigs-san-francisco-california.html', 'MORAGA, Calif. — The residents of the San Francisco Bay Area go to great lengths to accommodate the wealth of wildlife around them.', 'The New York Times', 'CALIFORNIA-PIGS-top-articleLarge.jpg', '1643730790', '1683923427'),
(192, 8, 6, 147, '2b9e54be-0eaa-59b2-9e3f-8b7588f9f335', 'Mr. Breivik, who killed 77 people in two attacks, has served 10 years of a 21-year sentence.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/world/europe/anders-behring-breivik-norway-parole.html', 'Anders Behring Breivik, the Norwegian terrorist who killed 77 people in gun and bomb attacks in 2011, was denied parole on Tuesday by a Norwegian court that said he “appeared devoid of empathy and compassion for the victims of the terror.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643731021', '1683923429'),
(193, 10, 0, 148, '86386ad4-2d63-529c-ae68-4e7ceb83153a', 'Ms. Goldberg’s comments, on Monday’s episode of “The View,” came amid growing ignorance about the Holocaust and rising antisemitism. She has apologized.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/us/whoopi-goldberg-holocaust.html', 'Whoopi Goldberg, the comedian and actress who is also a co-host of the ABC talk show “The View,” will be suspended for two weeks, the network announced Tuesday night, after she said repeatedly during an episode of the show that aired on Monday that the Holocaust was not about race, comments that come at a time of rising antisemitism globally. She later apologized.', 'The New York Times', '01-whoopigoldberg-articleLarge.jpg', '1643731255', '1683923430'),
(194, 15, 0, 149, 'ed9e0cd0-9f90-5869-86e4-0f346c468c07', 'A question about what doesn’t make a mammal a mammal.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/02/01/science/science-quiz-mammals.html', 'A question about what doesn’t make a mammal a mammal.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643731754', '1683923430'),
(196, 13, 0, 151, 'b9e7510f-7926-5ba3-9dc3-c823e26cd3de', 'Obviously.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/opinion/affirmative-action.html', 'My newsletter last week about illiberalism on the political right led to claims, in the Twittersphere and elsewhere, that I was engaging in “whataboutism” or “both-sides-ism,” perhaps even seeking absolution from the woke left by pointing to examples of censorship on the right.', 'The New York Times', '01McWhorter-image2-articleLarge.jpg', '1643732710', '1683923433'),
(197, 2, 0, 152, 'd2a78924-19dc-551d-b2dd-665e27aa08ca', 'With the backing of venture capital and well-known tech investors, Synapticure seeks to fill in the gaps in care and research for those with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/business/als-synapticure-startup.html', 'In August 2017, Brian Wallach’s notion of time changed forever.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200468544_98b5e6e3-2a75-4c6d-ad24-6c0b944b0f72-articleLarge.jpg', '1643733229', '1683923434'),
(198, 3, 15, 153, 'b81b6b1f-dffe-5a32-8c92-e1be785e26c2', 'A biracial woman in a predominantly white, male scene, the X-Ray Spex frontwoman brought fresh perspectives and sounds to punk. A new documentary explores her impact.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/01/arts/music/poly-styrene-i-am-a-cliche-documentary.html', 'Poly Styrene beams out from the screen, smile wide, braces cemented across her teeth. In most images of first-wave punk musicians, their eyes are filled with negativity and contempt. In footage from a new film, Styrene’s are bright with possibility.', 'The New York Times', '06poly-styrene1-articleLarge.jpg', '1643734813', '1683923435'),
(199, 1, 19, 154, '007123a6-65de-59a5-8496-e4aa1997983f', 'In her own words, top freeskier Eileen Gu describes finding the balance between confidence in her ability and the thrill of uncertainty.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/sports/olympics/eileen-gu-skiing-fear.html', 'In her own words, top freeskier Eileen Gu describes finding the balance between confidence in her ability and the thrill of uncertainty.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643734959', '1683923436'),
(200, 1, 19, 154, '1045c231-dbdb-5f37-9d48-fab8d5ba4818', 'Millie Knight, a world champion Paralympic skier, says, “I ski with my ears.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/sports/olympics/skiing-millie-knight-paralympics-fear.html', 'Millie Knight, a world champion Paralympic skier, says, “I ski with my ears.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1643734963', '1683923436'),
(201, 13, 0, 76, '60caff94-4aaa-5bf7-88ae-61fece510fd1', 'The Ukraine war has revealed the Putin regime’s true weakness.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/opinion/putin-military-sanctions-weakness.html', 'Beware, Vladimir Putin: Spring is coming. And when it does, you’ll lose much of whatever leverage you had left.', 'The New York Times', '28krugman-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1646092805', '1683923437'),
(202, 10, 5, 155, 'b0e30a78-8b30-5d51-a5cf-7d42c479ac44', 'The first election night of the 2022 midterms has some famous names and crowded primary races. Here’s a rundown.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/texas-primary-candidates-midterms.html', 'Follow our live updates on the Texas primary election and election results.', 'The New York Times', '28onpolitics-pm-newsletter-cpac-articleLarge.jpg', '1646093141', '1683923438'),
(203, 10, 5, 156, '7f1b9401-cdcf-5919-8894-034681655d6d', 'The speech was originally going to center primarily on the president’s domestic agenda. But the war in Europe has forced the White House to change gears.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/biden-state-of-the-union.html', 'WASHINGTON — President Biden will use his first State of the Union address on Tuesday to claim credit for a robust economy and a unified global response to Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, even as he acknowledges the pain of inflation and the struggle between “democracy and autocracy” around the world, administration officials said on Monday.', 'The New York Times', '28dc-speech-top-articleLarge.jpg', '1646093158', '1683923439'),
(204, 10, 5, 157, '9b1a4ff4-fd6b-50b2-ae26-a50dd4d44047', 'The participation of Representatives Marjorie Taylor Greene and Paul Gosar at a far-right event renewed calls for Republican leaders to root out extremism in their party.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/republicans-extremism-marjorie-taylor-greene.html', 'WASHINGTON — Republican congressional leaders on Monday broke their silence about the participation of two House Republicans at a far-right conference with ties to white supremacy, denouncing the actions of Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene of Georgia and Representative Paul Gosar of Arizona.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202898478_f5f33277-b655-45ec-b5b0-f642fc76671e-articleLarge.jpg', '1646093204', '1683923441'),
(205, 10, 5, 158, '9edba9b7-d940-5ce4-ac3b-2fc97179ef99', 'As a financier, he amassed a fortune that he spent on Democrats, helping to propel his wife from San Francisco mayor to a long career in the Senate.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/richard-blum-dead.html', 'Richard C. Blum, a financier and major donor to Democrats — above all his wife, Senator Dianne Feinstein of California — died on Sunday at the family home in San Francisco. He was 86.', 'The New York Times', '28blum1-articleLarge.jpg', '1646093489', '1683923442'),
(206, 8, 6, 159, 'ba404688-280d-505a-b39f-d82b4048e8e8', 'In a rare show of dissent, three deputies of the State Duma have expressed regret about the attack.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/world/europe/russia-parliament-ukraine-invasion.html', 'Three members of Russia’s rubber-stamp Parliament have criticized their country’s war in Ukraine, a rare episode of dissent from within the Russian establishment.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646093513', '1683923442'),
(207, 10, 5, 160, '864db5ae-f2ed-5fb5-a277-26a87726c4a0', 'With a Supreme Court ruling looming, both parties expect the issue to resonate in this year’s midterm elections.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/abortion-rights-measure-senate.html', 'WASHINGTON — Republicans on Monday blocked the Senate from taking up sweeping abortion rights legislation as Democrats sought to put lawmakers on the record on the issue in advance of the midterm elections and a coming Supreme Court ruling on access to abortion.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_197147376_5c58e829-d92c-4198-a27d-5f201bc87467-articleLarge.jpg', '1646093949', '1683923445'),
(208, 10, 5, 82, 'e0e49ea7-47b5-5007-9208-3ed03bc60da7', 'A security fence, National Guard troops and more police surround the Capitol in preparation for the State of the Union address and a possible truck convoy of protesters.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/capitol-security-sotu-truck-convoy.html', 'WASHINGTON — Officials have ramped up security around the Capitol to levels not seen in months before President Biden’s State of the Union address set for Tuesday, as lawmakers brace for planned convoys of protesting truck drivers descending on Washington.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_203006418_dcdf5428-13ba-4c7c-a828-8455c4e89373-articleLarge.jpg', '1646094373', '1683923446'),
(209, 8, 6, 161, '9e37eca3-b18a-5b9f-ac84-475df33e9d77', 'The move is part of a larger effort to isolate Russia diplomatically and economically since it invaded Ukraine last week.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/world/europe/us-russian-diplomats-un.html', 'With Russia’s invasion of Ukraine the center of attention at the United Nations, the United States said Monday that it would expel 12 Russian diplomats from Moscow’s U.N. mission, saying they were actually intelligence operatives who had spied on the United States.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646094431', '1683923447'),
(210, 2, 0, 162, '7be378c4-0cd7-588c-ba24-8d7b548bf6a0', 'Cryptocurrency has provided a way for investors to quickly move funds to Ukrainian fighters.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/business/ukraine-crypto-donations.html', 'As Russia’s invasion escalated over the weekend, Ukrainian officials made an unusual request on Twitter: Send us your crypto.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_176199291_04fdd43b-0a65-434f-b89e-bda295408e7f-articleLarge.jpg', '1646094673', '1683923448'),
(211, 13, 0, 163, '25bb6c32-40f7-5e41-90d7-b65e25e55644', 'Idealism has been a powerful weapon in the resistance against Russia.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/opinion/ukraine-victory.html', 'I met Volodymyr Yermolenko, a Ukrainian philosopher and the chief editor of UkraineWorld, an English-language news site, in Kyiv in 2019. I’d gone there to report on how Ukrainians felt about Donald Trump’s attempts to extort their president, Volodymyr Zelensky, and on the American right’s demonization of Ukrainians who’d worked against corruption. Yermolenko spoke, then, of Ukraine as a front line in the global battle between democracy and authoritarianism, with Europe on one side and Vladimir Putin’s Russia on the other — and the role of the United States under Trump confusing and ambiguous.', 'The New York Times', '28goldberg-SWAP-articleLarge.jpg', '1646095067', '1683923450'),
(212, 8, 0, 164, 'f00b2937-31d2-5ecd-9041-c2376df2e49c', 'A court has given the Congolese control of one of the world’s largest sources of cobalt while allegations against the mine’s Chinese owners are investigated.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/world/congo-cobalt-mining-china.html', 'A court in the Democratic Republic of Congo has sidelined the Chinese owner of one of the world’s largest copper and cobalt mines, a major victory for the Congolese government as it seeks to become a bigger player in the global clean energy revolution.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646095513', '1683923451'),
(213, 10, 5, 79, 'd6839d8a-c128-5ceb-953d-6da3152ef9e7', 'After years of talks about the need for public-private partnerships to combat cyberattacks, the war in Ukraine is stress-testing the system.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/ukraine-russia-microsoft.html', 'WASHINGTON — Last Wednesday, a few hours before Russian tanks began rolling into Ukraine, alarms went off inside Microsoft’s Threat Intelligence Center, warning of a never-before-seen piece of “wiper” malware that appeared aimed at the country’s government ministries and financial institutions.', 'The New York Times', '28dc-cyber-train-articleLarge.jpg', '1646095858', '1683923452'),
(214, 15, 0, 165, 'd8f70e17-0467-5ab8-972f-00ad26193b1f', 'The premise, put forth in a new paper, highlights an assortment of tensions in dinosaur paleontology, including how subjective the naming of species can be.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/science/tyrannosaurus-rex-species.html', 'Tyrannosaurus rex is the most iconic dinosaur. Its skeletons hold pride of place in museums around the world, and sell for millions of dollars at auction — and a bounty of relatively complete specimens have made it the most thoroughly studied dinosaur in the world.', 'The New York Times', '01sci-trex-longex-articleLarge.jpg', '1646096410', '1683923453'),
(215, 1, 9, 7, '58ca37c1-5703-5dbe-9b3a-ed33ff95cd21', 'Grambling had received backlash after Briles, Baylor’s coach when leaders mishandled sexual assault accusations against players, was hired last week.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/sports/football/art-briles-grambling-state.html', 'Art Briles, the former Baylor football coach who was hired last week as Grambling State University’s offensive coordinator, has resigned four days after being hired.', 'The New York Times', '28grambling-briles-articleLarge.jpg', '1646098819', '1683923454'),
(216, 2, 0, 2, '1db00257-6e76-5104-a278-0b6149b2790e', 'Affected films include “The Batman” from Warner and “Turning Red” from Disney-Pixar.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/business/disney-warner-bros-russia.html', 'Disney said on Monday that it was “pausing” the release of films in Russia, becoming the first Hollywood studio to weigh in publicly on the matter. Warner Bros., which had vowed to press on with the release of “The Batman,” reversed course soon after Disney’s announcement and said it, too, would enact a pause.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202853028_ff067ef9-021c-4fe6-82f4-da58ee6906af-articleLarge.jpg', '1646099246', '1683923455'),
(217, 2, 0, 166, '6a556a4d-d0ab-55f8-9be1-70eef9dd26f7', 'The proposed settlement, which requires a judge’s approval, would resolve a legal battle that began after the company, in 2016, raised the price for two EpiPens to $608 from $100.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/business/viatris-epipen-settlement.html', 'Viatris, the drugmaker previously known as Mylan, announced on Monday that it had agreed to pay $264 million to settle a class-action lawsuit that alleged the company was involved in an illegal scheme to monopolize the market for epinephrine auto-injector devices known as EpiPens, which are used to treat severe allergic reactions.', 'The New York Times', '28xp-viatris-articleLarge.jpg', '1646099762', '1683923456'),
(218, 10, 0, 167, '1136214c-4c87-5b31-8c70-dcda8925c0ef', 'Americans are less worried about both catching and spreading the coronavirus than they were six months ago, as the once-surging Omicron variant recedes in the United States and in much of the world, according to a new poll by The Associated Press-NORC Cen', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/a-new-poll-finds-americans-fears-about-the-virus-are-waning.html', 'Americans are less worried about both catching and spreading the coronavirus than they were six months ago, as the once-surging Omicron variant recedes in the United States and in much of the world, according to a new poll by The Associated Press-NORC Center for Public Affairs Research.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646101769', '1683923457'),
(219, 10, 5, 168, '8222b145-79f5-534a-84f1-f8658900a97d', 'Lawmakers in both parties hailed the action as historic, but a separate bill to outlaw discrimination based on a person’s natural hair failed amid Republican opposition.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/politics/house-lynching-hate-crime.html', 'WASHINGTON — The House on Monday overwhelmingly approved legislation that would make lynching a federal hate crime, moving to formally outlaw a brutal act that has become a symbol of the failure by Congress and the country to reckon with the history of racial violence in America.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_200586306_f83bda06-2ee0-4d05-854e-58c25c5324e0-articleLarge.jpg', '1646102164', '1683923458'),
(220, 4, 0, 75, 'bca7c751-ed1e-5121-a82d-cafb91ab9e17', 'Lisa Senzel and Jeff Chen let the good times roll.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-03-01.html', 'TUESDAY PUZZLE — This is a day of celebrations here in the Wordplay column! First, we’re celebrating Lisa Senzel’s auspicious New York Times Crossword debut, a fabulous puzzle that she made with the veteran constructor Jeff Chen. According to Mr. Chen’s site, XWord Info, Ms. Senzel is the 17th constructor to debut in 2022.', 'The New York Times', '01wordplay-clouds-articleLarge.jpg', '1646103607', '1683923459'),
(221, 10, 0, 166, 'ebe7c4bc-6196-5969-b812-9ca7d7013cad', 'The man also fatally shot an adult before killing himself during what appeared to be a supervised visit, the authorities said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/us/church-shooting-sacramento.html', 'A man believed to be meeting his three children for a supervised visit at a church just outside Sacramento on Monday afternoon fatally shot the children and an adult accompanying them before killing himself, police officials said.', 'The New York Times', '28xp-sacramento-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1646103911', '1683923460'),
(222, 1, 9, 169, '62a5ee6a-906a-57c9-bd00-e0202144752d', 'The league’s annual talent evaluation has become prime time viewing, but disputes over protocols and the rise of other scouting forums have prompted some to call for an overhaul.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/sports/football/nfl-combine.html', 'For 40 years, college football players hoping to be drafted by an N.F.L. team have shown off their speed, strength and personalities at the league’s most important talent evaluation — the scouting combine.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_169877232_0e83eddb-0417-4abb-a30a-2bac2414d1ab-articleLarge.jpg', '1646110866', '1683923461'),
