(255, 20, 0, 190, 'b6d4e224-4560-5621-9d53-355ef1e3491f', 'Is choosing not to respond to texts, emails and other digital messages rude? Or is it sometimes necessary?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/learning/do-you-ever-ignore-text-messages.html', 'Have you ever gotten so overwhelmed by texts, emails, direct messages on social media and chatter in Discord servers and group chats that you just … stopped responding?', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128809', '1683923495'),
(256, 24, 0, 191, 'd6a59340-e4b0-5068-a3d2-08bfbb22b513', 'With online auctions there’s no accounting for taste — only paying a price for it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/magazine/online-auction-art.html', 'You can blame George and Martha Washington for my love affair with online art auctions — or actually, two bedraggled dolls made in the image of the original first couple. They were a little more than a foot tall, made of carved wood and wire and painted by an unknown hand ages ago. “George’s hair has thinned, Martha is missing her right thumb,” read the sales description. They seduced me despite their dingy colonial attire and faces that had the waxed shine of supermarket fruit. To me, they were folk relics that embodied American culture: neither trash or treasure but a bit of both. They sold for 90 bucks.', 'The New York Times', '06mag-LOR-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128810', '1683923496'),
(257, 13, 0, 192, 'e6172d3e-bb36-515c-a931-52faa91cfadb', 'It has all the mystery and half the charm of a slapped-together awards show. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/opinion/state-of-the-union.html', 'More than a century ago, Woodrow Wilson gave the first in-person presidential address to Congress since Thomas Jefferson ended the practice in 1801. The new tradition stuck and eventually became the template for the president’s annual “message to Congress.” It was Franklin Roosevelt who used the phrase “the State of the Union” in one of those speeches, and by the late 1940s, it had become our national shorthand for the speech. The 20th century transformed what had been, for most of American history, a staid, written report into a giant annual spectacle of presidential majesty and congressional hooting and hollering.', 'The New York Times', '01Bacharach-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128810', '1683923497'),
(258, 12, 0, 193, '43182beb-1cb8-59be-9e24-3d50e780d04a', 'In her new book, Amy Bloom writes about loving her husband and helping him to end his life after a diagnosis of Alzheimer’s.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/books/review-in-love-memoir-amy-bloom.html', 'Amy Bloom and Brian Ameche were a handsome couple. I know this not because there’s a photograph of them in Bloom’s new memoir, “In Love,” about his Alzheimer’s and their search for a painless and dignified way for him to end his life. There isn’t.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128811', '1683923498'),
(259, 13, 0, 175, '5ed76056-4b4d-50d4-bd43-6856c0449575', 'For a community of Black women in New Orleans, dressing up as baby dolls is a tradition in which they’re encouraged to be free.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/opinion/you-cant-stop-spirit-mardi-gras.html', 'The short documentary above celebrates womanhood by spotlighting the baby dolls — one of the earliest Mardi Gras traditions established by Black women.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128811', '1683923499');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(260, 10, 0, 194, '87e684b8-1d41-516c-90a0-640e65d123d6', 'The crime has made a resurgence across the country over the past two years, and many of those arrested are startlingly young.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/us/car-theft-teens-pandemic.html', 'WASHINGTON — The quiet alley behind his mother’s house was where Tariq Majeed, a 45-year-old father of three, often came for some uninterrupted work. He ran a car-detailing business, and around midday on a chilly Tuesday in late January he was deep-cleaning the back seats of a client’s BMW. He felt a nudge from behind and turned to find it was a gun.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202861971_a1d9bf29-209f-40f6-a3a8-dc17e2199e87-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128814', '1683923500'),
(261, 17, 0, 195, 'ba10ea1d-09a7-5d5e-bbaf-c330ab7427a4', 'Evidence on global warming is piling up. Nations aren’t acting. Some researchers are asking what difference more reports will make.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/climate/ipcc-climate-scientists-strike.html', 'Sometimes, Bruce C. Glavovic feels so proud to be an environmental scientist, studying coastal planning and teaching future researchers, that it moves him to tears.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202589586_d6b7451b-3f52-4e40-9b8c-9a1678c4d1fe-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128816', '1683923502'),
(262, 2, 0, 196, '221814a0-fee4-595a-a66e-3626fa168a0e', 'The woman became a symbol of injustice and authorities’ incompetence in fighting human trafficking, posing a credibility challenge to an omnipotent government.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/china-chained-woman-social-media.html', 'The Chinese government faces a quandary: how to convince its people that what it said about a chained woman is true.', 'The New York Times', '24newworld-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128817', '1683923503'),
(263, 10, 0, 197, '3c07f3a4-2538-5aec-a0ac-359d56a24f15', 'The process behind calling elections: how The Times will report live election results during the 2022 primary season.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/article/election-results-process-explained.html', 'Follow our live election results of the Texas primary.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128817', '1683923504'),
(264, 13, 0, 198, '8bc50a0e-5db2-5989-a270-c480fd425387', 'Nations are not secure unless their food supplies are. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/opinion/what-the-war-in-ukraine-means-for-the-worlds-food-supply.html', 'As we watch Ukrainian refugees arrive by car and foot in Poland, it’s hard not to recall World War II, when the region was ravaged by fighting, famine spread and millions of Ukrainians died of starvation.', 'The New York Times', '01puma_1-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128817', '1683923505'),
(265, 13, 0, 0, '342a6839-a4e7-5cd1-aabd-4430d25e4811', 'The economic historian Adam Tooze explains how the invasion of Ukraine is inciting war in the financial markets.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/opinion/ezra-klein-podcast-adam-tooze.html', 'There’s the Russia-Ukraine war that’s easy to follow in the news right now. We can watch Russian bombs falling on Ukraine, see Russian tanks smoking on the side of the road, hear from Ukrainian resistance fighters livestreaming their desperate defense.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128819', '1683923506'),
(266, 9, 0, 117, 'fc363067-386b-5f1f-86f1-51a3c8b1f1f8', 'All it takes is a tiny space — a niche, a shallow closet or even a cabinet — to make a cocktail bar that’s a thing of beauty. Here’s how.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/realestate/how-to-create-a-home-bar-that-will-dazzle-your-guests.html', 'The pleasures of visiting a cocktail bar extend well beyond the libations. It’s just as much about the company, the atmosphere, all the accouterments. At home, a thoughtfully designed bar can create a similar feeling and serve as a special place for after-work drinks and celebrations with family and friends.', 'The New York Times', 'oakImage-1646062762472-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128819', '1683923507'),
(267, 24, 0, 199, 'bc7883ac-53cb-5a48-9df0-51e6e7c6cd57', 'Research shows that survivors of abuse can sustain head trauma more often than football players. But they are almost never diagnosed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/magazine/brain-trauma-domestic-violence.html', 'In 2017, when Becky was about to turn 40, she woke up in the middle of the night and was startled by her reflection in the bathroom mirror. Her face, gaunt from weight loss, looked pale. A scar snaked under her chin from when her boyfriend punched her. Her nostrils were now asymmetrical from when he broke her nose. Smaller scars marked her eyebrows and her bottom lip, where a tooth once cut through. She always wore her hair in a bun to mask a bald spot; he had slammed her head against a door frame, and she had needed staples there. She could barely hear from one ear.', 'The New York Times', '06mag-tbi-02-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128820', '1683923508'),
(268, 10, 5, 200, 'd40ec8c8-d8c1-5c10-a8cd-fe13ad84a449', 'Much of the funding is left up to state leaders, some of whom have already pushed back on the federal government’s goals. Mr. Landrieu will be key to resolving those differences.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/us/politics/mitch-landrieu-infrastructure-biden.html', 'WASHINGTON — At a rare formal news conference in January, President Biden hailed the $1 trillion infrastructure package that Democrats and Republicans had recently approved, promising that miles of roads would be rebuilt, railways and bridges would be upgraded, and America’s public transit system would become a source of international envy.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_197947659_908ab8d0-4162-4be6-928b-5c5b8375a588-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128820', '1683923509'),
(269, 10, 5, 81, 'd9b4ca04-f8e8-5031-ba82-2959758a7ac4', 'In the Texas race for governor, Gov. Greg Abbott overcame several opponents on his right, and Beto O’Rourke sailed to the Democratic nomination.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/us/politics/texas-primary-midterms-democrats-gop.html', 'HOUSTON — Gov. Greg Abbott of Texas fended off two right-wing primary challengers on Tuesday, avoiding a runoff by a wide margin but still falling well short of the 90 percent of the vote he marshaled in the primary four years ago as a restive Republican base continues to push the party farther to the right.', 'The New York Times', '01pol-texas-abbot02-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128820', '1683923511'),
(270, 25, 0, 201, '3e7f6094-4f89-5c12-9ea2-7ede658869c8', 'During the pandemic lockdown, when solitude dredged up the regret of missed opportunities, one writer hiked over the Pyrenees Mountains to better understand her father.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/travel/holocaust-pyrenees-jewish-refugees.html', 'His legs were scratched and bloody, but Henri never complained. That’s all I was told about my father’s escape from the Germans over the Pyrenees Mountains some time in the second half of 1940. He was 5 years old, his sister, Cecile, was 3, and the day they walked out of their apartment in Paris’s 17th Arrondissement, my grandmother left pots of unfinished food on the stove lest any neighbors, nosy or Nazi, became dangerously curious.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_197227404_99caf41d-d590-4236-88f7-34ec5da02a8f-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128821', '1683923512'),
(271, 5, 0, 202, '5672ee9a-797c-5e76-9cd9-f678784acdfa', 'The Republican State Convention is giving party leaders a chance to test messages about crime, inflation and Democratic leadership.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/nyregion/republicans-midterm-election-ny.html', 'GARDEN CITY, N.Y. — Four months after Republicans scored upset victories around the country and in local races across New York, the state’s party leaders gathered at a plush hotel in a Long Island village this week, painting a bleak picture of life under Democratic rule.', 'The New York Times', '01nygop31-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128821', '1683923513'),
(272, 23, 0, 203, '616c110a-1531-5962-a4bb-8abb58f564bb', '“As much as it hurts, tell the truth,” says the Tony-winning performer and playwright, tracing his path from Brooklyn to Broadway.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/theater/harvey-fierstein-memoir.html', 'Harvey Fierstein contains multitudes. The playwright, screenwriter, actor and drag performer has inhabited at least as many personalities as Walt Whitman. With trademark wit and empathy, he has written about himself in “Torch Song Trilogy”; a father with a drag queen partner and a straight son in “La Cage Aux Folles”; the bootlegging song and dance man Legs Diamond; English factory workers and an unlikely firebrand in “Kinky Boots”; heterosexual cross dressers in “Casa Valentina”; striking newspaper boys in his Broadway adaptation of “Newsies”; and a sissy duckling for an HBO animated special.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202638195_25edbb4d-a1f7-41d8-a140-f44d669e1521-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128821', '1683923514'),
(273, 22, 0, 118, '5c2cf9e7-ec30-5195-8837-94b582b57a9b', 'For years, a coalition of groups has supported food businesses, seeing them as critical to the city’s continuing recovery. The pandemic has put its accomplishments to the test.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/dining/detroit-restaurants.html', 'DETROIT — April Anderson built Good Cakes and Bakes, her bakery on this city’s west side, by attracting customers to linger over cupcakes and cookies inside a 70-seat storefront on Livernois Avenue.', 'The New York Times', '01-detroit-restaurants8-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128823', '1683923515'),
(274, 10, 0, 204, 'f3b54802-9a29-5bdc-acfb-63fd57574ee1', 'With so much evidence of racism, said Marcus Ransom, the only Black man on the jury, it was not difficult to find Ahmaud Arbery’s murderers guilty of hate crimes.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/us/arbery-trial-juror-marcus-ransom.html', 'ATLANTA — After each day of jury service in the hate crimes trial of the men who murdered Ahmaud Arbery, Marcus Ransom went to his hotel room and prayed.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_203019267_7a01c244-a799-499c-a1c9-380277c96a95-articleLarge.jpg', '1646128823', '1683923516'),
(275, 8, 0, 205, '7af77073-00d6-5613-be19-60cbae0037e8', 'The coronavirus vaccine made by Pfizer-BioNTech is much less effective in preventing infection in children ages 5 to 11 years than in older adolescents or adults, according to a large new set of data collected by health officials in New York State — a fin', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/world/the-pfizer-vaccine-is-less-effective-in-5-to-11-year-olds-than-in-older-groups-new-data-show.html', 'The coronavirus vaccine made by Pfizer-BioNTech is much less effective in preventing infection in children ages 5 to 11 years than in older adolescents or adults, according to a large new set of data collected by health officials in New York State — a finding that has significant ramifications for these children and their parents.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128829', '1683923517'),
(276, 8, 14, 206, 'aac95928-8c1e-5744-8b40-62eeef153ae1', 'President Biden will use his State of the Union address Tuesday night in part to announce steps to protect nursing home residents and hold providers accountable for unsafe and substandard care, including by expanding inspections and financial penalties on', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/americas/biden-will-lay-out-new-nursing-home-protections-in-his-state-of-the-union-speech.html', 'President Biden will use his State of the Union address Tuesday night in part to announce steps to protect nursing home residents and hold providers accountable for unsafe and substandard care, including by expanding inspections and financial penalties on what the White House is calling “bad actor nursing homes” and “poor-performing facilities.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128829', '1683923518'),
(277, 8, 4, 10, '7194a858-7ca1-5349-951e-a4622f73d4d6', 'A mosque dispute in a conservative city has forced some South Koreans to confront what it means to live in an increasingly diverse society.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/asia/south-korea-diversity-muslims.html', 'DAEGU, South Korea — Inside the dimly lit house, young Muslim men knelt and prayed in silence. Outside, their Korean neighbors gathered with angry signs to protest “a den of terrorists” moving into their neighborhood.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646128830', '1683923519'),
(278, 24, 0, 207, 'ac07644f-cb9d-5e15-a96b-4ff0432f465d', '“We’re not dealing with a grass-roots movement,” Chesa Boudin said. “We’re dealing with a small number of wealthy individuals.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/03/01/magazine/chesa-boudin-interview.html', '“We’re not dealing with a grass-roots movement,” Chesa Boudin said. “We’re dealing with a small number of wealthy individuals.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646129221', '1683923519'),
(279, 8, 4, 208, '68a4a525-aab2-5f48-ae39-9ada7d2cf00d', 'Many in Taiwan see parallels with Ukraine. “We must use this time of peace to prepare for the worst,” says a nonprofit working to promote civil defense.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/asia/ukraine-taiwan-china-russia.html', 'TAIPEI, Taiwan — Since Russia invaded Ukraine, Justin Huang, a 23-year-old recent university graduate in Taiwan, has been gripped by news of the crisis, just like many other people around the world. He has pored over reports about Ukrainians signing up for the military and scrutinized video footage of Russian missiles hitting residential buildings. He has been deeply disturbed by Russia’s brazen disregard for global norms.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646131217', '1683923520'),
(280, 1, 23, 209, 'f1b334ee-3d55-5361-a192-ffe3355e80b2', 'The league announced on Tuesday that it would delay the start of the 2022 regular season after it failed to reach a new collective bargaining agreement with the players’ union.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/sports/baseball/mlb-lockout.html', 'JUPITER, Fla. — Major League Baseball will cancel the first two series of the 2022 regular season on Tuesday after it failed to reach a new collective bargaining agreement with the players’ union by its self-imposed deadline, Commissioner Rob Manfred announced in a news conference Tuesday afternoon.', 'The New York Times', '01mlb-lockout-top-articleLarge.jpg', '1646131514', '1683923521'),
(281, 27, 20, 210, '3a65bbad-a52f-5025-8488-bd62d47d9c82', 'As hundreds of thousands of citizens flee the Russian advance, the country’s government has ordered men ages 18 to 60 to remain.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/podcasts/the-daily/ukraine-russia-kyiv-civilian-military.html', 'This episode contains strong language.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646132409', '1683923522'),
(282, 8, 0, 211, '49228bee-539c-5649-8266-5d42b01b5c1a', 'In January, at the height of the Omicron wave, one-quarter of U.S. schoolchildren missed more than a week of in-person learning, according to a national survey of 148,400 parents by The New York Times and the survey and data firm Dynata.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/02/28/world/school-is-back-in-person-but-many-children-arent-back-to-full-time.html', 'In January, at the height of the Omicron wave, one-quarter of U.S. schoolchildren missed more than a week of in-person learning, according to a national survey of 148,400 parents by The New York Times and the survey and data firm Dynata.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646132883', '1683923523'),
(283, 19, 0, 129, '9bd76268-3122-5a32-bc82-1f2c6520df43', 'But many experts are worried about what happens next.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/briefing/russia-invasion-ukraine-fighting.html', 'The initial days of the Ukrainian invasion have not gone well for Russia.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646133773', '1683923524'),
(284, 26, 0, 212, '047a2651-0953-522d-a3f6-db254de1723d', 'This documentary looks back at a Cold War defection drama that took place off the coast of Massachusetts.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/movies/the-jump-review.html', 'In its first half-hour, the documentary “The Jump” brings a bracing immediacy to a 50-year-old Cold War incident. In 1970, a Lithuanian sailor, Simas Kudirka, jumped from a Soviet trawler onto a U.S. Coast Guard vessel off Martha’s Vineyard in an effort to defect from the Soviet Union. (The boats were moored alongside each other for talks on fishing rights.)', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202798530_96baf7f4-4604-4158-bd77-95948ac44c44-articleLarge.jpg', '1646136006', '1683923525'),
(285, 28, 0, 213, 'd2a46059-d13f-55b2-84cf-7bc623b213d4', 'From hibiscus to borage to violet, blooms are showing up in drinks and lending them beauty, decadence and a flavor all their own.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/t-magazine/flowers-cocktails-drinks.html', 'ALL IS DARK as the bartender slides across a peach-colored cocktail balanced on a slim glass stem — a Lauren Bacall of a drink. There’s something called a buzz bud, a little furled blossom, on top. I sip and taste notes of lemon and honey. Then, as instructed, I eat the tiny bud, and something strange happens: My mouth feels shivery, almost numb. It’s disconcerting. Acmella oleracea, also known as buzz buttons or electric daisies, are known for their potent tingling effect. I’m not sure I like it. I’m not sure that’s even the point. When I take the next sip, the cocktail seems altered, almost pixelated — like shifting from animation to high-definition. I taste the drink more clearly and cleanly. Lemon. Honey. All of it melted into a near-buttery dissolution.', 'The New York Times', '01tmag-cocktailflowers-slide-7JVP-articleLarge.jpg', '1646136013', '1683923526'),
(286, 8, 6, 214, 'edced78c-4c1e-55ef-8c6b-70063045e4f9', 'In the former Communist East, security officials worry that a long-running movement against Covid restrictions is becoming an incubator of political violence.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/europe/01virus-briefing-germany-protests.html', 'DRESDEN, Germany — First vaccine opponents attacked the police. Then a group of them chatted online about killing the governor. And one day an angry crowd beating drums and carrying torches showed up outside the house of the health minister of the eastern state of Saxony.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646136485', '1683923527'),
(287, 11, 0, 173, 'cb301193-e3bd-5cca-afa6-39479e06fa66', 'Glenn Martens is no longer a niche taste.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/style/glenn-martens-diesel-y-project-gaultier.html', 'It was the first big show of Milan Fashion Week: 1 p.m. on Day 1.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202657395_6f4eb286-3596-475a-8f9a-819d7d29b083-articleLarge.jpg', '1646137311', '1683923528'),
(288, 8, 6, 215, 'efaa050f-ec8e-5719-a09c-512633a62227', 'The British monarch is feeling well enough to return to her duties, Buckingham Palace said, easing concerns about the 95-year-old’s health.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/europe/queen-elizabeth-covid-free.html', 'LONDON — Queen Elizabeth II is returning to work after a Covid scare, Buckingham Palace said on Tuesday, ending more than a week of heightened concern about the health of Britain’s longest-reigning monarch after it was announced that she had tested positive for the coronavirus.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646138576', '1683923530'),
(289, 20, 0, 216, '3333c144-5162-5212-baeb-57fb71d206d6', 'Have you been paying attention to the news recently? See how many of these 10 questions you can get right.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/03/01/learning/01Student-News-Quiz.html', 'Have you been paying attention to the news recently? See how many of these 10 questions you can get right.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646139199', '1683923532'),
(290, 2, 24, 134, '8ae9cd33-d0a2-5cce-8485-b95ba988dfb9', 'Investors are weighing the implications of Russian sanctions — and a new Cold War.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/dealbook/russia-sanctions-markets-cold-war.html', 'As severe sanctions against Russia take shape, economists, executives and investors around the world are trying to gauge the effects. Europe and its allies will wage “total economic and financial war,” Bruno Le Maire, France’s economy minister, said today. “We are going to cause the Russian economy to collapse.”', 'The New York Times', '01db-newsletter-russiamarkets-articleLarge.jpg', '1646139516', '1683923533'),
(291, 20, 0, 0, 'defe3520-f27d-5525-8fac-e0447c96249d', 'How many recent Words of the Day can you use correctly in a 50-word story? Send us yours by March 31.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/learning/march-vocabulary-challenge-write-a-story-using-our-words-of-the-day.html', 'Note: Winners of our January Vocabulary Challenge are published at the bottom of this post.', 'The New York Times', '01MarchVocabLN-articleLarge.jpg', '1646139529', '1683923535'),
(292, 5, 0, 217, '177092eb-cceb-5fa7-b13b-5204912978e6', 'A study found that retention varied widely by grade, and that enrollment was declining in younger grades, in line with a national trend that has some educators alarmed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/nyregion/nyc-school-retention-pandemic.html', 'Student retention in New York City schools, the nation’s largest public school system, has risen slightly since the pandemic began, according to a report released on Tuesday. But data in the report suggests that enrollment of new students is declining in the city, especially in the younger grades — adding to a national trend.', 'The New York Times', '28virus-briefing-nyc-schools-retention-articleLarge.jpg', '1646139859', '1683923536'),
(293, 2, 0, 218, '963423bd-e331-5686-8327-a473d72a2fcf', 'The announcement was aimed to assure markets that there would be “no shortfall” as a result of Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, but oil prices kept rising, closing above $100 a barrel.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/ukraine-russia-oil.html', 'As oil prices soared in the sharpest one-day jump since Russia’s invasion of Ukraine last week, more than two dozen countries agreed on Tuesday to release 60 million barrels of oil from their emergency reserves, aiming to send a “strong message” that there will be “no shortfall as a result of Russia’s invasion of Ukraine.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646140106', '1683923536'),
(294, 8, 4, 219, 'a35e06b1-c0f0-56ab-bcd6-6f2a9c4afd21', 'A nation isolated in a hostile region increasingly dominated by China, its challenge is to engage the West while not abandoning ties with an old ally.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/asia/india-russia-united-states-ukraine.html', 'NEW DELHI — When India abstained from a United Nations vote and the chorus of Western condemnation against the Ukraine invasion, it appeared to be taking sides: offering tacit support for President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646141305', '1683923537'),
(295, 8, 6, 220, '75964dec-b3f1-5497-a4b9-41361056eb41', 'The two countries have had strong economic ties for decades, but the invasion of Ukraine has spurred the government in Rome to realign with European allies — at an outsize cost.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/europe/ukraine-russia-italy-sanctions.html', 'ROCCA DI MEZZO, Italy — As Italian skiers kicked the snow off their boots and warmed up in the lobby of his lodge in the Apennine Mountains, the hotel owner worried what European sanctions on Russia would do to his already astronomically high heating bills.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646141406', '1683923538'),
(296, 2, 0, 134, 'db2bb594-b82e-5645-a1cb-34474a92dac5', 'The tennis star’s firm, Serena Ventures, will invest in founders with diverse points of view.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/serena-williams-venture-fund.html', 'Serena Williams’s early-stage venture capital firm, Serena Ventures, has raised an inaugural fund of $111 million that will invest in founders with diverse points of view, she told the DealBook newsletter. The investment firm led by the tennis star is already an active angel investor with a portfolio of 60 companies that includes SendWave, MasterClass and Daily Harvest.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_197873013_64ccec90-155a-4da2-bc81-97d5d932ea2a-articleLarge.jpg', '1646142031', '1683923539'),
(297, 10, 0, 221, 'f877aafb-5b97-502b-b0ea-b86febf961ed', 'This winter’s extreme rainfall and dryness might average out to near-normal levels of precipitation. But that’s no insurance policy against fire, scientists say.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/us/california-fires.html', 'When rain pummeled California in October, many breathed a sigh of relief: At least in some parts of the state, the worst of the fire season, experts said, was most likely over.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646142129', '1683923540'),
(298, 8, 6, 222, 'ae62272f-fa6d-5a99-ad27-6262d9e0b993', 'Sergey Lavrov accused Ukraine of seeking to acquire nuclear weapons, an unsubstantiated claim that Moscow has used as justification for its invasion.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/world/europe/lavrov-speech-un.html', 'GENEVA — About 100 diplomats, many from Western countries, walked out of a speech by Russia’s foreign minister at the United Nations Human Rights Council on Tuesday in protest over his country’s invasion of Ukraine.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1646142413', '1683923541'),
(299, 2, 0, 223, '9ce98518-7421-54db-a7a7-3250ede048a1', 'Developers have recently realized the value of even the most minor waterways for commerce, but experts advise caution because of flooding risks.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/creek-development-urban-renewal.html', 'Trotwood is a hard-luck suburb of Dayton, Ohio. With a population of about 25,000, it was once the region’s premier retail and entertainment destination. The city boasted one of the area’s first enclosed malls, numerous shopping plazas, big-box retailers and a 5,500-seat arena.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_202234050_c18d4497-dcd0-4da5-b0e8-f22e2cb6b7b9-articleLarge.jpg', '1646143209', '1683923542'),
(300, 2, 0, 218, 'b79006d8-1c2a-5f43-a38f-478d16dc528b', 'The company’s decision to stop providing capital for new projects in Russia falls short of the exits announced by BP, Shell and Equinor.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/01/business/totalenergies-oil-russia.html', 'TotalEnergies, the French oil company with large natural gas investments in Russia, said on Tuesday that it would no longer provide capital for new projects in the country in response to the invasion of Ukraine.', 'The New York Times', '01economy-briefing-total-articleLarge.jpg', '1646143243', '1683923543'),
(301, 16, 26, 224, '0115da20-943c-52dc-8992-817faa170aa1', 'A career in health journalism has taught me that when it comes to living well, it’s the inner workout that counts the most.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/well/mind/health-fitness-lessons.html', 'When I first started writing about health more than 20 years ago, my columns mostly focused on the physical body: A healthy diet, exercise and screening for disease were regular topics.', 'The New York Times', '31Well-NL-InnerFitness-articleLarge.jpg', '1648771208', '1683923544'),
(302, 11, 0, 173, '65deead0-0d23-5e5c-9926-aeb18958abc9', 'He was famous for his portraits of supermodels and his close relationship with Princess Diana. His images are part of the fashion canon.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/style/patrick-demarchelier-dead.html', 'Patrick Demarchelier, a photographer whose work helped define fashion and celebrity in the late 20th and early 21st centuries, died on Thursday. He was 78.', 'The New York Times', '00DEMARCHELIER-diana-articleLarge.jpg', '1648771454', '1683923545'),
(303, 26, 0, 212, '5f5fe2db-b93a-5f1d-a99c-5880fd0d0c78', 'Judd Apatow’s new film is a comedy about actors trying to make a dinosaur movie during the pandemic that plays more like a documentary of actors trying to make a Covid comedy.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/movies/the-bubble-review-swabs-camera-action.html', '“The safest place in the world right now is a film set,” an agent (Rob Delaney) tells his actress client Carol (Karen Gillan) to encourage her to join the quarantined production of “Cliff Beasts 6.” “The Bubble,” a new comedy from Judd Apatow, tells the story of how the stars of this apparently long-running dinosaur franchise spent their pandemic while doubling as a sort of documentary about how Apatow, who wrote the screenplay with Pam Brady, spent his.', 'The New York Times', 'bubble1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648774803', '1683923546'),
(304, 4, 0, 225, '23774e4c-1745-5520-9380-d08c8f693585', 'Evan Mahnken opens our solving weekend.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-04-01.html', 'FRIDAY PUZZLE — Constructors have this habit of trying to one-up each other when it comes to crossword derring-do and, frankly, I’m a fan. There was a time not too long ago when the constructor who could stack the most long entries on top of one another was a hero. This puzzle by Evan Mahnken, however, is on a whole different level. I’ve never seen anything like this one.', 'The New York Times', '01wordplay-clear-articleLarge.jpg', '1648778404', '1683923547'),
(305, 4, 0, 4, 'eb7314c7-f426-59db-be3b-f3df4e32fa51', 'Brendan Emmett Quigley drums up a challenging variety puzzle.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/crosswords/variety-marching-bands.html', 'MARCHING BANDS — This is always a fun puzzle to work on. The empty grid is a bit disconcerting to me — the alternating bands of gray and white have an optical-illusion effect and the lack of breaks between any of the words is intimidating. It’s hard to adjust to words running in four directions — across from right to left and up, as well as across from left to right and down. But as long as I get lucky with the across entries, or the beginnings of the bands, I find this variety grid more pleasant than frustrating.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648778598', '1683923548'),
(306, 17, 0, 0, '823af30e-3f10-5669-a34d-ea25e6763c57', 'Drinking water for as many as 16 million Americans may be contaminated with perchlorate, a chemical that can harm the development of fetuses and children.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/03/31/climate/epa-perchlorate-drinking-water.html', 'WASHINGTON — The Biden administration on Thursday said it would uphold a Trump-era decision and not impose limits in drinking water of perchlorate, a contaminant that has been linked to brain damage in infants.', 'The New York Times', '31cli-Perchlorate-articleLarge.jpg', '1648780572', '1683923549'),
(307, 11, 0, 226, '2ae66aa6-7682-5811-92c3-cd2705098a73', 'Ian Slater and Michael McVicker became best friends after arriving at Brown University, where they were on the swim team. By their junior year, they were ready to dive into dating.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/ian-slater-michael-mcvicker-wedding.html', 'Michael Theron McVicker and Ian Poris Slater met on the campus of Brown University in 2008, when both were visiting as high school seniors on a swim team recruiting trip.', 'The New York Times', '00MINI-SLATERMCVICKER-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785606', '1683923550'),
(308, 11, 0, 227, '55634916-899f-5ff5-bbe4-ed98d742307a', 'Eliza Giles knew that George Luo was “the one” after spotting him in a crowded high-school assembly 12 years ago.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/eliza-giles-george-luo-wedding.html', 'Elizabeth Giles first spotted George Luo on Jan. 19, 2010, during a crowded assembly at their high school, Cate School, in Carpinteria, Calif.', 'The New York Times', '01MINI-GILES-LUO-02-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785606', '1683923551'),
(309, 11, 0, 228, 'abc7ad36-2202-541d-bbf4-265e76b773ac', 'To show interest in Jayla Moody, a fellow undergraduate at his college, Jordan Marshall liked bunch of her Instagram photos. She then did the same.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/jayla-moody-jordan-marshall-wedding.html', 'Jayla Moody and Jordan Marshall’s love story might have started sooner if only they had spoken during the time that both attended Mercer University in Macon, Ga., where he was the captain of the football team, and she was the 2018 Homecoming Queen.', 'The New York Times', '00MINI-MARSHALL-MOODY-02-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785606', '1683923552'),
(310, 11, 0, 229, 'edb3dcdb-eb7e-5c0d-ae60-cb10dc7e0d9f', 'Jaclyn Tokarz met Dieter Seelig in 2015 at his bar, Plug Uglies, where she was a regular. But more than two years would pass before their romance took off.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/jaclyn-tokarz-dieter-seelig-wedding.html', 'When Dieter Demetrios Seelig and Jaclyn Michelle Tokarz first laid eyes on each other in 2015 at Plug Uglies, a bar he owns in Manhattan’s Gramercy Park neighborhood, both felt an immediate attraction.', 'The New York Times', '00MINI-SEELIG-TOKARZ-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785606', '1683923553'),
(311, 11, 0, 230, '5ebde1af-7fbf-54fe-8d03-ff524cdf4046', 'When in pain, it helps to know someone who has experience treating it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/modern-love-the-dentist-who-treated-my-divorce.html', 'I have spent countless hours reclined in dentists’ chairs, but this was the first time I had cried in one.', 'The New York Times', '03MODERN-STONE-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785608', '1683923554'),
(312, 11, 0, 227, '5892888e-291f-5fcb-8923-5fabe8fb112e', 'More than a decade after Miranda Robertson studied abroad in the city of her dreams, she returned to discover the man of her dreams in Nicolas Bayle.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/miranda-robertson-nicolas-bayle-wedding.html', 'When Miranda Patricia Robertson matched with Nicolas Robert Michel Bayle on the dating app Bumble in 2018, Ms. Robertson had also recently reconnected with what she called “the love of my life” — the city of Paris.', 'The New York Times', '01VOWS-FRANCE1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785612', '1683923555'),
(313, 1, 27, 52, '023175b6-f615-55f1-ad0b-2eff9e7c9be5', 'In December, UConn’s star player had an ugly knee injury. On Friday night, she will try to lead her team to a national title game.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/sports/ncaabasketball/paige-bueckers-uconn.html', 'MINNEAPOLIS — Brian Cosgriff first saw Paige Bueckers play when she was in second grade, during a scrimmage at the University of Minnesota.', 'The New York Times', '01wcbb-bueckers-articleLarge.jpg', '1648785669', '1683923557'),
(314, 5, 0, 92, 'a156b121-64c9-5e3b-b6ea-ad3a1d563755', 'The ruling puts the state’s June primary elections in doubt, but Democrats said they would appeal.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/nyregion/new-york-redistricting.html', 'Good morning. It’s Friday. We’ll look at the latest twist in redistricting in New York. We’ll also catch up on the state budget in Albany, about to be officially late.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648785711', '1683923558'),
(315, 7, 0, 0, '48862aaf-4bc0-5ef4-a177-604834bbc391', 'Corrections that appeared in print on Friday, April 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/pageoneplus/corrections-april-1-2022.html', 'An article on Thursday about pro-Russian Serbians misstated the given name of a Belgrade-based psychotherapist. She is Aurelija Djan, not Arijan.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648785838', '1683923558'),
(316, 6, 0, 0, '673de3c9-09f0-5b3f-8a9e-43235de8b61b', 'Quotation of the Day for Friday, April 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/todayspaper/quotation-of-the-day-judge-rules-parts-of-florida-vote-law-unconstitutional.html', '“For the past 20 years, the majority in the Florida Legislature has attacked the voting rights of its Black constituents.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648785855', '1683923559'),
(317, 20, 0, 0, '995cb239-8641-5f51-a548-71e7961cbd84', 'The teenage winner of our Invent a Word challenge suggests a noun for some leaders of the globalized economy.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/learning/word-of-the-day-oblivionaire.html', 'Note: This April Fools’ Day, we’ve turned our vocabulary column over to the winner of our Invent a Word challenge, which invited students to fill a gap they saw in the English language.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648787405', '1683923560'),
(318, 19, 0, 90, '2a0c4866-313d-51d9-834f-2edd7ddc3fd4', 'Fighting rages on in Ukraine.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/briefing/ukraine-war-hungary-election.html', 'Facing deeper isolation by the day over the war in Ukraine, Russia seemed to slightly recalibrate its stance, allowing greater humanitarian access to the devastated port city of Mariupol and apparently retreating from a payment confrontation with European gas customers. Fighting around Kyiv, Ukraine’s capital, continued unabated. Follow the latest updates.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648787472', '1683923561'),
(319, 5, 0, 231, '73b6fa03-56cf-5193-9144-ee57bacedc6b', 'The boy was the latest child to be caught in the crossfire of a surge in shootings that has plagued New York City since the pandemic began.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/nyregion/boy-shooting-minivan-brooklyn.html', 'A day after a 12-year-old boy was fatally shot in a parked car in Brooklyn, community leaders said the killing was just the latest episode to unsettle neighborhood residents who are both scared of street violence and wary of a return to aggressive police tactics. ', 'The New York Times', '01met-child-shot-brooklyn-articleLarge.jpg', '1648790223', '1683923562'),
(320, 3, 3, 93, '5ab9e71f-f947-52f4-9102-1d319cfaace1', '“Of course they’re afraid to be honest,” Stephen Colbert said. “No matter what you say to a psychotic boss, you lose.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/arts/television/late-night-putin-advisers.html', 'Welcome to Best of Late Night, a rundown of the previous night’s highlights that lets you sleep — and lets us get paid to watch comedy. Here are the 50 best movies on Netflix right now.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648795608', '1683923563'),
(321, 8, 28, 232, '08f88761-6410-528e-8f6c-dd06077238c0', 'Australia has had its fair share of music that made it big overseas. But why do some bands succeed internationally while others do not? And does that even matter?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/australia/midnight-oil-brings-australia-home.html', 'In the days immediately following my return to Australia in September 2017, after almost 30 years of living in the United States, an old high school friend invited me to go with her to see Midnight Oil at the Sidney Myer Music Bowl. I was an Oils fan as a teenager almost by osmosis: My best friend was obsessed with them, and my stepfather was part of the same late-70’s Australian punk scene from which they sprang.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648796178', '1683923564'),
(322, 4, 0, 9, '9ab896d6-69ce-53b5-a793-0a856bb6a69a', 'Feeling stuck on today’s puzzle? We can help.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/crosswords/spelling-bee-forum.html', 'FRIDAY — Hi busy bees! Welcome to today’s Spelling Bee forum. There are a number of terms that appear in both this article and other online discussions of the Spelling Bee; a glossary of those terms compiled by Monicat, a Times reader, can be found below.', 'The New York Times', '01bee-forum-fri-articleLarge.jpg', '1648796403', '1683923565'),
(323, 2, 11, 233, '15278437-30e8-5330-ba00-d78e5ebcb612', 'The jobless rate in February, 2.1 percent, was close to the lowest ever. Employers are adjusting to the power of workers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/economy/nebraska-economy-unemployment-labor.html', 'Harry’s Wonder Bar is a trusted old dive in Nebraska’s capital, frequented by office clerks, construction workers and graduate students alike: the sort of wood-paneled place with a pool table in the back where phones generally stay in pockets, second fiddle to casual conversation, and beer mugs come frosted regardless of the season.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204066273_56dd7250-2f41-40b1-9e34-1a194fb08799-articleLarge.jpg', '1648796409', '1683923566'),
(324, 12, 17, 234, 'aa64f493-7f74-5a77-b9ba-a2f4542057a4', 'Or take a cloud out on a walk, or climb the antlers of a deer.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/review/childrens-picture-books-stop-and-smell-the-roses.html', 'EMILE AND THE FIELDWritten by Kevin YoungIllustrated by Chioma Ebinama', 'The New York Times', '01PictureThis_Lizzy-articleLarge.jpg', '1648797126', '1683923567'),
(325, 8, 4, 90, 'b2f69344-87e6-5273-b962-43f1599a977c', 'New Zealand officials say anti-vaccination protesters seeded cannabis during a three-week occupation.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/asia/new-zealand-parliament-weed.html', 'When anti-vaccination protesters finally cleared out of New Zealand’s Parliament grounds after a three-week occupation, they left behind a scene of destruction and disorder — the charred remains of a children’s playground, camping equipment and human waste, among other items.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648801854', '1683923568'),
(326, 3, 0, 235, 'ce0ae576-34fe-58fe-8060-ce8a7f3e773d', 'Selections from our current articles on weekend events, including a preview of the Grammy Awards.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/04/01/arts/weekend-editors-picks-grammys.html', 'Selections from our current articles on weekend events, including a preview of the Grammy Awards.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803602', '1683923569'),
(327, 12, 17, 236, '01d46870-f64d-5127-8b9f-6a13ee2bdc3a', 'Six new paperbacks to check out this week.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/review/new-paperbacks.html', 'WHILE JUSTICE SLEEPS, by Stacey Abrams. (Anchor, 480 pp., $17.) In this legal thriller, a young law clerk catches a whiff of a dangerous conspiracy in Washington after the Supreme Court justice she works for slips into a coma. “Those desirous of perils and surprises will encounter them in abundance,” commented our reviewer, Richard North Patterson.', 'The New York Times', '03PAPERROW-COMBO-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803603', '1683923570'),
(328, 19, 0, 0, '2b8b6cf7-3a37-5755-b66d-ca25ef428c70', 'Did you follow the news this week? Take our quiz to see how well you stack up with other Times readers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/04/01/briefing/news-quiz-boosters-susan-collins-coors-light.html', 'Did you follow the news this week? Take our quiz to see how well you stack up with other Times readers.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803603', '1683923571'),
(329, 12, 17, 237, '40903aee-ab35-57ce-b16a-e17b9200482f', 'In Aamina Ahmad’s stunning debut novel,“The Return of Faraz Ali,” a police officer is asked to cover up a young girl’s death in the red-light district of Lahore, Pakistan.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/review/return-of-faraz-ali-aamina-ahmad.html', 'In the early 1980s, not long after President Anwar el-Sadat of Egypt was assassinated, my father was walking home from work one night when two soldiers stopped him. They were young, bored. They decided to give him a hard time.', 'The New York Times', '03El-Akkad-Mohalla-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803612', '1683923572'),
(330, 12, 0, 187, '571c3c86-df12-5195-957a-9540f9ebd15a', 'Julian Winters’s new novel, “Right Where I Left You,” is a love letter to queer Black and brown nerds.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/right-where-i-left-you-julian-winters-ya-nyt.html', 'Welcome to YA/NYT, a monthly column in which we recommend one new young adult book that you won’t want to miss.', 'The New York Times', '01Winters-YA-SUB01-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803614', '1683923573'),
(331, 13, 0, 116, '53562609-877b-5779-9427-042dfdb013ba', 'Our political system was the primary obstacle to protecting the lives and livelihoods of its own citizens.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/opinion/anti-lynching-bill-biden.html', 'On Tuesday, President Biden signed a bill to make lynching a federal crime. Devised by a group of Black lawmakers in the House and Senate — Tim Scott of South Carolina, Cory Booker of New Jersey, Bobby Rush of Illinois and Kamala Harris of California (when she was still in the Senate) — the law comes into being after more than 200 failed attempts, over more than 100 years, to pass anti-lynching legislation through Congress.', 'The New York Times', '01bouie-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803617', '1683923575'),
(332, 9, 0, 238, 'd2f89c42-0595-5407-8500-741fd45f3c43', 'Some couples who’ve ended their marriages are finding common ground right at home.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/realestate/separated-living-together.html', 'Kate Warren and her husband, Yanni Kotsonis, separated in early 2016. But they didn’t exactly go their separate ways.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204310275_a18f15af-2bcb-4c3a-b6b2-d7717addf7b8-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803617', '1683923576'),
(333, 2, 0, 239, '2d042f69-0cfc-5419-a437-806f31d83e99', 'Turning your home equity into cash can help pay bills and preserve other savings and investments. But they’re complicated, and not for everyone.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/retirement-reverse-mortgages-home-equity.html', 'After her husband died suddenly from a fall in 2016, Marjorie Fox decided to hold off on any big decisions. She waited two years to retire as a financial planner and three to sell their house and buy a lakeside townhome in Reston, Va. For added protection, she took out a reverse mortgage on her new home.', 'The New York Times', '01retiring-reverse1-illo-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803618', '1683923577'),
(334, 20, 0, 0, '8620c380-6e0b-57cd-8e0f-624b1859527b', 'Tell us a story, real or made up, that is inspired by this image.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/learning/at-the-fountain.html', 'Use your imagination to write the opening of a short story or poem inspired by this illustration — or, tell us about a memory from your own life that this image makes you think of.', 'The New York Times', '28socialmedia-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803618', '1683923578'),
(335, 2, 0, 240, '751ad883-9315-5815-a3b3-d8f8927a7634', 'Our columnist answers questions about the troubles in the bond market, and what they mean for investors.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/bond-market-decline.html', 'It’s been a horrible start of the year for the bond market, the worst in decades.', 'The New York Times', '01Strategies-illo-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803619', '1683923579'),
(337, 20, 0, 241, '87de13da-8351-5f68-a320-69dc88d9555b', 'Do you see walking as an enjoyable activity, or is it just a way to get from one place to another?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/learning/do-you-enjoy-taking-long-walks.html', 'Do you enjoy walking around your neighborhood? Have you ever discovered something interesting or surprising near where you live when walking around? During the pandemic, Mary Hosbrough and Jennifer Jacobsen-Wood tried something new: They met up daily to walk every street of their hometown, Peoria, Ill.', 'The New York Times', '01AASOLN1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803621', '1683923581'),
(338, 13, 0, 163, '05423692-2995-52fc-9e17-16311aeb3247', 'How the company got mired in a moral panic.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/opinion/disney-dont-say-gay.html', 'I don’t know Latoya Raveneau, but I feel terrible for her. An executive producer at Disney, she was a speaker at a recent virtual all-hands company meeting about Florida’s “Don’t Say Gay” bill. Inside Disney, there had been considerable anger that the company, one of the state’s largest employers, had donated to politicians behind the bill and hadn’t done more to fight it. Raveneau stepped up to defend the company’s queer friendliness, only to become a national object of right-wing fury and disgust.', 'The New York Times', '01goldberg1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803622', '1683923582'),
(339, 8, 6, 220, 'a388b613-a037-5523-a9bd-ec5af2539dff', 'At 26, Sammy Basso is believed to be the oldest person with the disease Progeria. And now he’s researching it, hoping to find a treatment and the secrets of aging.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/europe/scientist-patient-progeria.html', 'TEZZE SUL BRENTA, Italy — Like many an Italian man living at home in his mid-20s, Sammy Basso is a little embarrassed by the childhood mementos that clutter his small bedroom.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803622', '1683923583'),
(340, 13, 0, 242, 'e1f69e72-201c-50f5-8d38-b5d7c44fb017', 'In seeking to discredit her, they have concocted a scary version of a Black woman  to serve up to their base.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/opinion/jackson-supreme-court-republicans.html', 'When Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson’s Supreme Court nomination reaches the Senate floor soon, every Republican who votes against her confirmation will be complicit in the abuse that the Republican members of the Judiciary Committee heaped on her.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204294744_a945f0ec-1a56-4ffe-a17f-bbdc0361ceee-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803622', '1683923584'),
(341, 2, 11, 233, 'd432bf5d-ce05-599b-bb5e-951b53cbeb3b', 'The U.S. economy added 431,000 jobs and the unemployment rate fell to 3.6 percent. Wages showed sharp gains, but that has been blunted by inflation.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/economy/jobs-report-march-2022.html', 'A continued torrent of consumer demand, paired with a decline in coronavirus caseloads and health restrictions, led to a burst of job creation last month, showing the staying power of the economic recovery.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803623', '1683923585');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(342, 10, 5, 206, 'ea239f60-fe8b-5148-95ff-19a8693af8cb', 'States pushed back on a plan to take back some of their stimulus money to fund President Biden’s emergency spending request. Now Congress is trying to find other ways to offset the cost.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/politics/covid-relief-funds.html', 'FRANKFORT, Ky. — Gov. Andy Beshear has been toting oversize checks around his state in recent weeks, handing them out to city and county officials for desperately needed water improvements.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204755472_8115584b-a4b1-4183-89d1-3a86d0ad2ea9-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803623', '1683923586'),
(343, 13, 0, 243, '1e78a9a9-52c8-5d0f-807d-8f6d3c69b14f', 'Vladimir Putin made a threat of nuclear weapons. The U.S. and NATO should be less deferential.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/opinion/biden-putin-ukraine-nuclear-weapons.html', 'The Biden administration has done an admirable job checking Russian disinformation efforts by disclosing U.S. intelligence assessments of Moscow’s intentions and marshaling unified political support for Ukrainian sovereignty and indirect military support for its defense.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_182421162_f38100e0-d6d4-4205-9adb-d85089144b13-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803625', '1683923587'),
(344, 13, 0, 0, '48f8514c-2a03-53c3-89e1-5049adc3cea5', 'The historian Nicholas Mulder on how the West’s sanctions can help end Putin’s war — or escalate it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/opinion/ezra-klein-podcast-nicholas-mulder.html', 'The Russian political scientist Ilya Matveev recently described the impact of the West’s sanctions on his country as “30 years of economic development thrown into the bin.” He’s not exaggerating. Economists expect the Russian economy to contract by at least 15 percent of G.D.P. this year. Inflation is spiking. An exodus of Russian professionals is underway. Stories of shortages and long lines for basic consumer goods abound.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803625', '1683923588'),
(345, 10, 5, 82, '6a263121-03ce-5e43-8666-e5ef153e88a6', 'Democrats and Republicans alike stuffed nearly 5,000 earmarks totaling $9 billion into the $1.5 trillion government spending bill signed by President Biden.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/politics/congress-earmarks.html', 'WASHINGTON — One hundred million dollars for an airport in Mobile, Ala. Tens of thousands for upgrades to a police station in the tiny town of Milton, W.Va. Hundreds of thousands of dollars sent to Arkansas to deal with feral swine.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803626', '1683923589'),
(346, 1, 27, 244, '030a2f3d-574e-5254-90c5-ed50be8e90bb', 'Under Coach Jay Wright, the Wildcats have made four Final Fours and won two national titles, all without any one-and-done players.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/sports/ncaabasketball/villanova-one-and-dones.html', 'Update: Kansas beat UNC to win the NCAA Championship.', 'The New York Times', '00mcbb-villanova-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803628', '1683923590'),
(347, 20, 0, 0, '32ba3845-7df9-5991-9a85-a5b7f12858be', 'Create a one-page field note that explores the meaning and usage of one of our Words of the Day. Submissions are due on April 29.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/learning/april-vocabulary-challenge-create-a-word-field-note.html', 'Naturalists often record their discoveries about nature in field notes. A field note about fire ants might catalog where they are found, what they look like, how common they are and how they interact with other animals.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803628', '1683923591'),
(348, 1, 0, 245, 'b5e2e57f-1003-5a92-bcd4-801c9e550827', 'Vladyslav Heraskevych, a skeleton competitor from Ukraine, gathers supplies and uses the team van to deliver them to Kyiv as he waits to be called for military duty.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/sports/ukraine-vladyslav-heraskevych-war.html', 'A little more than a month has passed since the end of the Beijing Olympics, but already the Games, like the ones before, have distilled into a handful of images and moments.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204741891_8cf06457-d53b-420b-bff1-1832f0652cde-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803628', '1683923592'),
(349, 5, 0, 246, '22d37023-0fab-543d-b861-f48e4708b3f1', 'A major restoration project aims to protect the Jamaica Bay area — and all of New York — by returning salt marshes and sand dunes to their natural states. But will it be too late for the people of Broad Channel?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/nyregion/jamaica-bay-broad-channel-climate-change.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', '04jamaica-bay-02-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803629', '1683923593'),
(350, 1, 0, 245, '4c4df2cf-20d0-5baf-9d8a-14747170f946', 'After struggling for more than a year, the former world No. 1 has advanced to her first women’s singles final since she won the Australian Open in 2021.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/sports/naomi-osaka-miami-open.html', 'MIAMI GARDENS, Fla.— Thirteen months.', 'The New York Times', '01tennis-osaka1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803629', '1683923594'),
(351, 10, 0, 247, 'bd42e5ba-81d3-538f-ba39-8a8f1e654028', 'Lawyers made closing arguments on Friday in the federal trial involving four men with militia ties who are accused of conspiring to kidnap Gov. Gretchen Whitmer.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/whitmer-plot-trial-closing.html', 'GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. — The government’s accusations were jarring: Several men with militia ties had schemed to abduct Gov. Gretchen Whitmer of Michigan at her vacation home. The group, prosecutors and witnesses said, had held a series of “field training exercises” and discussed killing or stranding her in a boat in the middle of Lake Michigan.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_198595965_3dcdfacc-0561-4e2d-be76-5bc7fc6430b9-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803630', '1683923595'),
(352, 8, 14, 248, '30b08068-caa5-538b-8e77-91622fccb915', 'In Costa Rica’s runoff on Sunday, voters will decide between a candidate found to have sexually harassed junior employees at the World Bank and a former president once accused of corruption.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/americas/costa-rica-election-sexual-harassment.html', 'SAN JOSÉ, Costa Rica — He was demoted from a senior position at the World Bank because of sexual harassment. Now, the economist Rodrigo Chaves — who has campaigned as a populist outsider in an election marked by anger at traditional politicians — leads the polls to become Costa Rica’s next president on Sunday.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803632', '1683923596'),
(353, 10, 5, 249, 'eeefd14e-a90a-5f09-abc8-2e9ff26f3b23', 'Democrats have long held up Nevada as a symbol of their future. But as the state’s economy struggles, it has become the epitome of the party’s midterm difficulties.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/politics/nevada-midterms-democrats.html', 'LAS VEGAS — Scars from the coronavirus pandemic are still visible here. Housing prices skyrocketed, with rents rising faster than almost anywhere else in the country. Roughly 10,000 casino workers remain out of work. Gas prices, now more than $5 a gallon, are higher than in every other state except California.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204453582_6916aafb-9d7e-4769-905c-aa3f88aa3a27-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803636', '1683923597'),
(354, 2, 11, 250, '79c508fb-d0f1-5038-bfb2-4adb517b6f61', 'Federal Reserve officials are tasked with fostering “full employment.” At least for now, some see the labor market as uncomfortably tight.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/economy/jobs-fed-full-employment.html', 'Federal Reserve officials are tasked with fostering “full employment,” and while it has been difficult to guess what that means as the economy recovers from huge job losses at the start of the pandemic, March hiring data seemed likely to reaffirm to policymakers that the labor market is running hot.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648803661', '1683923598'),
(355, 9, 0, 251, '73299b92-e93e-5524-8fc3-d12870fd6b00', 'When parents go their separate ways in a divorce, children are torn between two places — both should feel like home.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/realestate/divorce-kids-homes.html', 'The day my ex and I had to tell our children that we were getting divorced, we sat on the couch in the living room as they played on the rug below us. It was a pivotal moment, and our almost 5-year-old, Isaac, sensing that something big and disruptive was happening, had one very important question: What would happen to his Legos?', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204352779_f9c67ff4-0623-4247-b96f-840a34ac0acf-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803762', '1683923599'),
(356, 18, 0, 252, '911a814d-760c-5c79-9532-146910bdc550', 'The Times’s Visual Investigations team shares the rigorous process of confirming (or disputing) the authenticity of videos about the war in Ukraine.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/insider/verifying-images-of-the-war-in-ukraine.html', 'A brief, shaky video uploaded to Telegram on March 17 showed bodies on the ground in Mariupol, one of Ukraine’s largest cities, which has been battered by Russian military attacks in the continuing war. The person behind the camera shouted that it was March 13. But could the date — and the content itself — be corroborated?', 'The New York Times', '11vid-sat-fire-2-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803763', '1683923600'),
(357, 17, 0, 253, 'f6b5cc9e-5056-53ed-8138-3f75722a4477', 'Rising costs at the pump, war in Ukraine, an emboldened fossil fuel industry and stalled legislation have imperiled President Biden’s climate agenda.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/climate/biden-climate-change.html', 'WASHINGTON — A year after he entered the White House with a vow that fighting global warming would be a driving priority for his administration, President Biden finds his climate agenda is mired in delay and faces legal, legislative and political headwinds that could diminish or dismantle it entirely.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_203855169_2be1dbc5-ef15-458b-8da3-89125d4c1340-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803769', '1683923601'),
(358, 25, 0, 254, '875846b1-4d16-5a84-b312-86e227f0c897', 'As pandemic restrictions lifted, the travel industry was looking forward to a strong summer season. But they may be disappointed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/travel/europe-tourism-ukraine-war.html', 'Diego Sanz, a tour guide on Spain’s southeastern Mediterranean coast, received his first international group booking in more than a year in mid February. It was, he thought, an augury of better things to come.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204696144_edf73ee6-6a6d-4273-8ba0-8d33c5e7a725-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803785', '1683923602'),
(359, 12, 17, 255, '351b61a4-3d91-56df-b094-23fd7fe60de5', 'New Yorkers still tell stories of browsing at Harlem’s Liberation Bookstore or spending the afternoon at Scribner’s.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/review/remembrance-of-bookstores-past.html', 'New York City is home to wonderful bookstores, but there used to be so many more of them to choose from — from Coliseum Books, just south of Columbus Circle; to Ivy’s Curiosities and Murder Ink on the Upper West Side; to the dearly departed St. Mark’s Bookshop in the East Village. By one count, there were 386 booksellers in Manhattan in 1950, including almost 40 on a six-block stretch of Fourth Avenue. (By comparison, there are fewer than 100 in the city now.) Here’s a look back at a few old favorites.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_151676856_bd3fe27c-0620-4a35-8b05-875009dfeb72-articleLarge.jpg', '1648803789', '1683923604'),
(360, 27, 0, 0, 'ff2cceaa-4293-5cd8-b754-a533fe57a565', 'Five articles from around The Times, narrated just for you.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/podcasts/hillsong-rumble-kids-books-narrated-articles.html', 'This weekend, listen to a collection of narrated articles from around The New York Times, read aloud by the reporters who wrote them.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_204586266_9fe17c3b-cb68-4cdf-9202-c750af4e58ce-articleLarge.jpg', '1648805406', '1683923605'),
(361, 8, 6, 256, '9ae88c19-796d-5b1a-8bcf-dfb109f08beb', 'Russian soldiers left the decommissioned nuclear plant and a nearby city after five weeks of occupation.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/europe/chernobyl-radiation-poisoning.html', 'As Russian troops pulled out of Ukraine’s shuttered Chernobyl nuclear plant five weeks after seizing it, an international nuclear watchdog agency is looking into reports that some of the soldiers are experiencing radiation poisoning.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648806022', '1683923606'),
(362, 27, 20, 257, '736a84d3-83b0-58ee-99b9-a69a0d0105c8', 'What the fight for the Ukrainian port city means for the future of the war.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/podcasts/the-daily/russia-ukraine-war-mariupol.html', 'This episode details graphic scenes.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648807207', '1683923607'),
(363, 10, 0, 258, 'ede5131e-1c4d-590f-89e7-cb829d74bb82', 'The ship, a replenishment oiler, is designed to carry fuel to the Navy’s operating carrier strike groups.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/navy-ship-ruth-bader-ginsburg.html', 'Ruth Bader Ginsburg, the Supreme Court Justice who fought for women’s rights for more than a half century before her death in 2020, will have a U.S. Navy ship named after her, military officials said on Thursday.', 'The New York Times', '01xp-ginsburg-articleLarge.jpg', '1648808729', '1683923608'),
(364, 19, 0, 129, 'f76ca470-ad9e-58b8-bbf7-8880d3b8187c', 'The state will help determine Senate control in this year’s midterm elections.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/briefing/nevada-senate-battleground-state-midterms.html', 'Nevada, perhaps more than any other state, has showcased the potential for a more diverse America to move the country’s politics to the left. Rising numbers of Asian American and Latino residents have helped Democrats win the state in the past four presidential elections. The party also holds both of Nevada’s Senate seats.', 'The New York Times', '01-THE-MORNING-NL-NEVADA-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1648809815', '1683923609'),
(365, 2, 11, 68, '8131d9a8-f28b-51e6-8658-71d3ae592c20', 'A continued run-up in prices shows how rapidly the impact of the war in Ukraine is coursing through Europe’s economy.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/economy/eurozone-inflation.html', 'PARIS — Soaring energy and food prices driven by Russia’s continued aggression against Ukraine pushed inflation in Europe last month to levels not seen in four decades, with prices in the 19 countries that use the euro soaring 7.5 percent, according to data released Friday by Europe’s statistics agency.', 'The New York Times', '01eurozone-inflation-sub-articleLarge.jpg', '1648810615', '1683923610'),
(366, 10, 0, 167, 'beb47a51-4b47-5c7d-8890-213d12e50be7', 'Edith Kanaka‘ole, who died in 1979, will appear on the coin next year along with four other notable women.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/us-quarter-women-edith-kanakaole.html', 'George Washington will be sharing some space with a native Hawaiian hula teacher next year.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648811217', '1683923611'),
(367, 2, 24, 134, 'bdea7756-f0fd-5515-ad86-f6f491d8e08e', 'Despite strong job growth, all the positions lost during pandemic may not be regained.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/dealbook/jobs-numbers-employment.html', 'This morning, the Labor Department will report how many jobs employers added to their payrolls in March. Economists expect a healthy gain. But how much longer can the labor market keep it up?', 'The New York Times', '01db-newsletter-jobs1-articleLarge.jpg', '1648811440', '1683923612'),
(368, 8, 6, 28, '77bdd87e-5a54-548f-b257-aa5cf8a70f66', 'Pope Francis also promised to visit Canada as part of a process of healing and reconciliation over the church’s involvement in an abusive system of residential schools.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/europe/pope-apology-indigenous-people-canada.html', 'VATICAN CITY — Pope Francis apologized on Friday for the Roman Catholic Church’s involvement in a system of Canadian boarding schools that abused Indigenous children for 100 years, and said he would travel to Canada as part of a process of healing and reconciliation.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648811583', '1683923613'),
(369, 26, 0, 122, 'a9933c30-b4ce-503e-9e51-485ab65727a7', 'The producer of the telecast, Will Packer, said that Smith had been asked to leave after slapping Rock, and that he had urged officials not to “physically remove” the actor.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/movies/oscars-will-smith-slap.html', 'LOS ANGELES — Will Smith, who slapped the comedian Chris Rock at the Oscars, said Friday that he was resigning from the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences, saying that he had “betrayed” its trust with conduct that was “shocking, painful, and inexcusable.”', 'The New York Times', '01slap-folo3-articleLarge.jpg', '1648812999', '1683923614'),
(370, 10, 0, 140, '4615c736-f792-5a7b-b837-ac3795afdf8f', 'The state is the home of some of the nation’s biggest Ukrainian population centers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/us/ukrainian-refugees-california.html', 'President Biden announced last week that the United States would accept up to 100,000 refugees fleeing the conflict in Ukraine. Many of them, it turns out, may end up in California.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648814018', '1683923615'),
(371, 8, 4, 259, 'dc2d35ff-279d-57b5-b411-b37e48f228e3', 'Coronavirus infections have spread at an elder care facility in Shanghai. Workers said deaths are increasing and resources dwindling.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/asia/china-covid-shanghai.html', 'A coronavirus outbreak is ravaging a hospital in Shanghai for older adults, underscoring the difficulties officials have had in containing infections even as the city imposed a 10-day staggered lockdown.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648817827', '1683923616'),
(372, 21, 0, 260, '8bc64446-fcc9-58cc-afe8-c6f41a3d9f02', 'A tornado that hit a delivery station in Illinois last year will be a focus of the inquiry.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/technology/amazon-labor-practices.html', 'The House Committee on Oversight and Reform has opened an investigation into Amazon’s labor practices during severe weather events, according to a letter members sent to Andy Jassy, Amazon’s chief executive.', 'The New York Times', '01amazon-articleLarge.jpg', '1648818008', '1683923617'),
(373, 29, 0, 261, '1e821ab9-711f-5d9e-a05d-241d3d961d2a', 'A pandemic program allowed people to exclude the benefits from their income, but in some cases they are still being counted. Here’s what to do.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/your-money/college-financial-aid-unemployment-benefits.html', 'Unemployment benefits helped millions of people who lost their jobs in the pandemic, but now the payments may throw a wrench into the college financial aid process.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648818011', '1683923618'),
(374, 3, 3, 262, 'abf83b03-c372-5685-94eb-fd660e736cf5', 'This cross-cultural crime thriller, which recalls a time when the yakuza ruled Tokyo’s red-light districts and back alleyways, traced a twisty path to TV.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/arts/television/tokyo-vice-hbo-max.html', 'TOKYO — These days there are few visible signs of the yakuza in Kabukicho, the storied entertainment and red-light district in the heart of this churning metropolis of more than 37 million people — the biggest city in the world. Aggressive laws have weakened Japan’s organized crime syndicates and chased their aging, declining memberships into the shadows.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_189207369_cd2dac11-bd53-40a5-bc1e-b0fbda63144e-articleLarge.jpg', '1648818011', '1683923619'),
(375, 3, 12, 263, '7ecc1047-e067-514b-b915-04429e81c7e5', 'In a major new commission for the Tate museum group in London, the British-Guyanese artist returns to the themes of empire and postcolonial reckoning that have fascinated him throughout his career.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/arts/design/hew-locke-the-procession-tate-britain.html', 'LONDON — On a recent morning, a cavernous studio in south London was a vista of ordered chaos. Elaborate headdresses covered several tables, a jumble of cardboard cutout body parts lay heaped on a palette and boxes overflowed with leopard-print fabrics, fake fur and gaudy fake jewelry. Sewing machines whirred and hammers banged.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_203769438_9cb64939-9793-42a4-a3d2-7a6a816780d2-articleLarge.jpg', '1648819483', '1683923620'),
(376, 2, 11, 250, '3dac57b4-a80c-5bcf-8036-0df36958c40a', 'Federal Reserve officials have said the pace of pay gains, if they continue, would not be consistent with stable inflation.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/economy/jobs-fed-wages.html', 'Wages climbed at a rapid pace in the year through March and the unemployment rate dropped notably last month, signs of a hot labor market that could keep pressure on the Federal Reserve as it contemplates how much and how quickly to cool down the economy.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648820181', '1683923621'),
(377, 4, 0, 264, '9c0b770e-0a1d-53d6-b74c-2bbffcec6952', 'Every year, hundreds of crossword constructors and fans gather to compete in Stamford, Conn. This year will feature the first live Wordle competition.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/crosswords/get-to-know-the-american-crossword-puzzle-tournament.html', 'Every year, crossword lovers and solvers come together to participate in the American Crossword Puzzle Tournament.', 'The New York Times', '01acpt-preview-articleLarge.jpg', '1648821607', '1683923622'),
(378, 11, 0, 265, '8dfa8d8b-1f65-5a8e-a83e-5aa11f73fcfa', 'Two years into the pandemic, people are coping with big existential problems by making time for simple joys.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/style/yes-you-do-deserve-a-little-treat.html', 'These days, whenever Jules Zucker has to run an errand, she throws a Reese’s Fast Break candy bar into her bag.', 'The New York Times', '01TREATS-articleLarge.jpg', '1648821826', '1683923623'),
(379, 8, 8, 72, 'ffe7e37f-0188-50a9-a1b8-906b0ff4b88b', 'The conflict has driven up the cost of food in a region that depends heavily on crops from Russia and Ukraine and is facing what could be its worst drought in four decades.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/africa/food-crisis-africa-drought-ukraine.html', 'NAIROBI, Kenya — First came the drought, drying up rivers, and claiming the lives of two of Ruqiya Hussein Ahmed’s children as her family fled the barren countryside in southwest Somalia.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648823718', '1683923624'),
