(384, 2, 0, 268, 'b2d4d701-b7cc-5919-940c-711dc4b45d90', 'Jim Weber, the chief executive of Brooks Running, was a devoted distance runner. Then came cancer.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/brooks-running-jim-weber.html', 'Jim Weber, the longtime chief executive of Brooks Running, was for many years a devoted runner. The hours spent racking up the miles were more than exercise for him. They were a chance to meditate on life, to devise strategy about business, and to ruminate on the thorny problems that come with operating a company with more than $1 billion in annual sales.', 'The New York Times', '01Corneroffice-Weber-articleLarge.jpg', '1648824884', '1683923628'),
(385, 3, 15, 269, '70710570-fdfa-5337-9f15-e7733f96e9b2', 'Hear tracks by Angel Olsen, Koffee, Barrie and others.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/arts/music/playlist-harry-styles-angel-olsen.html', 'Every Friday, pop critics for The New York Times weigh in on the week’s most notable new songs and videos. Just want the music? Listen to the Playlist on Spotify here (or find our profile: nytimes). Like what you hear? Let us know at theplaylist@nytimes.com and sign up for our Louder newsletter, a once-a-week blast of our pop music coverage.', 'The New York Times', '01playlist-articleLarge.jpg', '1648825164', '1683923629'),
(386, 26, 0, 270, 'df503cd8-fa9a-57eb-8ccb-fd68c92cfda2', 'This month’s picks are proof that it doesn’t take big bucks to scare people’s pants off with undead messiahs, unseen demons and uncanny commotions.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/movies/streaming-horror-movies.html', 'Kevin (Oghenero Gbaje) and his older sister, Brittney (DeShawn White), arrive with Brittney’s fiancé, Tony (Lenny Thomas), at their parents’ waterside cabin, only to discover that their mother, father and the neighbors have been killed. That’s when they — all three are Black — are accosted by an angry white guy (Nick Damici) with a gun.', 'The New York Times', 'streaming-horror-bloodconscious-articleLarge.jpg', '1648825206', '1683923630'),
(387, 22, 0, 56, 'be25c102-0b74-5093-a8c9-235032791367', 'Try our newest recipes for qatayef, caldo de costilla and Italian broccoli salad.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/dining/what-to-cook-this-weekend.html', 'Good morning. Today I am pleased to announce that New York Times Cooking will no longer publish recipes for chicken, duck, turkey, goose, Cornish game hen, pigeon or grouse. This is in keeping with recent reporting that shows that birds aren’t real. They are actually drones used by the government to spy on Americans. They charge on power lines.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648825207', '1683923631'),
(388, 15, 0, 271, 'f7ddcfe2-b9fc-5c10-b0fc-69be7bc0add7', 'After settling a lawsuit filed during the Trump administration, the Fish and Wildlife Service granted six permits to bring elephant parts into the country. It may approve more in the coming months.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/science/elephant-trophies-hunting.html', 'The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service informed some hunters last month that it would allow the import of six elephant trophies into the United States from Zimbabwe. The African elephant carcasses will be the first allowed into the country in five years.', 'The New York Times', '01trophies-articleLarge.jpg', '1648825481', '1683923632'),
(389, 3, 0, 272, '53e6db55-2b98-544a-86ec-2bc32fbcc86b', 'An art collector and the institution’s longest-serving board member, she was also a pioneering Black woman in the corporate world.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/arts/nancy-lane-dead.html', 'Nancy Lane, a trailblazing corporate executive who promoted the works of Black artists as a champion of the Studio Museum in Harlem for a half-century, died on March 28 at her home in Manhattan. She was 88.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648825925', '1683923633'),
(390, 8, 6, 273, '660af8ca-c1fb-5417-aa0b-63eeb5eb3438', 'The mystery of nine hikers who died in Russia has baffled people for more than 60 years. The authors of a recent paper think they’ve found another clue.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/world/europe/dyatlov-pass-avalanche-russia.html', 'A small avalanche on a desolate Russian mountain, harming no one and quickly erased by the relentless wind, does not usually make news.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1648826513', '1683923634'),
(391, 2, 0, 60, '93e09221-8a07-5655-a663-0a12b8afe637', 'The companies struggled to produce vehicles in the first three months of the year, a sign that shortages could last longer than executives had hoped.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/business/toyota-general-motors-sales-reports.html', 'General Motors and Toyota Motor suffered significant drops in car and truck sales in the United States in the first three months of the year as the global shortage of computer chips continued to disrupt production and leave dealers with bare lots.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_199914297_1f2298f6-6794-4660-9666-f426df5a01e2-articleLarge.jpg', '1648826718', '1683923635'),
(392, 12, 0, 274, '5c3454e0-ef86-5d1a-b4dd-ac72a2af7405', 'His attention-getting first book, “Easy Travel to Other Planets,” began with dolphin-human sex. The three that followed were comparably offbeat.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/books/ted-mooney-dead.html', 'Ted Mooney, who opened his first book, in 1981, with a scene of dolphin-human sex, and who proceeded to write three other offbeat, inventive novels at roughly 10-year intervals, died on March 25 at his home in Manhattan. He was 70.', 'The New York Times', '01mooney-image-articleLarge.jpg', '1648826768', '1683923636'),
(393, 1, 30, 275, '2b9ec12f-bcbc-5f69-99b4-8517c755f09a', 'Everyone talks about it, no one wants to be in it, and it may not even really exist.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/01/sports/soccer/group-of-death-world-cup.html', 'Everyone talks about it, no one wants to be in it, and it may not even really exist.', 'The New York Times', '01world-cup-draw-group-of-death-articleLarge.jpg', '1648828216', '1683923637'),
