(811, 21, 0, 491, 'a0d1b1d4-396b-5017-bf10-de64b3e2f8f1', 'Limits were placed on high-end GPUs that power supercomputers and artificial intelligence, said Nvidia and AMD, two Silicon Valley chip makers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/technology/gpu-chips-china-russia.html', 'The Biden administration has imposed new restrictions on sales of some sophisticated computer chips to China and Russia, the U.S. government’s latest attempt to use semiconductors as a tool to hobble rivals’ advances in fields such as high-performance computing and artificial intelligence.', 'The New York Times', '31chips-china-articleLarge.jpg', '1661994871', '1683927513'),
(812, 1, 31, 245, '528ee250-f930-5c1f-877c-1e2dcb3ff2f6', 'If two nights earlier was about posterity and sweet send-offs, Round 2 was about doing everything possible to win a tennis match, as Williams beat the world No. 2, Anett Kontaveit, in three sets.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/sports/tennis/serena-williams-us-open-win.html', 'The U.S. Open threw the closest thing to a farewell celebration that Serena Williams would allow for her opening-round match Monday night. But if a party was all that the 23-time Grand Slam singles champion wanted, she could have thrown herself one and skipped all those hours of sweat on the hard courts back home in Florida.', 'The New York Times', '31serena-second-match-ledeall-win1-articleLarge.jpg', '1661996729', '1683927514'),
(813, 4, 0, 225, 'd4658ec7-b150-5ee7-b48e-8fd71abd2874', 'John Wrenholt helps us figure things out.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-09-01.html', 'THURSDAY PUZZLE — We all have our weaknesses, and one of mine is the topic of today’s crossword theme. And yet, I had a great time solving John Wrenholt’s puzzle. It didn’t really require specialized knowledge, and it kept a smile on my face as the theme revealed itself.', 'The New York Times', '01wordplay-jet-articleLarge.jpg', '1661997603', '1683927515'),
(814, 1, 31, 166, '7759eb54-54a9-55d0-a337-722e1541ee32', 'Tomljanovic beat Evgeniya Rodina of Russia in three sets, 1-6, 6-2, 7-5.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/sports/tennis/serena-williams-ajla-tomljanovic-third-round.html', 'The scene was quieter on the much smaller Court 7, with only a few dozen people sitting on the metal bleachers on Wednesday night to watch Ajla Tomljanovic of Australia defeat Evgeniya Rodina of Russia in three sets.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211728030_39244756-5104-407b-8d8c-ef102b7b2251-articleLarge.jpg', '1661997790', '1683927516'),
(815, 10, 5, 492, '810358ae-0037-5f2f-87bf-fcd0e16fd87d', 'A filing claimed that the Justice Department was criminalizing the former president’s possession of “his own presidential records,” a stance at odds with the Presidential Records Act.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/us/politics/trump-court-documents.html', 'WASHINGTON — Former President Donald J. Trump’s legal team on Wednesday aggressively renewed its push for an independent arbiter to review documents the F.B.I. seized in its Aug. 8 search of his Florida residence, telling a federal judge that he had merely possessed “his own presidential records.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211635216_c0f6d511-dc2b-4ea3-a905-f0d0d76210a6-articleLarge.jpg', '1661998514', '1683927517'),
(816, 1, 31, 342, '90469ddf-9b85-5ddf-9345-94183f582148', 'Kontaveit was up for the challenge of facing Williams in front of fans who had little interest in her winning as they celebrate Williams’s career. She forced a third set, but the fans got what they wanted.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/31/sports/tennis/serena-williams-kontaveit-crowd-us-open.html', 'Anett Kontaveit walked out of the players’ tunnel first, with barely a notice from the audience in Arthur Ashe Stadium, which was half full at the time. She made a small waving gesture, to no one in particular, and then went to her chair to prepare for her role as the villain in the biggest tennis spectacle of her life: the Serena Williams U.S. Open.', 'The New York Times', '31usopen-serena-sidebar1-articleLarge.jpg', '1661998646', '1683927519'),
(817, 6, 0, 0, '76070cc6-204f-5cbe-a049-52c5f58ab4f3', 'Quotation of the Day for Thursday, Sept. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/todayspaper/quotation-of-the-day-taking-aim-with-tanks-at-gorbachevs-legacy.html', '“They gave us the gift of at least 30 years of life without the threat of a global nuclear war. We have wasted this gift. The gift does not exist anymore.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662004860', '1683927519'),
(818, 7, 0, 0, 'fd2a9902-34e5-552c-9722-d5cbd0f23740', 'Corrections that appeared in print on Thursday, Sept. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/pageoneplus/corrections-sept-1-2022.html', 'An article on Wednesday about the rescheduling of the Artemis I mission launch because of an engine problem misstated the name of the launch weather officer. He is Mark Burger, not Marc Berger.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662004861', '1683927520'),
(819, 10, 0, 493, '32604986-fa76-56fb-b3af-fa871a49dd63', 'The results of a national test showed just how devastating the last two years have been for 9-year-old schoolchildren, especially the most vulnerable.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/us/national-test-scores-math-reading-pandemic.html', 'National test results released on Thursday showed in stark terms the pandemic’s devastating effects on American schoolchildren, with the performance of 9-year-olds in math and reading dropping to the levels from two decades ago. ', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_196962087_2696337d-848e-4ca8-9e1b-a27bcee3e63b-articleLarge.jpg', '1662004866', '1683927521'),
(820, 5, 0, 494, '9f7d2592-83e4-50a9-9b8e-b3f00cc175c0', 'In an effort to regulate guns, the city drew a new map of its famed district. Some New Yorkers beg to differ.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/nyregion/where-exactly-is-times-square-its-complicated.html', 'Good morning. It’s Thursday. Today we will look at Times Square — what its boundaries are, and why that question has suddenly become important. We will also look at tennis, New York City style, as it is played on public courts.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662005405', '1683927522'),
(821, 19, 0, 69, '4ccbb3a5-688a-54e0-bea6-562f2a1cd373', 'Vladimir Putin reacts to Mikhail Gorbachev’s death.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/briefing/putin-gorbachev-russia-draft.html', 'After Mikhail Gorbachev died at 91, all eyes turned to Vladimir Putin, the leader of Russia.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662006701', '1683927523'),
(822, 13, 0, 0, '5fa85290-ad4f-5865-8c4a-a4028b223de5', 'Twelve public school teachers joined Times Opinion to discuss the state of education today.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-teachers.html', 'Twelve public school teachers joined Times Opinion to discuss the state of education today.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662008401', '1683927524'),
(823, 8, 4, 495, '5ebbcc1b-60b7-50d5-8e8b-f734ebd59f6b', 'The package includes nearly $3 billion in loans for an island nation that ousted its president amid a devastating economic crisis.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/asia/sri-lanka-imf-bailout.html', 'COLOMBO, Sri Lanka — Sri Lanka and the International Monetary Fund on Thursday reached a preliminary agreement on a bailout package as the bankrupt island nation tries to rebuild trust with lenders and find a way out of a crippling economic crisis that toppled its president.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662010060', '1683927524'),
(824, 8, 6, 300, '057c1616-e9e9-5639-b162-0a1f31e726bb', 'An estimated 2.8 million of the nation’s six million children have been forced from their homes because of the war. If they are fortunate enough to find a seat in a classroom, it will probably be in an unfamiliar town or city.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/europe/pencil-chalk-and-first-aid-kits-ukrainian-children-return-to-school-in-the-midst-of-war.html', 'BUCHA, Ukraine — The bodies that littered the school playground in April are gone. The blood on the walls has been scrubbed clean and workers were repairing shattered windows.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662012027', '1683927525'),
(825, 8, 4, 496, 'eb3254b3-faf7-5cd0-adce-496cc61e63a9', 'The drastic response to a rise in Covid cases adds to the pressures facing Sichuan Province, which already had been dealing with drought, heat and wildfires.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/asia/china-covid-lockdown-chengdu.html', 'China has locked down Chengdu, one of its biggest and most economically important cities, as it turns once again to its Covid strategy of restricting people’s movements to stop outbreaks.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662015403', '1683927527'),
(826, 4, 0, 0, '2d4db7a2-4849-58b7-953f-42ba93ad7595', 'Feeling stuck on today’s puzzle? We can help.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/crosswords/spelling-bee-forum.html', 'THURSDAY — Hi busy bees! Welcome to today’s Spelling Bee forum. There are a number of terms that appear in both this article and other online discussions of the Spelling Bee; a glossary of those terms compiled by Monicat, a Times reader, can be found below. For more Spelling Bee conversation, check out Deb Amlen’s weekly humor column, “Diary of a Spelling Bee Fanatic.”', 'The New York Times', '01bee-forum-thu-articleLarge.jpg', '1662015602', '1683927528'),
(827, 8, 28, 367, '96911d18-498f-58c8-8bb8-7f4f9c11cb20', 'Divisions over the acceptance of homosexuality have proved intractable both on a global level and inside even liberal-leaning countries like New Zealand.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/australia/anglican-church-homosexuality-new-zealand.html', 'WELLINGTON, New Zealand — Craig Watson has spent his life searching for a church that accepts him fully as a gay man. After having left the Baptist church, Mr. Watson thought he had found it within the famously progressive Anglican faith in New Zealand.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662015607', '1683927529'),
(828, 11, 0, 497, 'de2c9f88-b11e-520c-8c97-ec898795e032', 'Shein continues its rise with American shoppers, who don’t mind the controversies.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/shein-clothing.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211977327_a8914bb1-cd91-489a-8444-7ea4e03544ba-articleLarge.jpg', '1662015607', '1683927530'),
(829, 8, 6, 0, '11565566-b60b-5896-914c-a4e7f36644da', 'Rafael M. Grossi, the International Atomic Energy Agency’s secretary general, told reporters he had been briefed on the increased shelling in the region between the Russian and Ukrainian armies.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/video/world/europe/100000008513233/un-team-crosses-buffer-zone.html', 'Rafael M. Grossi, the International Atomic Energy Agency’s secretary general, told reporters he had been briefed on the increased shelling in the region between the Russian and Ukrainian armies.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662016584', '1683927531'),
(830, 8, 4, 498, 'd595b1d7-a0c6-5c9d-8e9b-6884c5e01d70', 'They get paid in formula and diapers, and their work hours are flexible, in a program that connects people across generations and brightens lives.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/asia/japan-nursing-home-babies.html', 'TOKYO — Cooing, giggling and the patter of tiny feet mix with the sound of walkers and wheelchairs at a nursing home in southern Japan. In this graying nation, one home has been recruiting an unusual class of workers to enliven its residents’ days.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662016991', '1683927532'),
(831, 8, 4, 428, '83cc442f-ec33-5d6a-b425-451e1fed3096', 'The report’s assessment that China’s crackdown in Xinjiang could amount to “crimes against humanity” gives new momentum to a campaign to pressure Beijing.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/asia/china-xinjiang-uyghurs.html', 'HONG KONG — At first China said there was “no such thing” as re-education centers that held vast numbers of people in its far western Xinjiang region. Then, as more reports emerged that hundreds of thousands of Uyghurs and members of other largely Muslim groups were being detained, Beijing acknowledged the camps’ existence but described them as vocational training centers.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662018681', '1683927533');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(832, 23, 0, 384, 'd2385a7b-a656-5a1d-add6-4dd894de9d98', 'Two productions at the London playhouse feature heroines who, reluctantly, allow transformative characters into their lives.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/theater/national-theater-all-of-us-much-ado.html', 'LONDON — Love is a powerful, redemptive force at the National Theater here, where two very different shows convey the value of letting someone into your life. “All of Us,” the first play from the performer Francesca Martinez, opens our eyes to the hardships of disabled people in Britain. In a separate auditorium, the playhouse has revived Shakespeare’s “Much Ado About Nothing.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211335939_7924d9a9-3065-4496-b930-2c3e004b5cf9-articleLarge.jpg', '1662020000', '1683927534'),
(833, 13, 0, 0, '0ec6dd42-b2d2-5a28-ab03-c039dc0f0829', 'Writers, parents and students make sense of education’s purpose in America.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/09/01/opinion/schools-education-america.html', 'Writers, parents and students make sense of education’s purpose in America.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022802', '1683927534'),
(834, 13, 0, 0, '996fb3a4-36eb-5bd2-a0ee-1bdd34796530', 'Three parents join Lulu Garcia-Navarro to discuss why their children\'s education became the focus of their activism.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-parents.html', 'Three parents join Lulu Garcia-Navarro to discuss why their children\'s education became the focus of their activism.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022802', '1683927535'),
(835, 24, 0, 499, '414b9671-3fe2-5c72-aa59-105855caf526', 'The 5-month-old boy’s blood sodium levels were dangerously high. The parents were desperate for answers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/magazine/diabetes-insipidus-diagnosis.html', 'The couple sat in silence as they drove home from Blank Children’s Hospital in Des Moines. Their 5-month-old seemed dwarfed by the baby carrier strapped into the back seat. He was tiny. He hadn’t grown since he turned 2 months old. He weighed just 10 pounds — barely three pounds more than when he was born. ', 'The New York Times', '04mag-diagnosis-2-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022807', '1683927537'),
(836, 24, 0, 500, '9b33da55-1ef2-551b-8fbd-f7749eaf13c8', 'This prose poem by Laura Da’ juxtaposes the loss of land and Shawnee culture with the birth of the speaker’s son.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/magazine/poem-nationhood.html', 'This prose poem by Laura Da’ juxtaposes the loss of land and Shawnee culture with the birth of the speaker’s son. It deploys flat and journalistic language to describe the violence of colonialism in America. The poem is written primarily in declaratives: The speaker lists medical facts in the first section and cites incorrect facts in the second. The ending simply states that the speaker lacks “Shawnee words” to describe their nation and culture, and that the only language that’s available is the colonial lingo of surveying and measuring. In this way, the diction of the poem mirrors the precise (but historically incorrect) and cold grammar of cartography. Selected by Victoria Chang', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022807', '1683927538'),
(837, 9, 0, 501, '0c8ea3da-fd60-5cfc-a7c0-b0e160a1efd2', 'After a mouse infestation at her West Village rental, a single mother needed a better spot for her family, including a son with autism. Could she find it downtown?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/09/01/realestate/01hunt-sample.html', 'After a mouse infestation at her West Village rental, a single mother needed a better spot for her family, including a son with autism. Could she find it downtown?', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022807', '1683927539'),
(838, 13, 0, 156, '9e7a2cf3-6a3e-502d-baab-38b613f22e85', 'Amazon’s “The Rings of Power” will struggle to recreate the magic of Middle-earth, a world not fit for “cinematic universe” treatment.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/rings-of-power-amazon-tolkien.html', 'In the months leading up to its premiere this Friday, Amazon Prime’s “The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power” has prompted both excitement and concern among fans at the expansion of J.R.R. Tolkien’s world in the era of the “cinematic universe.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212115159_ad1e4ce7-6a82-4ced-b8f3-e358343b47a9-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022808', '1683927540'),
(839, 12, 17, 502, '5bfd9003-1673-5b00-b28e-9de8d7dd44a8', 'In King’s latest novel, a teenage boy discovers another world beneath a backyard shed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/review/stephen-king-fairy-tale.html', 'Stephen King is no stranger to the portal fantasy genre, or to the kinds of young, unwitting protagonists who end up traveling to other worlds. In “The Gunslinger,” the first volume of his epic Dark Tower series, King gave us 11-year-old Jake Chambers, who arrives in Roland of Gilead’s world after dying in ours. In “The Talisman,” co-written with Peter Straub, 12-year-old Jack Sawyer “flips” between America and the fantastical Territories on a quest to save his mother’s life. Twenty years later, King and Straub sent Jack on another Territories adventure in “Black House,” this time connecting his story to the Dark Tower books and King’s larger multiverse.', 'The New York Times', '06Bell-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022809', '1683927541'),
(840, 24, 0, 503, 'cd2dac12-f04a-5b23-8ca5-2291c8903107', 'Siblings can’t see eye to eye on where to put the litter box.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/magazine/judge-john-hodgman-on-swampy-the-cat.html', 'Alana writes: My little sister and her cat, Swampy, are living with me for a month. Swampy is an excellent cat, but I would like his litter box in our basement apartment with my sister. She wants it in our living room because she doesn’t think Swampy will “feel welcome” upstairs without it. ', 'The New York Times', 'Mag-Hodgman-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022809', '1683927542'),
(841, 13, 0, 504, 'f3c1e68f-0020-553b-9bd6-732af778a9cb', 'I have deep doubts about the intellectual and social value of schooling. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-knowledge.html', 'I have deep doubts about the intellectual and social value of schooling. My argument in a nutshell: First, everyone leaves school eventually. Second, most of what you learn in school doesn’t matter after graduation. Third, human beings soon forget knowledge they rarely use.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022810', '1683927542'),
(842, 13, 0, 505, '444f35a7-2c91-529b-981e-e24e65debaeb', 'Many migrant parents believe that American schools promise their children the opportunity for a better life.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-immigrant-children.html', 'It was a cold day in January 2019, and Heidi, who was 6 years old, was ready for her first day of school in the United States. Her father, Jorge, woke up early to help her with her hair and pack her lunch. Jorge and Heidi had migrated from Guatemala to the United States in 2018. (I am using their first names only because of their vulnerable and changing immigration status.) Upon arrival at the Mexico-U.S. border, they were separated. For more than two months Jorge was in Texas while his daughter was 1,700 miles away in New York City.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022813', '1683927543'),
(843, 13, 0, 506, 'abfb3fb8-58b5-550c-bbcb-5d1dc6b5b4db', 'It can be a safe haven for our most vulnerable children.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-care.html', 'Kimberly Wilson’s TikTok videos often begin with the back of a little girl’s head. The child’s hair is matted, and Wilson, who works at Butcher-Greene Elementary in Grandview, Mo., begins to gently comb out the snarls. By the end of the videos, which tend to be just a minute or two long, the girl’s hair has been transformed into a beautiful braided style, often with colorful bows adorning it.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022813', '1683927544'),
(844, 11, 0, 507, 'e9b24fdc-cf13-5536-a79f-36174c083901', 'The fashion-turned-furniture designer lets his creativity flow from wherever.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/rogan-gregory-designer.html', 'The artist and designer Rogan Gregory often has a spasm of creativity after midnight, shaking off slumber at 1 a.m. or 2 a.m. to take notes or sketch ideas for his furniture and objects. The habit is his version of the “dorveille,” a period of creative wakefulness.', 'The New York Times', '04sp-design-gregory1-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022813', '1683927545'),
(845, 1, 31, 508, 'e909533b-45f4-50f3-bd7b-a24b19aba4cf', 'Of course Serena Williams is confident. She deserves to be. And her opponents know that her improving game and overwhelming crowd support make beating her in this U.S. Open all the more difficult.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/sports/tennis/serena-williams-us-open-run.html', 'Serena Williams is almost 41. She did not play competitive tennis for nearly a year, and it showed — truly it showed — at Wimbledon, in Toronto and in Mason, Ohio, the three tournaments where she made painfully brief appearances this summer before arriving in New York for her farewell U.S. Open.', 'The New York Times', '01usopen-serena-ontennis01-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022814', '1683927546'),
(846, 10, 5, 315, '9781caf4-fb56-5d5e-bb8c-7bc4a39c8c82', 'In a prime-time speech in Philadelphia, President Biden cast the midterm elections as a choice between his agenda and the extremism of “MAGA Republicans.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/us/politics/biden-speech-trump-maga.html', 'PHILADELPHIA — President Biden traveled to Independence Hall on Thursday to warn that America\'s democratic values are under assault by forces of extremism loyal to former President Donald J. Trump, using a prime-time address to define the midterm elections as a “battle for the soul of this nation.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022815', '1683927547'),
(847, 1, 1, 5, '141d8da2-06db-580c-8794-4beeb7b05fb9', 'The play Kenny Pickett made famous has been banned. Defensive holding? Now an automatic first down. And the N.C.A.A. is still trying to rid the game of feigned injuries.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/sports/ncaafootball/college-football-rule-changes.html', 'For all that does not seem to change in college football — Alabama around the top of the polls, hype about Texas, Kirk Ferentz as Iowa’s coach — the sport’s rule book gets some rewrites and tweaks before every season.', 'The New York Times', '01cb-slide-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022816', '1683927548'),
(848, 13, 0, 509, '306b185f-b6c4-5619-8543-f3fcd8e525a3', 'If politics is the art of the possible, perhaps the biggest silver lining of these past two years has been to redefine what is possible.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-social-mobility.html', 'America is often hailed as a land of opportunity, a place where all children, no matter their family background, have the chance to succeed. Data measuring how low-income children tend to fare in adulthood, however, suggest this may be more myth than reality.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022816', '1683927549'),
(849, 12, 17, 111, 'a74c30c3-ce10-562a-8946-65a2f42e5057', 'In her new novel, “On the Rooftop,” Margaret Wilkerson Sexton introduces a musical family with wide-ranging visions of happiness.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/review/on-the-rooftop-margaret-wilkerson-sexton.html', 'Welcome to Group Text, a monthly column for readers and book clubs about the novels, memoirs and short-story collections that make you want to talk, ask questions, and dwell in another world for a little bit longer.', 'The New York Times', '06GroupText-SEXTON-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022816', '1683927550'),
(850, 3, 3, 471, 'b50d170f-77b7-5ce8-a7b0-98b0a9545afd', 'Amazon’s pricey, gorgeous fantasy spectacle delivers what fans expect, but it could thrive by giving them what they don’t.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/arts/television/the-rings-of-power-lotr-review.html', 'What does several hundred million dollars buy?', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212209122_a6fc8ec8-46ce-4026-b343-2721a31d5f1a-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022818', '1683927551'),
(851, 13, 0, 510, 'b9647a37-ce42-57c3-9cc0-355a2d9fdef5', 'Public education requires lessons about history and also contact with and context about other Americans: who we are and what has made us.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-citizenship.html', 'Why do we have public schools? To make young people into educated, productive adults, of course. But public schools are also for making Americans. Thus, public education requires lessons about history — the American spirit and its civics — and also contact with and context about other Americans: who we are and what has made us.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022818', '1683927552'),
(852, 13, 0, 511, 'b67cb4da-392b-5db4-a56d-6ddbc6c6d08f', 'All kinds of kids, from all kinds of families — rich, poor and middle class — need more help with reading than they’re getting in school. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-reading.html', 'The most important thing schools can do is teach children how to read. If you can read, you can learn anything. If you can’t, almost everything in school is difficult. Word problems. Test directions. Biology homework. Everything comes back to reading.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022819', '1683927553'),
(853, 12, 17, 0, '58c0bae3-b4fb-56ff-a1ed-9ffaaa696a89', '“Somewhere along the line I liberated myself from the idea that I have to finish every book I start, instantly enlarging my exposure to new kinds of books.,” says the author and illustrator, whose latest picture book is “The Pigeon Will Ride the Roller Co', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/review/mo-willems-books-reading.html', 'It’s a joy to read a few pages in my library in the evenings. Weekend reading outside is also wonderful. But I think I most love a reading lunch with my wife, because we get to chat about what we’ve just read over coffee.', 'The New York Times', '04ByTheBook-WILLEMS-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022820', '1683927554'),
(854, 12, 17, 512, '2844519c-8b4b-56cb-aea2-115b29f18d3f', 'Max Fisher’s “The Chaos Machine” examines the psychological impacts of technology.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/review/max-fisher-chaos-machine.html', 'In Max Fisher’s authoritative and devastating account of the impacts of social media, “The Chaos Machine,” he repeatedly invokes Stanley Kubrick’s masterpiece “2001: A Space Odyssey.” The 1968 movie, in which a supercomputer coldly kills astronauts on a ship bound for Jupiter, was in Fisher’s thoughts as he researched the book. Its stark, ambiguous aesthetic is perfectly poised between the utopian and the dystopian. And as a story about trying to fix a wayward technology as it hurtles out of control, it is beautifully apt.', 'The New York Times', '06SHAWCOVER-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022822', '1683927555'),
(855, 13, 0, 513, '7c30e39a-a6f1-5712-8b90-08c6a4702d20', 'Merit demands excellence and rigor. It is not, as its critics often insist, an elitist, classist or racist value.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-merit.html', 'In 1982, as a 5-foot-0 teen at Morgantown High School in the foothills of West Virginia’s Appalachians, I stepped forward at our annual sports award ceremony to claim an honor: female athlete with the highest G.P.A. A boy named Michael Roh, who won the male athlete award, towered over me at 6-foot-6. He’d been my academic rival since middle school. But on this day, we both smiled. We had both ascended based on hard work and merit.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022823', '1683927556'),
(856, 17, 0, 210, 'f5ba3041-8365-5f75-a7c4-537f8480036f', 'A ban on single-use plastic and paper bags in grocery stores had an unintended effect: Delivery services switched to heavy, reusable sacks — lots of them.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/climate/paper-plastic-bag-ban-new-jersey.html', 'Nicole Kramaritsch of Roxbury, N.J., has 46 bags just sitting in her garage. Brian Otto has 101 of them, so many that he’s considering sewing them into blackout curtains for his baby’s bedroom. (So far, that idea has gone nowhere.) Lili Mannuzza in Whippany has 74.', 'The New York Times', '31cli-njbags1-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022824', '1683927557'),
(857, 1, 31, 322, '9c324c57-b587-5d1c-8995-5e5081ec600d', 'Since the Williams sisters first burst into tennis in the 1990s, their legacy has been tied to one another. They will play doubles in perhaps the final tournament of their careers.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/sports/tennis/serena-venus-williams-doubles.html', 'The Williams sisters. They are the yin to the other’s yang. Starkly different in disposition but tied together by history and sisterly bond.', 'The New York Times', '01streeter-sot-4-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022829', '1683927558'),
(858, 9, 0, 514, '8232c810-88e8-585e-be9b-a79b2e4dcb27', 'A new study digs into what is most important to young adults ages 18 to 25.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/realestate/generation-z-best-cities.html', 'Jumping into adulthood has been tough of late. When the coronavirus pandemic hit, young adults scurried back to their parents’ or grandparents’ homes. Roughly 80 percent of them were members of Generation Z, those born in the late 1990s through the early 2000s; a third of that generation is still living there today. Now, inflation and competition for rentals have created more obstacles to moving out.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022832', '1683927558'),
(859, 3, 3, 515, '98a9de23-7275-5b74-8390-d14aeaa20529', '“The U.S. and the Holocaust,” coming to PBS Sept. 18, examines the reasons behind the country’s inadequate response to Germany’s persecution of Jews.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/arts/television/ken-burns-the-us-and-the-holocaust.html', 'A new documentary about the Holocaust opens with photos of perhaps the most familiar faces from that dark chapter of history: those of Anne Frank and her family, whose story has been read or seen by millions around the world.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211305507_d5f6101c-3b08-4379-bd12-c35ba9b5074b-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022833', '1683927559'),
(860, 13, 0, 516, '42964c8f-9116-5e5b-896a-71df4d54dd54', 'Our democracy sprouts in the nursery of public schools — where students grapple, together, with our messy history and learn to negotiate differences.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-history.html', 'For the majority of human history, most people didn’t go to school. Formal education was a privilege for the Alexander the Greats of the world, who could hire Aristotles as private tutors.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022834', '1683927560'),
(861, 9, 0, 501, 'b4028644-0ae3-5565-916f-96e7defd3aaf', 'The painting, known as “Swing Girl” and “Girl on a Swing,” and the building it adorns are headed to the auction block with the hope that the sale price will reach $30 million.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/realestate/banksy-swing-girl-los-angeles-building.html', 'In 2010, while in town for the Los Angeles premiere of his documentary “Exit Through the Gift Shop,” the British street artist Banksy left a gift for fans: a mural of a girl on a swing, dangling beneath the five-foot red “A” of the word “PARKING” on a gritty downtown lot.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212131137_ff64a25b-fd46-4f05-9131-5c6704686eab-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022836', '1683927561'),
(862, 11, 0, 517, 'e14ce03a-9a37-562b-912a-d3c8b2c30a5e', 'Cotton forms the foundation of Caralarga’s objects and fashions.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/caralarga-mexico-design-firm.html', 'The way Ana Holschneider explained it, everything Caralarga makes is jewelry. It all depends on how you wear it.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211226289_a16c3f0e-caad-49d8-80a0-1f8d4a9b72e0-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022842', '1683927562'),
(863, 8, 6, 317, '3ef8dfd8-904f-5341-adc8-44b2c2accf17', 'A successful deal to restrain Iran’s nuclear program would mean that Washington lifts tough sanctions on Iran’s oil and gas exports. But it may already be too late for that to help this winter.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/europe/iran-nuclear-deal-energy-prices.html', 'BRUSSELS — As Russia squeezes Europe on supplies of natural gas and Europe readies an embargo on Russian oil, some are looking for help from Iran. That is, of course, if and when Tehran and Washington agree to revive the 2015 nuclear deal, lifting tough economic sanctions on Iran that have limited its ability to export energy.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022843', '1683927563'),
(864, 12, 17, 111, 'af7f7504-30f4-5eed-b3f3-e8fd4234f1f6', 'When the “Crime Junkie” co-host’s debut novel came out, it didn’t seem real until she signed copies to the sound of boarding announcements.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/review/all-good-people-here-ashley-flowers.html', 'When Ashley Flowers strolled into Hudson News in Indianapolis International Airport and spotted a book with her name on the cover, she knew she had arrived.', 'The New York Times', '01Insidethelist-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022843', '1683927564'),
(865, 3, 0, 0, '4671a25a-4551-58af-a986-3c97ff7c34ba', 'A look at design-world events, products and people.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/arts/design-world-events-products-people.html', 'For the German-born designer Jan Kath, now living in Chiang Mai, Thailand, rugs are not just decorative objects; they also reflect global politics. His “Rug Bombs” exhibition of 11 handknotted works at the Alte Brüderkirche, a church in Kassel, Germany, follows a modern tradition by artisans in troubled countries of weaving images of violence and warfare into textiles.', 'The New York Times', '04sp-design-pano-rugs2-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022848', '1683927565'),
(866, 23, 0, 392, 'f5b4c16e-8d32-5d2f-9b5f-9a4c490c5881', 'She’s landed her dream role in “Funny Girl.” Now she’s tasked with rescuing the faltering Broadway show and proving that she is not the person she once was.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/theater/lea-michele-funny-girl-broadway.html', 'Fifteen years ago, Lea Michele was sulking in her “Spring Awakening” dressing room, heartbroken over a guy, when the Broadway show’s director offered her a bit of advice.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211790082_ed31f826-ffb5-4b1d-a048-d200c2614c6d-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022848', '1683927566'),
(867, 13, 0, 518, 'ad2a8322-f9db-546b-9be3-47c9b0db549f', 'School is for nurturing children’s innate talents and helping them figure out where those gifts, necessarily diverse, fit in the whole. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-school-nature.html', 'Throughout the first five years of my older daughter’s life, I watched her dance through the clover, climb trees, puddle jump and play her way through the day. As she stood on the threshold to kindergarten, I pictured her stuck inside at a desk, cut off from her relationship to the wild, and my stomach sank. I believe that school is for nurturing children’s innate talents and helping them figure out where those gifts, necessarily diverse, fit in the whole. The school system, by contrast, tends to produce a monoculture. Despite the heroic efforts of many thoughtful, caring teachers, public school mostly prepares children to be obedient workers and fails millions of students who don’t fit the mold.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212104140_543ab7b3-5339-45ee-85ad-9520f784257d-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022849', '1683927567'),
(868, 11, 0, 519, 'a42eb132-afac-596b-8434-8a3d7ef58ac0', 'Eric Egan’s interior design studio upholds couture traditions with exquisite — but far from stodgy — details for the home.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/eric-egan-design-studio-milan.html', 'MILAN — Across the street from the medieval Sforzesco Castle, up an iron cage elevator and through a dark-paneled foyer, sits a showroom that is a shrine to the bespoke with a particularly Italian attitude.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211038837_4c5ad6ce-dcbf-47ef-860d-98f5bb317121-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022850', '1683927568'),
(869, 24, 0, 520, 'e9fdcd05-c1eb-5162-9d89-3b5e9e6d58e0', 'Survivors describe the defining atrocity of the war in Ukraine.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/magazine/ukraine-mariupol-theater.html', 'Elyzaveta Fatayeva was sitting on a blanket in the basement, next to her boyfriend, when the theater exploded above her. The whole building convulsed, and she with it. Her ears filled with a tremendous crashing sound. Her eyes squeezed shut for a moment. When they opened, the air was a cloud of masonry dust. She gasped it in and choked. When her breath returned, there was a ringing in her ears. Then silence. Then people around her coughing. Then yelling. ', 'The New York Times', '04mag-Mariupol-15-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022850', '1683927569'),
(870, 25, 0, 521, '451cf9d8-9564-5f3d-ae7c-64869b270e31', 'The pandemic may have left some gaps in the urban fabric, but a neighborhood-by-neighborhood rundown of new restaurants and art events reveals that recovery is well underway.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/travel/things-to-do-seattle.html', 'On Feb. 9, 2020, the Seattle Asian Art Museum reopened after a three-year, $56 million renovation and expansion that transformed the look, feel and reach of the venerable institution. Five weeks later, the first round of statewide Covid lockdowns shuttered the place. “It was heartbreaking for me and my colleagues,” said Foong Ping, the Foster Foundation Curator of Chinese Art at the museum. “It was shoulder to shoulder in the newly imagined galleries — then silence.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212004255_09141470-97e7-405d-b758-eda0b21e706c-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022852', '1683927570'),
(871, 3, 12, 522, 'b5c90ada-a513-5cfb-b843-1455841a1023', 'New books on gnarly trees with pedigrees, lost Miami buildings and vintage construction toys, along with a deep dive into African textiles.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/arts/design/architecture-books.html', 'The landscape architect Frederick Law Olmsted, in laying out thousands of 19th-century parkland acres, specified fine points down to the rock textures. The serendipities of age keep improving his designs. “Olmsted Trees” (Hirmer/University of Chicago Press, $40, 160 pp.), by the photographer Stanley Greenberg, celebrates bark that resembles barnacles, lizard skin or cooled lava. (The book includes essays by Tom Avermaete, an urban design professor; Kevin Baker, a writer; and Mindy Thompson Fullilove, a social psychiatrist.) Torqued trunks have knobs and cavities that evoke human eyes and animal snouts, while roots bulge like giant paws kneading the earth. The trees shrug off signs of human intervention, dwarfing fencing and playground equipment, and appearing unfazed by carvings of lovers’ initials.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211047714_577799f9-da6f-4a96-89a2-30763225b4e5-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022858', '1683927572'),
(872, 26, 0, 523, '23888095-282c-572f-8140-c7e54057ac8f', 'At 83, the filmmaker behind “Cooley High” and “Car Wash” may be the longest-working Black director in history. His own story is a Hollywood epic.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/michael-schultz-krush-groove-car-wash-cooley-high.html', 'When Michael Schultz began work on his first film, in 1971, there was no road map for a lengthy career as a Black director in Hollywood. The first two studio movies to employ Black directors — Gordon Parks’s “The Learning Tree” (1969) and Ossie Davis’s “Cotton Comes to Harlem” (1970) — had only relatively recently left theaters. And the movement that would soon be known as Blaxploitation — mimicking the work of Davis, Parks and the trailblazing independent filmmaker Melvin Van Peebles — did little to suggest a promising future.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211900128_a62b38d4-3303-4470-93df-3aa2c4d25243-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022859', '1683927573'),
(873, 21, 0, 524, 'e78e123e-3255-55c8-84ca-0a1b88220a57', 'As Apple prepares to unveil new models next week, the smart watch has found an unexpected audience: children as young as 5.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/technology/apple-watch-children-kids.html', 'Florian Fangohr waffled for about a year over whether to buy an Apple Watch SE as a gift. The smart watch cost $279, and he worried that its recipient would immediately break or lose it. In May, he decided the benefits outweighed the costs and bought the gadget.', 'The New York Times', '00applewatch-3-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022861', '1683927574'),
(874, 11, 0, 525, '981cf029-3581-5362-8bb2-69f705fa90ae', 'For three-quarters of a century, the $1.7 trillion global fashion industry has found opportunity in home furnishings.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/fashion-home-furnishings.html', 'Ralph Lauren Home. Fendi Casa. Louis Vuitton’s Art of Living. Fashion companies cannot seem to resist the lure of household objects.', 'The New York Times', '04sp-design-timeline3-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022862', '1683927575'),
(875, 2, 11, 172, '0135331d-0256-5cd3-a4f4-976e71fce6ad', 'Long cut off from the continent’s grid, Portugal and Spain built a system based on imports and alternatives like solar that is the envy of fellow European Union nations.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/business/economy/portugal-russia-natural-gas.html', 'Portugal has no coal mines, oil wells or gas fields. Its impressive hydropower production has been crippled this year by drought. And its long-running disconnect from the rest of Europe’s energy network has earned the country its status as an “energy island.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212177901_9a7b27cf-3085-476d-93f7-6c8002e62fe5-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022870', '1683927576'),
(876, 2, 0, 337, '24d230aa-87e9-5aff-8757-509edb59fc00', 'Worried about geopolitical tensions and stung by pandemic shutdowns, Google, Apple and others are moving some work to nearby countries.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/business/tech-companies-china.html', 'In the coming weeks, Apple and Google will unveil their latest generation of smartphones, jockeying to distinguish the new devices from previous models. But one of the most significant changes will go largely unnoticed by consumers: Some of these phones will not be made in China.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211859484_b665be17-7162-4260-9d0f-9c65a988b5f7-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022870', '1683927577'),
(877, 32, 39, 409, '2d0add91-ea55-5a0a-9fd6-c1e8cad58cc2', 'For those who crave efficiency, some websites tackle wedding planning with an add-to-cart approach.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/fashion/weddings/wedding-planning-online-shopping.html', 'It wasn’t long after Samantha Tully and Colton Sykes began planning their nuptials before the process became overwhelming.', 'The New York Times', '01ONE-CLICK-WEDDINGS-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022870', '1683927578'),
(878, 12, 0, 526, 'b6371397-97b6-5014-90cf-0c4bccc85459', 'New novels from Stephen King, Elizabeth Strout and Maggie O’Farrell; stories by Ling Ma and David Means; and plenty more.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/books/new-books-september.html', 'The author, a civil rights activist, traces the roots of political dissatisfaction among many Black voters and examines the ways she believes Democratic Party has abandoned them.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022870', '1683927580'),
(879, 11, 0, 527, '62eee427-af4f-58d9-bdac-e5cd0b03a51e', 'It can be a short step from a runway look to a home furnishing — especially if the designer has a foot in both worlds.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/household-goods-fashion.html', 'When you ask Raf Simons, the co-creative director of Prada, why he abandoned his intended career as a furniture designer for fashion, he has two words to say: “Martin Margiela” (referring to the avant-garde couturier and fellow Belgian). But when Mr. Simons returned to his furnishing roots recently to create a Shaker-inspired storage system that mounts on a wall, it hardly seemed like a step away.', 'The New York Times', '04sp-design-products-simons-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022871', '1683927581'),
(880, 13, 0, 528, '9c5cc643-5d84-53d0-b01d-dc3149f5c7d3', 'What is school really for? Students at Oakland’s Fremont High answer this question with their cameras.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/opinion/us-high-school-oakland.html', 'OAKLAND, Calif. — School is a community, a common place to gain relationships. School is for social interactions and learning to become an active member of society.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662022871', '1683927582'),
(881, 11, 0, 529, '39cdcd0d-a8ee-577b-a650-4ac9931f8b23', '“It’s a bit of fashion, a bit of design, but I see it more like a book about paintings,” said the author, Benoit Pierre Emery.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/scarves-benoit-pierre-emery.html', 'LONDON — When Benoit Pierre Emery bought a silk Christian Dior scarf from the 1970s for about $30 on eBay in 2001, little did he realize it would be the seed of a collection that would grow to more than 10,000 pieces over two decades and lead to a book to be published later this year.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_210662355_b57ec52a-e76e-4806-8be6-dac9625c769f-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022987', '1683927583'),
(882, 3, 12, 530, '5b892098-a604-5b8b-bdd7-5f8c7f8c513a', 'Once the head of women’s wear for Stella McCartney and Jil Sander, Leena Similu has taken a 180-degree turn into ceramics.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/arts/design/leena-similu-ceramics.html', 'LOS ANGELES — Leena Similu leads the way from her porch to her backyard, in a hilly portion of Silver Lake. Outside, she passes a large electric kiln, a potter’s wheel and a shelf of grimacing and grinning figures that have come to define her ceramics work. Near the back door of her house, a child’s scooter lies on its side.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211220814_124176d5-d71a-4375-ac01-543fc67db035-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022988', '1683927584'),
(883, 11, 0, 519, '972a4cc5-a028-5630-a430-58a574cfaf94', 'Questions on filling a home, carving out guest quarters, deciding whether to choose marble and finding a decent-looking light switch.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/style/design-questions-answers.html', 'I recently relocated and took with me basically nothing. What’s the best strategy to fill up an apartment? Should I buy everything at once? Or wait and build it out?', 'The New York Times', '04sp-design-qna-03-articleLarge.jpg', '1662022988', '1683927585'),
(884, 1, 23, 301, 'ebd20409-75c1-5ca4-8f02-f67ddaba07e5', 'Edwin Díaz’s entrance music has been a sensation this season, and the Australian trumpet player appearing in person made it that much better.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/09/01/sports/baseball/edwin-diaz-timmy-trumpet.html', 'Edwin Díaz’s entrance music has been a sensation this season, and the Australian trumpet player appearing in person made it that much better.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662026401', '1683927586'),
(885, 1, 23, 361, 'e23ddf7c-0c64-5b51-ad51-aedef08e6c8f', 'Jacob deGrom dominated, Brandon Nimmo made a catch to remember and Timmy Trumpet played a live version of Edwin Díaz’s entrance song during a thrilling win.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/sports/baseball/brandon-nimmo-mets-dodgers.html', 'On a shelf in his spare locker at Citi Field, Brandon Nimmo has a baseball with a series of markings by Wayne Kirby, the Mets’ first base coach. Kirby noted the data from a stellar play Nimmo made earlier this summer, inscribing it: “Best Catch 2022.”', 'The New York Times', '01kepner-mets-nimmo-horiz-articleLarge.jpg', '1662026404', '1683927587'),
(886, 27, 20, 257, 'aa53c605-3904-57e9-9bff-93e096438c03', 'Mikhail S. Gorbachev set out to reform the Soviet Union. But the social and economic forces he unleashed ended up destroying it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/podcasts/the-daily/gorbachev-dead-putin-soviet-union.html', 'Few leaders have had as profound an effect on their time as Mikhail S. Gorbachev, the last leader of the Soviet Union, who died this week at 91.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662026405', '1683927588'),
(887, 19, 0, 531, 'ca87d157-b2f0-5e8c-89b3-54847cf23833', 'Why NASA wants to go back now.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/briefing/nasa-moon-mars-space-travel.html', 'Human beings will soon walk on the moon again, if NASA gets its way.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212196810_ddba68d4-fa77-4be6-8aa0-c273c30361f8-articleLarge.jpg', '1662027325', '1683927589'),
(888, 26, 0, 212, 'e6091ffd-815f-5e31-9e49-a432e851826b', 'The film, about a Russian intelligence officer’s covert mission at the end of World War II, begins on a suspenseful note, but the tension soon dissipates.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/burial-review-corpse-ride.html', '“Burial” begins suspensefully enough. It opens in 1991 at the London home of a Russian Jewish woman, Anna (Harriet Walter), as she watches TV news of Mikhail S. Gorbachev’s resignation as the Soviet president.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212008110_0e54cb9d-650f-42d3-9f6e-5f2de1206587-articleLarge.jpg', '1662030005', '1683927590'),
(889, 26, 0, 532, 'f0cef1f0-d7df-5793-94a2-4ee095e0523c', 'A team of African mercenaries encounters supernatural foes in this fable-like adventure.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/saloum-review.html', 'Revenge, trauma, child exploitation and environmental degradation — all of these, to one extent or another, undergird the feverish momentum of “Saloum,” a picture that proceeds with more visual brio than narrative clarity.', 'The New York Times', 'saloum-review-articleLarge.jpg', '1662030005', '1683927591'),
(890, 26, 0, 533, '0dec3ff2-b947-5c1e-abf3-323a7a920d24', 'Set in Paris in the 1960s, the film tells the story of two irrepressible lovers, and their young son, whose tale turns tragic.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/waiting-for-bojangles-review-endless-love.html', 'Régis Roinsard’s “Waiting for Bojangles,” based on the novel by Olivier Bourdeaut, is a film so unabashedly romantic that it could only be French. It tells the story of two boundless, irrepressible lovers, Georges (Romain Duris) and Camile (Virginie Efira), and the life they share in Paris in the 1960s with their young son, Gary (Solan Machado-Graner).', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212008902_6560ab65-e3d2-40d0-966d-7330a9cef871-articleLarge.jpg', '1662030006', '1683927592'),
(891, 26, 0, 534, '406087a6-6fe0-5776-9ff2-263385f26688', 'In this documentary about his life and career, the tennis player John McEnroe, known for his temper, doesn’t bother trying to apologize for his behavior.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/mcenroe-review.html', 'John McEnroe knows it’s too late to apologize. In “McEnroe,” a new documentary chronicling his meteoric rise in the world of tennis, the champion who still holds more titles than any other male player certainly expresses regret over his past behavior, both on the court and off. In the contemporary interviews that frame the documentary, written and directed by Barney Douglas, McEnroe is wise enough to know a “sorry” won’t cut it.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212008689_e048543f-1563-4169-8220-b11cea30d467-articleLarge.jpg', '1662030006', '1683927593'),
(892, 26, 0, 534, '2750d851-fe8f-54a6-8eca-57c2a87a09a1', 'A documentary examines race in football via Colin Kaepernick’s career.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/movies/kaepernick-america-review.html', 'In the past, when people talked about football heroes, both collegiate and professional, they meant white men. When the game became more integrated, after World War II, a racist myth among some fans held that Black players were good for muscle, while strategic thinking was the domain of white quarterbacks and coaches.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212008278_fd496968-b055-4b85-b176-9e7e72d62378-articleLarge.jpg', '1662030007', '1683927594'),
(893, 2, 24, 134, 'd3177cf1-f9a8-540c-b73c-d9a7f389d0c1', 'Apple, Google and Microsoft are among the technology firms looking to shift some of their manufacturing out of China.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/business/dealbook/big-tech-reconsiders-made-in-china-iphone.html', 'This month, Apple is expected to release the iPhone 14. Beyond rumors, little is known about what the crew from Cupertino, Calif., has planned for the company’s newest version of its nearly ubiquitous smartphone.', 'The New York Times', '01db-china-articleLarge.jpg', '1662033245', '1683927595'),
(894, 8, 6, 535, '86903945-bb73-5625-9eec-572a2f146a5d', 'Pavel Filatiev has been greeted as a hero by some in the West but is seen as a scourge in his native country for criticizing what he called Russia’s “terrible war.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/world/europe/russian-defector-france-book.html', 'He wrote a book describing a Russian military so ill-prepared when it invaded Ukraine that he didn’t know his unit had entered the country until he  awoke to the sound of artillery fire.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662033609', '1683927596'),
(895, 2, 0, 123, 'b90ccd28-6b5e-5a5e-8d10-82898791ba55', 'Workers at Bernheimer Architecture said they hoped to prompt changes to industrywide problems like long hours and low pay.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/business/architects-union.html', 'A union campaign dating back two years and involving workers at several New York-based architecture firms has notched its first victory.', 'The New York Times', '01economy-briefing-architects-union-articleLarge.jpg', '1662036980', '1683927597'),
(896, 4, 40, 536, 'b83c2b62-dd59-5701-b9b9-2bcee0693a8d', 'Take on Mads Andersen in a recreation of a Kvika Reykjavik Open game in Iceland, 2022. Solve for the best series of moves.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/crosswords/chess/chess-replay-you-versus-andersen.html', 'This is Chess Replay, an interactive puzzle based on a historic chess game. As a solver, you embody a famous player during a critical game in his or her career. There is one new puzzle left in this limited series, published each week on Thursdays. Play previous Chess Replay puzzles here.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662037202', '1683927599'),
(897, 4, 0, 225, 'f2620fa1-b3df-5849-96cd-58d555181022', 'What the data tells us about how people play the game.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/crosswords/wordle-starting-words-adieu.html', 'The internet is full of advice about the best first guess to use for Wordle, the New York Times game in which players have to figure out the five-letter word of the day in six tries.', 'The New York Times', 'wordle-top-articleLarge.jpg', '1662037205', '1683927600'),
(898, 21, 0, 537, 'be87b0bc-8781-56f4-bf85-aa0c591236bc', 'Finally.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/technology/twitter-edit-button.html', 'Begone, typos and grammar mistakes! Begone, fat-fingered auto corrected slip-ups and textual despair! The edit button is coming to Twitter.', 'The New York Times', '01twitter-edit-articleLarge.jpg', '1662037209', '1683927601'),
(899, 10, 0, 140, 'c348bad3-598d-5d83-b7c9-e4f7cc1817e9', 'The Golden State is one of only five regions in the world with a Mediterranean-type climate.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/us/california-climate-global-warming.html', 'The allure of California has long been its almost unbelievably good weather: predictably dry summers and pleasant, if occasionally rainy, winters. Who wouldn’t want to escape swampy heat for this temperate paradise?', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1662037211', '1683927602'),
(900, 28, 0, 0, '643ada43-d2aa-50d5-8509-0ab84bfc0fff', 'Plus: a new hotel on Kastellorizo in Greece, arboreal wallpaper and more recommendations from T Magazine.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/01/t-magazine/elton-john-peter-hujar.html', 'Though not a duet, Elton John’s latest project is a harmony of sorts. An avid collector of black-and-white photography, the singer has handpicked 50 Peter Hujar prints for an exhibition at San Francisco’s Fraenkel Gallery. Opening next week, “Peter Hujar curated by Elton John” showcases the photographer’s breadth of subjects, which range from seascapes to beefcake to pets. “I’d long wanted to invite a formidable guest curator to dig into Hujar’s work,” says Jeffrey Fraenkel, who’s represented the artist’s estate since the early 2000s. “I came up with about a half dozen names, mostly writers and visual artists, but the idea of Elton seemed unbeatable.” Besides the fact that John has acquired 15 works by Hujar since 2011, the union made emotional sense to Fraenkel. “Hujar’s work focused on the [queer] cultural scene, male erotica and other issues that overlap with Elton’s interests,” says Fraenkel. Hujar is perhaps best known for his images of members of the cultural vanguard of 1970s and ’80s New York — among them Fran Lebowitz, Susan Sontag and David Wojnarowicz, who was Hujar’s partner. John made a point of choosing some of the photographer’s less-seen portraits, including those variously depicting a young Stevie Wonder, a middle-aged Peggy Lee and the Warhol acolyte Jackie Curtis in her open casket. “The show doesn’t shy away from the tough pictures about illness or death, which are main components of Hujar’s work,” says Fraenkel. Hujar himself died of complications from AIDS in 1987. Fittingly, all proceeds from the show’s first two sales will go to the Elton John AIDS Foundation. On view from Sept. 8 through Oct. 22, fraenkelgallery.com.', 'The New York Times', '31tmag-newsletter-slide-KLGJ-articleLarge.jpg', '1662037216', '1683927603'),
(901, 10, 0, 46, '08f251e2-0e90-55a5-a1e4-bbb587212a31', 'A day of hesitation in Lee County came despite warnings that the Fort Myers and Cape Coral area could see mass flooding. Now authorities are encountering mass death.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/us/hurricane-ian-lee-county-fort-myers-delay.html', 'FORT MYERS, Fla. — As Hurricane Ian charged toward the western coast of Florida this week, the warnings from forecasters were growing more urgent. Life-threatening storm surge threatened to deluge the region from Tampa all the way to Fort Myers.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_214090836_40ca0283-5a0c-48af-849f-048c04fb212d-articleLarge.jpg', '1664582628', '1683927604'),
(902, 8, 4, 10, 'c641faeb-9984-5433-9f13-e825a8dd5d0a', 'The test came a day after the United States, Japan and South Korea conducted their first joint anti-submarine exercise in five years.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/world/asia/north-korea-ballistic-missile-test.html', 'SEOUL — North Korea launched two short-range ballistic missiles off its east coast on Saturday, a day after the United States, Japan and South Korea conducted a rare joint anti-submarine naval exercise.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664584853', '1683927605'),
(903, 30, 0, 0, 'nyt://slideshow/576deafa-579f-5ed1-b27a-dda47a8d5373', 'A mountain pass into Georgia has become a choke point for Russians fleeing the country.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/slideshow/2022/09/30/homepage/portraits-of-flight-from-russia.html', 'A mountain pass into Georgia has become a choke point for Russians fleeing the country.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664585125', '1683927605'),
(904, 10, 5, 538, '79df60db-37ad-599e-89a7-93a3e1066810', 'A U.S. District Court judge found that the sections of the state’s election law that cover absentee ballots, voter rolls and voter applications “violate neither the constitution nor the Voting Rights Act.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/us/politics/voting-lawsuit-georgia.html', 'ATLANTA — A federal judge on Friday evening ruled that Georgia’s election law does not violate voters’ constitutional rights, dealing a blow to Fair Fight Action, the voting rights group aligned with the Democratic nominee for governor, Stacey Abrams.', 'The New York Times', '30pol-lawsuit-01-1-f089-articleLarge.jpg', '1664586826', '1683927607'),
(905, 10, 0, 140, '2245d4ff-fcd7-5c38-9d6a-e99902c67e94', 'The toll could take weeks to emerge.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/us/hurricane-ian-death-toll-florida.html', 'The toll in lives that Hurricane Ian exacted in Florida may take weeks to emerge, but the first list of confirmed deaths was released on Friday night by the state Medical Examiners Commission.', 'The New York Times', '30ian-blog-florida-deaths-confirmed-1-1e6d-articleLarge.jpg', '1664587334', '1683927608'),
(906, 4, 0, 4, 'a4eaa4cf-9e6e-59b3-98b4-f89f0203bcbc', 'Natan Last drops off a poetic Saturday grid.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-10-01.html', 'SATURDAY PUZZLE — This is a buoyant, themeless challenge from Natan Last, a veteran Times constructor of 15 years. I say buoyant because there are a lot of smile-inducers, even among the more difficult entries, and a great deal of happy nostalgia that I hope will resonate with a wide spectrum of solvers.', 'The New York Times', '01wordplay-crowdsurf-1-9e16-articleLarge.jpg', '1664589603', '1683927609'),
(907, 1, 23, 539, 'af90b7a8-cd55-53af-857d-972dac2d77c1', 'A utility player for the powerhouse Yankees of the 1960s, he later became the first Black manager at minor league baseball’s highest level.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/30/sports/baseball/hector-lopez-dead.html', 'Hector Lopez, the first Black manager at the highest level of minor league baseball and one of the last living members of the early 1960s Yankees dynasty, who played in the team’s outfield alongside Mickey Mantle and Roger Maris, died on Thursday in Hudson, Fla. He was 93.', 'The New York Times', '30Hector-Lopez-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1664591000', '1683927610');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(908, 6, 0, 0, 'df09a01d-cd24-53d4-a742-fabb8a05a64e', 'Quotation of the Day for Saturday, Oct. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/todayspaper/quotation-of-the-day-unprepared-for-covid-and-monkeypox-and-the-next-outbreak-too.html', '“This is the new normal. It’s like the levees are built for the one-in-a-100-years crisis, but then the floods keep happening every three years.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664596860', '1683927610'),
(909, 7, 0, 0, 'cbd2c1e9-3a2f-5e01-93cb-db790c1ed37a', 'Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Oct. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/pageoneplus/corrections-oct-1-2022.html', 'An article on Friday about Hurricane Ian misstated the location of the storm’s landfall in Florida. It was in Lee County, not to the south of the county.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664596861', '1683927611'),
(910, 2, 0, 429, '142ac313-455f-5f2c-92c8-d7be393d2552', 'Natural gas is set to flow through a new undersea pipeline between Norway and Poland after suspected sabotage devastated the Nord Stream pipelines.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/business/baltic-pipe-nord-stream.html', 'It should be a moment of celebration for Europeans working to achieve energy independence from Russia: On Saturday, natural gas is set to start flowing through Baltic Pipe, the only new natural gas pipeline to come online in Europe in decades.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_213901563_5b24719d-a6c0-430e-9580-6d4671dec66e-articleLarge.jpg', '1664596870', '1683927612'),
(911, 8, 6, 540, '02d2dcb6-3930-50f2-b68b-fa5f107fa48a', 'A mountain pass into Georgia has become a choke point for Russians fleeing the country, many of them men who faced being drafted and sent to fight in Ukraine.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/europe/escape-from-russia.html', 'DARIALI, Georgia — They are bus drivers, programmers, photographers, bankers. They have driven for hours, bribed their way through many police checkpoints — spending a month’s wages in some cases — and then waited at the border, most of them for days, in a traffic jam that stretched for miles.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664596873', '1683927613'),
(912, 4, 0, 0, '104bb9cb-40df-575d-a7cb-58dc0259f464', 'Feeling stuck on today’s puzzle? We can help.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/crosswords/spelling-bee-forum.html', 'SATURDAY — Hi busy bees! Welcome to today’s Spelling Bee forum. There are a number of terms that appear in both this article and other online discussions of the Spelling Bee; a glossary of those terms compiled by Monicat, a Times reader, can be found below. For more Spelling Bee conversation, check out Deb Amlen’s weekly humor column, “Diary of a Spelling Bee Fanatic.”', 'The New York Times', '01bee-forum-sat-articleLarge.jpg', '1664607603', '1683927614'),
(913, 1, 30, 434, '9dbac7d6-1fdb-5f22-935a-afea56b165fb', 'The Manchester City striker is too big, too fast, too strong, too good. Manchester United was the most recent team to find that out. It won’t be the last.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/sports/soccer/erling-haaland-manchester-city-united.html', 'MANCHESTER, England — Pellegrino Matarazzo starts with the bad news. In theory, he should be in possession of what may be the most valuable single piece of knowledge in world soccer. Twice in his time as the coach of VfB Stuttgart, Matarazzo has faced a team that featured Erling Haaland. And twice, he has managed to shut him down.', 'The New York Times', '30onsoccer2-1-3a35-articleLarge.jpg', '1664613331', '1683927615'),
(914, 8, 6, 541, 'acd5100f-7255-57b7-b49c-106a2ebbcb7c', 'The head of the United Nations’ nuclear agency called on Saturday for the release of the director general of the Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant, who has been detained by Russia, saying that his detention has “a very significant impact” on the safety of ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/europe/russia-has-detained-the-zaporizhzhia-nuclear-plants-director-general-its-operator-says.html', 'The head of the United Nations’ nuclear agency called on Saturday for the release of the director general of the Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant, who has been detained by Russia, saying that his detention has “a very significant impact” on the safety of the Russian-controlled facility.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664614361', '1683927616'),
(915, 16, 29, 433, '9b6ab7e0-ba26-5bd8-8d71-72ff97e2fe8b', 'A friendship expert shares strategies for finding connection in a lonely, disconnected world.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/well/live/how-to-make-friends-adult.html', 'In July, Marisa Franco went on a solo vacation to Mexico. But by the time she flew back to Washington, D.C., 10 days later, she’d formed an entirely new group of friends.', 'The New York Times', '01How-To-Make-Friends-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614803', '1683927617'),
(916, 12, 17, 542, 'e229dab6-b2b3-5830-94bb-171874127ea7', 'In “Breathless,” David Quammen explores the predictable lead-up to the global Covid pandemic, and the frantic, belated attempts to stop it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/books/review/breathless-david-quammen.html', '“Nobody,” Donald Trump claimed in a March 2020 address, “had any idea.” He was talking about the Covid virus — which had, seemingly overnight, sparked a global pandemic. In his compelling and terrifying new book, “Breathless: The Scientific Race to Defeat a Deadly Virus,” the veteran science journalist David Quammen demonstrates just how much was known — and expected — by infectious disease scientists long before patrons of the Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market fell ill in December 2019 with a pneumonia-like virus.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_171015723_2c35a25b-8861-4563-a562-444ac2f2c3b4-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614812', '1683927617'),
(917, 9, 0, 11, 'c0275eae-07c7-51c0-bc77-566ad412bd69', 'In most cases, a co-op board has enormous latitude to approve or deny the transfer of a unit’s shares and proprietary lease.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/realestate/co-op-heirs-trust.html', 'Q: My spouse and I purchased a studio apartment in a New York City co-op for our adult son, who has special needs and is able to live independently with the support of an agency. We recently asked the co-op board to allow us to transfer the property to an irrevocable trust, so that when we die he will still have a place to live. The board denied our request. Now we are in a quandary. Our son cannot inherit property directly or he will no longer be able to receive the government benefits that support him. How do we manage this situation?', 'The New York Times', '01Ask-illo-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614814', '1683927618'),
(918, 5, 0, 543, '30c81866-7962-506a-8b68-f89cc9953966', 'The team sport, more brain than brawn, is played in bars throughout the city and culminates in the King’s Cup.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/nyregion/nyc-trivia-league-kings-cup.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', '00trivia-nyc-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614817', '1683927619'),
(919, 12, 17, 544, '54fc685f-055a-5c92-8132-6938b7290daf', 'Kiersten White, the Bram Stoker Award-winning author of “The Dark Descent of Elizabeth Frankenstein,” “Hide” and more, recommends a few of her favorite horror novels.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/books/review/young-adult-horror-novel.html', 'Life as a teenager is like walking around with your skin peeled away: Every experience is magnified against exposed nerve endings and desperate hearts. That’s why horror is the perfect genre for young readers. The form is filled with heightened emotions, pulse-pounding terrors and the exquisite agonies of firsts — and lasts, because this is horror, after all.', 'The New York Times', '00White-YA_Horror-SUB01-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614817', '1683927620'),
(920, 1, 0, 442, '71f2ca01-46fc-5e47-9511-5c56b4b22ccf', 'Farah, a four-time Olympic gold medalist, dropped out of the London Marathon because of an injury. Is his competitive career reaching the finish line?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/sports/mo-farah-london-marathon.html', 'It has been a running career of remarkable success and breadth and revelation: four Olympic gold medals won at 5,000 and 10,000 meters, a brave disclosure of being trafficked as a young boy, a knighthood conferred by Queen Elizabeth II — even a pose called the Mobot that celebrated the infectious joy with which Mo Farah of Britain prevailed.', 'The New York Times', '01farah-london1-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614817', '1683927621'),
(921, 10, 0, 194, 'a8831408-90dc-5144-9cc5-410f16ab7268', 'The worst trouble was in Lee County, where a badly damaged water system was affecting a population of nearly 760,000 people.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/florida-water-hurricane-ian.html', 'FORT MYERS, Fla. — Francine Cole’s problem was a depressingly common one this week in Florida: First, there was too much water. Now, there is not enough of it.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_214096671_28ed877c-8439-4acc-a179-9ca2e8981cb7-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614819', '1683927623'),
(922, 10, 5, 545, '34bebcd0-86de-57fa-8229-5a84004c0426', 'Tudor Dixon, the party’s nominee for governor, has ground to make up in her race against Gov. Gretchen Whitmer. She is hoping the former president can rally their party’s base.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/politics/tudor-dixon-trump-michigan.html', 'CLARKSTON, Mich. — As she runs to lead a narrowly divided swing state, Tudor Dixon is pursuing a hazardous strategy in the Michigan governor’s race: embracing Donald J. Trump, and at times emulating his no-holds-barred political style.', 'The New York Times', '01pol-dixon-1-4472-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614820', '1683927624'),
(923, 11, 0, 497, '405d2055-4d79-5f8c-b474-fcc6c76ef571', 'Matthew M. Williams has a modern vision for the brand that once dressed Audrey Hepburn. Can he make others see it?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/style/will-you-give-matthew-m-williams-a-chance.html', 'PARIS — Matthew M. Williams will, under the right conditions, be open and generous and vulnerable. He will show you his slightly messy bedroom and fix you an iced coffee that he cold-brewed himself and tell you about his sometimes tortured love life and lean back on his big Brutalist couch so that a sliver of one of the most vulnerable parts of the body (the stomach — his is taut on account of his exercise routine, which he’ll also describe if you’d like) is revealed beneath his fitted white T-shirt.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_213782526_ff68aee2-915e-456f-8dd6-a451fb3494b4-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614821', '1683927625'),
(924, 14, 0, 211, '927e5b3b-bc64-5c85-851d-f781d1162b89', 'As programs expire, such federal spending is returning to prior levels: $1 for every $6 spent on older adults.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/upshot/children-pandemic-spending.html', 'The pandemic, at first, left many American parents feeling stranded, cut off from school and other support systems. But then something momentous happened. The government invested billions of dollars in children, including cash payments to families, free school meals and money for child care centers and public schools.', 'The New York Times', '01up-kids1-1-73c9-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614821', '1683927626'),
(925, 11, 0, 546, '839ada91-9bc8-5590-aa24-a511915d5cac', 'Nineteen days and more than 150 shows later, we’ve made it to Paris.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/style/paris-fashion-week-photos.html', 'Outside the fashion shows of the past month, the crowds have been crackling with an energy that’s been missing for years. The streets of New York were ecstatic. In London, the mood was initially subdued, dampened by the death of Queen Elizabeth II, but the city made a spirited rally on its final day. Milan, on the other hand, can always be counted on to dress the part. Italians have a way of turning out for the things they are proudest of — Ferrari, Prada, Gucci. (In Milan, the fashion-obsessed accessorize almost exclusively with Italian brands.) It’s a sportier affair than other city’s fashion weeks but also a strange, beautiful mess. You can’t catch a taxi to save your life, but it’s not Italy if it’s not a little discombobulated.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_213972105_5212d896-088b-45dd-a81f-7a717fad5a80-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614824', '1683927627'),
(926, 31, 0, 547, 'c2352b04-97f9-5749-8068-4cd0fca9f636', 'Proponents say the ability to check drugs for the presence of lethal fentanyl may save lives. But critics say the strips enable drug use.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/health/fantanyl-test-strips.html', '“You smoke weed?” Eufamia Lopez asked the half-dozen young men lounging on benches in a public housing courtyard in the South Bronx.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211784082_a03c5771-2996-43b6-be69-935e22cf5416-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614825', '1683927628'),
(927, 8, 4, 50, '43c83bc3-d063-5137-80e1-93588744d7b7', 'The country’s strict coronavirus restrictions dictate the patterns of daily life, like waiting in line for frequent Covid tests and stocking up on extra groceries in case of lockdown.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/asia/china-covid-zero.html', 'SHENZHEN, China — The signs of a looming lockdown in Shenzhen, China, had been building for a while. The city had been logging a few coronavirus infections for days. Daily Covid tests were required to go pretty much anywhere. Individual buildings had been sealed off.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664614826', '1683927630'),
(928, 5, 0, 548, '079fd530-6409-5911-8c3c-e4db852a8f08', 'From geckos to chinchillas, small pets were a pandemic balm. Now shelters across the country say they are being surrendered.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/nyregion/the-great-guinea-pig-giveaway-has-begun.html', 'In recent weeks, so many people have called Bill Crain’s Hudson Valley farm rescue to surrender their ducks and chickens — many purchased at the height of the pandemic lockdown — that he finally marched into a local farm store and demanded to speak to a manager. His plea: Stop selling chicks and ducklings.', 'The New York Times', '00NY-GUINEA-PIGS-7-1-9640-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614829', '1683927631'),
(929, 5, 0, 409, '3d3c5a47-c19a-59ee-82d5-0fda6cd5930c', 'If he’s not greeting arrivals from Texas at the Port Authority Bus Terminal, Murad Awawdeh is with his family.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/nyregion/murad-awawdeh-immigration.html', 'Since August, Murad Awawdeh has been one of many New Yorkers showing up regularly at the Port Authority Bus Terminal to welcome immigrants arriving from Texas.', 'The New York Times', '01routine-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614829', '1683927632'),
(930, 2, 0, 549, '5a776b4e-c23d-5a98-a1ab-5bad0e870961', 'The internet, according to the ruling, “affected her mental health in a negative way and contributed to her death in a more than minimal way.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/business/instagram-suicide-ruling-britain.html', 'Sitting in the witness box of a small London courtroom this week, a Meta executive faced an uncomfortable question: Did her company contribute to the suicide of a 14-year-old named Molly Russell?', 'The New York Times', 'INTERNET-SUICIDE-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1664614829', '1683927633'),
(931, 8, 14, 550, 'd7a3aeef-4b4d-5d6f-86f2-e63e074cc372', 'Brazilians voting for president on Sunday will choose between two political titans in a contest seen as a major test for one of the world’s largest democracies.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/americas/bolsanoro-lula-brazil-election.html', 'Follow our live coverage of Brazil’s presidential election between Bolsonaro and Lula.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664614830', '1683927634'),
(932, 8, 4, 310, 'd25d98bc-b544-5595-b051-37eae96306a5', 'The recent flooding has plunged small farmers in sharecropping arrangements further into debt with their landlords — a cycle that has worsened as extreme weather events become increasingly common.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/asia/pakistan-flood-farmers.html', 'NAWABSHAH, Pakistan — The young woman waded into the waist-deep floodwater that covered her farmland, scouring shriveled stalks of cotton for the few surviving white blooms. Every step she took in the warm water was precarious: Her feet sank into the soft earth. Snakes glided past her. Swarms of mosquitoes whirred in her ears.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664614834', '1683927635'),
(933, 10, 0, 208, '66414696-ef10-5508-b675-9bc3c83f285f', 'The pair found themselves at the center of what Gov. Ron DeSantis of Florida on Friday called “ground zero.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/fort-myers-beach-insurance.html', 'Amy Lazzell and her husband, Robert, had made preparations thinking that Hurricane Ian, based on earlier predictions, would track north, sparing their home on Fort Myers Beach. They stocked up on drinking water, coolers of ice and nonperishable food. Their elevated house had been reinforced with hurricane-resistant impact glass. They thought they were prepared.', 'The New York Times', '30ian-blog-fortmyers-couple-01-1-6c0a-articleLarge.jpg', '1664618009', '1683927636'),
(934, 8, 7, 551, '6b401a27-4f00-581e-b5d2-40f904be3dd6', 'Alberta, later followed by Saskatchewan, has directed Mounties in the province not to participate in a buyback program for banned rifles.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/canada/alberta-revives-its-long-running-campaign-against-federal-gun-controls.html', 'A perennial theme in Canadian politics is Alberta’s government feuding with the federal government over gun laws. This week, as the federal government moves toward starting up its buyback program for “military-style assault weapons,” the dispute returned, if with a new twist.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664618402', '1683927637'),
(935, 19, 0, 552, 'e451c4a9-d13d-5b11-8114-ffb4c82a5f47', 'A psychologist and friendship expert has advice for how to make friends as an adult.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/briefing/making-friends.html', 'I was recently chatting with a colleague whose son just started ninth grade at a new school. He had a tight group of pals in elementary and middle school. Now, at 14, he was starting over, the new kid trying to make new friends.', 'The New York Times', '01-THE-MORNING-NL-articleLarge.jpg', '1664619825', '1683927638'),
(936, 2, 24, 336, 'ff4c93d9-7b7c-585e-aed4-b83137548d44', 'Upcoming Supreme Court cases could have big implications for businesses.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/business/dealbook/supreme-court-business-cases.html', 'The DealBook newsletter delves into a single topic or theme every weekend, providing reporting and analysis that offers a better understanding of an important issue in business. If you don’t already receive the daily newsletter, sign up here.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211160985_65d0636b-31e7-4c2a-ab4f-28d0a23c84ce-articleLarge.jpg', '1664625603', '1683927639'),
