(944, 8, 6, 214, 'b4db503b-90b7-5b58-9fd4-f66004f0b938', 'The act of sabotage has brought the Ukraine war closer, raising anxiety levels and threatening to undermine the Europeans’ resolve to help Ukraine fight on.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/europe/germany-pipeline-damage-fear.html', 'LUBMIN, Germany — When Heidi Moritz stands at her window and gazes over the gray expanse of the Baltic Sea stretching to the horizon, she cannot make out the giant swirling pool of methane bubbling from leaks in two sabotaged gas pipelines from Russia far offshore.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664632669', '1683927646'),
(945, 13, 0, 554, '20010e03-2cf5-5411-8271-12cf12816fc4', 'Amid the bluster and veiled threats, the president made three distinct points that form a blueprint for war and peace.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/putin-speech-nuclear-russia-ukraine.html', 'Vladimir Putin’s speech on Friday, in which he formally proclaimed the annexation of four Ukrainian regions, was many things: a distorted history lecture, a rather tedious enumeration of supposed Western sins, an airing of grievances and a vaunting of power. For all the rhetorical flourish — accusing Western elites of Satanism, for example — it was in many ways a typical address from Mr. Putin.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_214072104_f712dd33-0e73-47f7-8c7c-48c844697ed3-articleLarge.jpg', '1664634304', '1683927647'),
(946, 13, 0, 0, '7ff04a65-2189-5395-9a93-e01afaeab513', 'A court that does not keep the public’s trust cannot perform its critical role in American government.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/supreme-court-legitimacy.html', 'The Supreme Court’s authority within the American political system is both immense and fragile. Somebody has to provide the last word in interpreting the Constitution, and — this is the key — to do so in a way that is seen as fair and legitimate by the people at large.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_156585936_2fef757f-5e44-47f5-aab4-96019acdebf4-articleLarge.jpg', '1664636405', '1683927648'),
(947, 13, 0, 555, '82e6a250-0b46-5db2-8fa1-9d3c34ea5772', 'The case for a progressive levy on consumption.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/inflation-consumption-tax-rich.html', 'Inflation often begins as a mismatch of supply and demand. But if people get accustomed to prices rising, then inflation becomes about expectations. And so the task of ending it grows fuzzier: You need to use policy not just to manage the economy but also to alter psychology. The arid language of economics obscures the brutality this demands. You need to hit the economy hard enough to cow everyone who makes decisions within it.', 'The New York Times', '02klein1-articleLarge.jpg', '1664636405', '1683927649'),
(948, 13, 0, 556, '9550f285-5b99-5db4-b311-847a54f49a2d', 'And it can be yours for just four yearly payments of $50,000!', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/school-private-college.html', 'Every American high schooler knows the supposed secret to a lifetime of success: admission to an elite university. Competition for coveted spots is so fierce that while an admission victory can’t be guaranteed, it can be gamed, if you know how to play. ‌', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664636406', '1683927649'),
