(958, 10, 0, 559, '29037997-02b9-5b1a-b863-f99bbc270ed5', 'Aerial imagery taken before and after Hurricane Ian made landfall revealed the extent of the damage to parts of Florida’s Gulf Coast.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/hurricane-ian-florida-damage.html', 'In some areas of southwest Florida, Hurricane Ian left barely a trace of what once stood before. Homes along the coast were reduced to splinters, with only faint hints of their foundations visible. From above, a bridge appeared erased by a violent brushstroke of sand, water and debris. The coastline is scarred with deep gashes of sand.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664650405', '1683927658'),
(959, 13, 0, 351, '64b286dc-0aa1-5238-b546-72ace36aea31', 'A yearning for the 1980s meets a very 21st-century kind of European crisis.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/uk-liz-truss-conservatism-europe.html', 'Liz Truss, the new prime minister of Britain who may not be the prime minister for long, is by general agreement out of touch with reality.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_212591181_4b413ba7-d3be-4429-b223-cef2875ffca0-articleLarge.jpg', '1664650805', '1683927659'),
(960, 13, 0, 560, '86df2a9f-274d-5fcf-8a87-59e24b5f07d0', 'It’s time for Indigenous voices to lead the climate fight.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/opinion/climate-change-indigenous-activists.html', 'The natural resources that Indigenous peoples depend on are inextricably linked to their identities, cultures and livelihoods. Even relatively small changes in temperature or rainfall can make their lands more susceptible to rising sea levels, droughts and forest fires. As the climate crisis escalates, activists fighting to protect what remain of the world’s forests are at risk of being persecuted by their governments — and even at risk of death.', 'The New York Times', '30falquez-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1664650816', '1683927660'),
(961, 8, 6, 429, '35f928ca-456e-54f2-b04c-8c8e1a912023', 'The Italian gas provider Eni said that the Russian monopoly did not deliver the natural gas it had booked for Saturday.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/europe/gazprom-halts-gas-supplies-to-italy.html', 'Italy on Saturday became the latest European country to see its supply of natural gas from Russia severed, after the Russian monopoly Gazprom said it was unable to transport gas to Italy because of an administrative change in Austria, the Italian gas provider Eni said.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664654786', '1683927661'),
(962, 10, 0, 156, 'eda1c5aa-cdea-516a-9563-df1386d5d453', 'Caracas freed seven Americans in a trade for two nephews of Venezuela’s first lady who had been convicted on drug charges. Separately, Tehran released its longest-held American captive.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/venezuela-iran-prisoner-swap.html', 'WASHINGTON — Seven Americans who had been held captive in Venezuela for years were on their way home Saturday after President Biden agreed to grant clemency to two nephews of Cilia Flores, Venezuela’s first lady, officials said. The men had been sentenced in 2017 to 18 years in prison for conspiring to smuggle cocaine into the United States.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664658102', '1683927661'),
(963, 10, 5, 82, '3e1bb0ef-9a45-56ee-9341-1e7bedbd1a2c', 'The archives said in a letter to the House Oversight Committee that it was seeking electronic messages from unnamed White House officials sent through personal accounts.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/us/politics/trump-white-house-records-national-archives.html', 'WASHINGTON — The National Archives informed Congress on Friday that members of the Trump White House still had not turned over all presidential records and signaled there could be legal consequences for those who do not comply.', 'The New York Times', '01dc-archives-articleLarge.jpg', '1664658204', '1683927662'),
(964, 10, 0, 561, '1998e088-4a52-5336-a49b-011cde67eaba', 'At one station, in Port Charlotte, cars stretched for over a mile, while hundreds of others in need carried cans. And lawn chairs.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/us/port-charlotte-florida-gas-lines-ian.html', 'PORT CHARLOTTE, Fla. — The parking lot of a Wawa convenience store here was transformed into a sea of red gasoline cans on Saturday as hundreds of residents waited for hours in hopes of powering generators and cars after the city, about 30 miles northwest of Fort Myers, was battered by Hurricane Ian.', 'The New York Times', '01ian-blog-update-gasline-articleLarge.jpg', '1664659208', '1683927664'),
(965, 8, 6, 557, 'f0edbcb1-34e9-523b-ad5e-a30d643325c4', 'Russia’s withdrawal from the city comes one day after Moscow illegally annexed the surrounding region.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/world/europe/lyman-ukraine-russia.html', 'RIVNE, Ukraine — Russian forces retreated from the strategic eastern Ukrainian city of Lyman on Saturday, a humbling setback for President Vladimir V. Putin just one day after he illegally declared the surrounding region to be part of Russia.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664661467', '1683927665'),
(966, 4, 0, 4, '0ef70f8e-5121-5b2f-9c89-30503a3fa716', 'Et voilà! Kathy Bloomer makes a Sunday debut with panache.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-10-02.html', 'SUNDAY PUZZLE — Kathy Bloomer, who lives in Seattle, is a retired hospital pediatrician. Constructing crossword puzzles developed out of her love of solving diagramless puzzles, which involves a similar sort of logic. This is her second Times puzzle after a 2018 debut, but she has made a few attempts that didn’t quite succeed, and she jokes that  “I am working on a book I am going to call ‘Best Puzzles Rejected by The New York Times.’”', 'The New York Times', '02wordplay-lounge-1-ff77-articleLarge.jpg', '1664661605', '1683927666'),
(967, 1, 23, 166, '6a418efd-f216-5658-bdb3-fc341f90b981', 'Baltimore largely pitched around Aaron Judge, who went 0 for 2 with a pair of walks, lowering his average to .313.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/sports/baseball/aaron-judge-yankees-orioles.html', 'If a moment of history wasn’t on the line, Yankees fans would have been quite pleased with their team’s 8-0 win over the Baltimore Orioles on Saturday.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664662318', '1683927667'),
(968, 1, 9, 169, '235bf4b1-dd31-552d-af20-6cbb07b3e3f8', 'After Miami Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa sustained two head injuries in the last week, a neurologist who was part of the process that allowed him to return to the field was removed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/01/sports/football/tua-tagovailoa-doctor-fired.html', 'The N.F.L. Players Association has dismissed a neurologist who evaluated Miami Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa after Tagovailoa hit his head in a game against the Buffalo Bills last Sunday. Tagovailoa was allowed to return to that game, only to be carted off the field during a game four days later after apparently sustaining a second head injury.', 'The New York Times', '01nfl-tua-1-70ea-articleLarge.jpg', '1664665178', '1683927668'),
