(976, 18, 0, 252, 'af9c7ee1-c4cd-5aa3-ae72-657c2dd92264', 'Reporters often have little time to prepare before they set out to cover a blaze. To mitigate risk, they adhere to their own guidelines and lean on the experience of others.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/insider/preparing-to-cover-a-wildfire-before-it-starts.html', 'One morning in November 2018, Jim Wilson was on a three-hour drive to Paradise, Calif., to cover the Camp fire, which would turn out to be the deadliest fire in California history. The fire had just ripped through 17 miles of wooded foothills in 12 hours, catching Paradise by surprise. Mr. Wilson, a New York Times photographer based in Oakland, was going through a checklist in his head. He had packed his fire-resistant Nomex clothing, his helmet and an emergency fire blanket. But what about the things he couldn’t anticipate?', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_197634711_3fbd80fb-1fca-4964-808f-f071963ba405-articleLarge.jpg', '1664694010', '1683927675'),
(977, 8, 18, 304, 'f6474735-b096-5d0b-aaac-438c2ad8f9af', 'The country’s long economic decline has been one of the main forces sending Iranians into the streets over the past two weeks to demand change.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/middleeast/iran-protests-economy.html', 'When Nader, a 41-year-old construction company employee in Tehran, shops for groceries, he constantly adjusts his list as he wanders the aisles, double-checking prices and factoring them into his budget. His basket keeps shrinking as inflation surges: A year ago, he gave up red meat, then chicken.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664694014', '1683927676'),
(978, 10, 5, 154, 'fa04333c-ceb3-5b1b-9bd4-694b0ee7a00b', 'As a teenage football prodigy, Mr. Walker was pressed to join a fight for civil rights in his hometown. His decision echoes decades later.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/us/politics/herschel-walker-georgia-senate-race.html', 'WRIGHTSVILLE, Ga. — The race for a critical Senate seat was in full motion by midsummer, but there were just a few Herschel Walker campaign signs sprinkled around his hometown.', 'The New York Times', '00pol-walker-teenager02-articleLarge.jpg', '1664694024', '1683927677'),
(979, 8, 4, 428, '843e4f63-27cb-590a-ae8e-04bc222ab96f', 'These events have prompted major changes. But fatal tramplings still occur, with more than 125 killed in Indonesia on Saturday.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/asia/worst-soccer-deaths.html', 'Soccer matches around the world have seen deadly stadium disasters, sometimes set off by crowd violence and often made worse by inept police responses that result in spectators being crushed as they try to flee.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664697977', '1683927678'),
(980, 8, 6, 79, '2d576333-383c-57c8-ba83-935fe9a96f28', 'In a gathering Cold War atmosphere, American officials are gaming out responses should Russia resort to battlefield nuclear weapons.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/europe/putins-nuclear-threats-stir-growing-alarm-in-washington.html', 'WASHINGTON — For the first time since the Cuban Missile Crisis in October 1962, top Russian officials are making explicit nuclear threats and officials in Washington are gaming out scenarios should President Vladimir V. Putin decide to use a tactical nuclear weapon to make up for the failings of Russian troops in Ukraine.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664700541', '1683927678'),
(981, 12, 17, 565, 'b2db2885-2abd-5bcc-9b6e-4b399f65e019', 'In “The Rupture Tense,” Jenny Xie looks at silence surrounding the Cultural Revolution and explores its lasting impact on her own family.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/books/review/jenny-xie-rupture-tense-poems.html', 'William Butler Yeats once pictured himself as a golden bird perched on a golden bough, singing to ancient lords and ladies “of what is past, or passing, or to come.” Western civilization has long imagined the fullness of time as a three-act drama with a beginning, a middle and an end; but the end of “Sailing to Byzantium” reveals that “what is past,” or “passing,” or “to come” eludes any simple grammar of the past, present and future. Even now, I’m writing this sentence not in the simple present, but in the present continuous.', 'The New York Times', '02REDDY-POETRY-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701206', '1683927680'),
(982, 12, 17, 566, '36ca44c0-b11c-567a-bbb0-7d2ae32d831a', 'In “The Hero of This Book,” Elizabeth McCracken plays with the usual novelistic conventions.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/books/review/the-hero-of-this-book-elizabeth-mccracken.html', 'When is a memoir not a memoir? Maybe when the writer insists that it is not. “Perhaps you fear writing a memoir, reasonably,” Elizabeth McCracken writes at the beginning of her soulful, melancholy novel, “The Hero of This Book,” about a writer reminiscing about and missing her recently deceased mother.', 'The New York Times', '04Lee-SUB01-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701207', '1683927680'),
(983, 9, 0, 43, '67e2e98a-32a5-5742-8897-81a2598949a4', 'Recent residential sales in New York City and the region.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/realestate/homes-sold-975000.html', 'Each week, our survey of recent residential sales in New York City and the surrounding region focuses on homes that sold around a certain price point, allowing you to compare single-family homes, condos and co-ops in different locales.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664701208', '1683927681'),
(984, 1, 0, 567, '1d3e52fe-f19a-5f3a-8761-2b357c8dbbfe', 'Eliud Kipchoge, the world’s greatest marathoner, has an unlikely partner in his world-record-setting marathon runs: a course volunteer who is responsible for handing him nutrition.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/sports/eliud-kipchoge-bottle-claus.html', 'When Eliud Kipchoge crossed the finish line at the Berlin Marathon last weekend, breaking his own world record, Claus-Henning Schulke breathed a sigh of relief.', 'The New York Times', '02marathon-bottles-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701209', '1683927682'),
(985, 13, 0, 568, '5d004b98-c292-5641-937b-11ce237a048c', 'Parents aren’t doing enough to protect their kids from gaming addiction.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/opinion/video-game-addiction.html', 'Gov. Gavin Newsom of California has just signed legislation that would require social media companies to make sure new products won’t be harmful to minors. The focus is on Big Tech and social media apps like Facebook, Instagram and TikTok. Flying under the radar are video games even though kids in the United States spend much more time playing video games than engaging in social media, according to a recent Common Sense Media report.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664701210', '1683927683'),
(986, 13, 0, 569, '0a0dba93-51fb-5c74-b185-2cb97c6fb7f1', 'When it became clear that Vladimir Putin would require me to support his war in Ukraine, I had to leave. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/opinion/moscow-rabbi-yom-kippur.html', 'JERUSALEM — This is my first Yom Kippur in exile.', 'The New York Times', '30goldschmidt-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701211', '1683927686'),
(987, 12, 0, 104, '4232c1e7-a8f1-5c40-9b0a-095b6bb04927', 'In “Bully Market,” Jamie Fiore Higgins describes being seduced, and ultimately repelled, by nearly two high-flying decades at Goldman Sachs.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/books/bully-market-jamie-fiore-higgins.html', '“Do What You Love, the Money Will Follow” is the title of a popular, rainbow-covered self-help book published in 1988. “Bully Market,” the new memoir by Jamie Fiore Higgins, a former Goldman Sachs managing director, is clad in unambiguous blood red, suggesting rather that if you do what you hate, the money will chase you down a dark alleyway and throttle you. Maybe eventually it will release you to self-awareness, but not without first inducing temporary blindness.', 'The New York Times', '04HIGGINS-COVER-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701215', '1683927686'),
(988, 2, 2, 276, '733f3c3a-885b-51f8-9c42-e0d6703138a2', 'The true crime storytelling that has done so well for so long on television seems to have met a moment in an entirely new medium.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/business/media/dateline-podcast-true-crime.html', 'The podcast begins with the sound of a car slowing down, and then a straight-talking narrator takes over. “It was dark when the killer shut off the engine,” he says.', 'The New York Times', 'DATELINE-02-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701215', '1683927687'),
(989, 21, 0, 524, '337147c8-0105-505c-a9e3-98673f2953a2', 'Photographers and illustrators who once eagerly shared images of their work on Instagram are moving away from the site as it emphasizes video.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/technology/instagram-artists-video.html', 'SAN FRANCISCO — Deb JJ Lee built a career in illustration on Instagram, one colorful comic at a time.', 'The New York Times', '02instagram-artists-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701216', '1683927689');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(990, 10, 0, 570, '80f8c2a9-44e0-5567-bcb5-6a0a89189e98', 'Darcy Bishop for decades has cared for her two brothers, who have cerebral palsy. Hurricane Ian was her biggest test yet.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/us/sister-ian-rescue-brothers.html', 'When the water slipped in, it was just a glimmer on the floor, a sign that it was time to go.', 'The New York Times', '01naples--articleLarge.jpg', '1664701217', '1683927690'),
(991, 10, 0, 336, '0c03475e-f969-527e-bb6c-8331a6d8105d', 'The justices return to the bench on Monday to start a term that will include major cases on affirmative action, voting and discrimination against gay couples. Several will take on questions about race.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/us/conservative-supreme-court-legitimacy.html', 'Follow our live coverage of the Supreme Court hearings on affirmative action.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_179130081_c438cc15-2232-48ce-afe6-10227e5352f6-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701220', '1683927691'),
(992, 10, 0, 140, 'ce5b2ef0-5979-54eb-b018-ef53af38f891', 'The wealthy California county just north of San Francisco has one of the nation’s highest Covid-19 vaccination rates after years of being known for parents who opposed shots for childhood diseases.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/us/covid-vaccine-marin-california.html', 'SAN RAFAEL, Calif. — For more than a decade, few places in the nation were associated with anti-vaccine movements as much as Marin County, the bluff-lined peninsula of coastal redwoods and stunning views just north of San Francisco.', 'The New York Times', '00marin-county-wide-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701220', '1683927692'),
(993, 11, 0, 294, '4204f560-4fb3-5f6f-b652-58ff37502f79', 'Top looks from the Met Opera opening night, the New York City Ballet fashion gala and Annabel’s for the Amazon.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/style/fall-fashion-met-opera-nyc-ballet.html', 'The fall social season is back with a twist. The Metropolitan Opera held its opening night gala on Tuesday for “Medea,” with a notably more diverse cross-section of the city’s philanthropic, arts and social circles. The venerable affair, which raised $4.8 million, also pushed the boundaries of what constitutes black tie, with some men ascending the grand staircase in heels and dresses.', 'The New York Times', '02MOST-DRESSED-top-articleLarge.jpg', '1664701247', '1683927693'),
(994, 8, 4, 571, '484af25a-34e1-5a97-a64f-e1f191b215f1', 'One witness said most of the victims were people trapped in the stands, not those on the field. Without tear gas “there would have not been any casualties,” he said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/asia/fan-tragedy-indonesia.html', 'Joshua had gone to the stadium with his wife and 13 friends, all Arema football fans.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664701973', '1683927693'),
(995, 11, 0, 497, 'cfd28aac-e730-5519-b308-783872a9e214', 'And Bella Hadid had the best day of her life so far.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/style/bella-hadid-coperni-paris-fashion-week.html', 'PARIS — Of course it was going to go viral. The performance at the end of Coperni’s fashion show on Friday night offered many of the internet’s favorite things: a nearly-naked supermodel, 1990s fashion nostalgia and a high-ranking member of the Kardashian-Jenner family in the vicinity to bear witness.', 'The New York Times', '02PFW-WOW-BELLA-0-articleLarge.jpg', '1664702973', '1683927694'),
(996, 8, 6, 326, '9622912c-9bb7-5e88-a9e0-f85e9f772ffe', 'Violent confrontations in Leicester have prompted soul searching in an area long heralded as a success story of diversity and integration among its large Indian diaspora.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/europe/leicester-violence-uk.html', 'LEICESTER, England — In east Leicester, decorations for the Hindu celebration of Diwali hang near a sign advertising a Halal butcher. The fish shop down the road is owned by a Muslim Indian family and staffed almost exclusively by Hindus.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664703009', '1683927695'),
(997, 11, 0, 173, 'b02fadaf-b6a0-5a8c-80c1-ec1ef480f19c', 'Bring on the mayhem and magic of weirdness. Plus a bit of surrealism at Loewe, and Victoria Beckham’s Paris debut.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/style/comme-des-garcons-loewe-paris-fashion-week.html', 'PARIS — There’s nothing like a little Duran Duran in the morning.', 'The New York Times', '03PFW-LOEWE-15-articleLarge.jpg', '1664703775', '1683927696'),
(998, 27, 20, 572, 'a8b247c3-93fd-51c7-8900-279d56be2729', 'An argument at Arizona State’s multicultural center spiraled into a disaster for everyone involved. Who was to blame?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/podcasts/the-daily/the-sunday-read-the-safe-space-that-became-a-viral-nightmare.html', 'In September 2021, a group of female minority students at Arizona State University confronted two white male students who were studying in the library’s multicultural center.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664704803', '1683927697'),
(999, 2, 0, 298, '017cc644-085a-5e55-9e03-1777a6e6d785', 'Wall Street volatility continued. Tallying the costs of Hurricane Ian has just begun. And a report on the strength of the job market is coming this week.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/business/the-week-in-business-markets-britain-pound.html', 'The new British government’s announcement last week that it planned to make drastic tax cuts sent markets tumbling, the pound sinking and the Bank of England scrambling to restore some calm. The panic stemmed from fear that the tax and spending measures proposed by Britain’s recently appointed prime minister, Liz Truss, would add to soaring inflation in the country, running up against the central bank’s efforts to rein it in. Ms. Truss’s government argues that cutting taxes will stimulate investments and that the benefits will buoy the rest of the economy — but investors do not appear convinced. Their unease rippled throughout Europe and to the United States, where benchmark indexes slid. The pound hit its lowest recorded point, creeping near parity with the dollar. On Wednesday, the Bank of England stepped in, saying it will undertake large-scale purchases of British government bonds in the coming weeks to “restore orderly market conditions.” Its forceful intervention pushed the pound back up slightly and helped markets regain some of their losses.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664708404', '1683927698'),
(1000, 8, 14, 550, 'c6c0b2b3-bc1f-5225-af86-645f0af88557', 'RIO DE JANEIRO — Since Brazil’s high-stakes presidential race began last year, Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, Brazil’s former leftist president, had led the polls by a wide margin. Many analysts had even predicted he would take the presidency in the first rou', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/02/world/americas/brazilians-face-radically-opposite-choices-as-they-vote-for-their-next-president.html', 'RIO DE JANEIRO — Since Brazil’s high-stakes presidential race began last year, Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, Brazil’s former leftist president, had led the polls by a wide margin. Many analysts had even predicted he would take the presidency in the first round on Sunday, ousting President Jair Bolsonaro after just one term.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1664708439', '1683927698'),
(1001, 5, 0, 573, 'df646720-840a-559b-9019-a38e073d374d', 'The officer was seriously injured in the attack, which took place in the protective custody unit at Rikers, a union official said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/31/nyregion/rikers-inmate-stabbing-correction-officer.html', 'A city correction officer at the Rikers Island prison complex was seriously injured on Monday when a detainee stabbed him more than a dozen times in the back of the head, the correction officers’ union said in a statement.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667264488', '1683927701'),
(1002, 1, 23, 342, 'bea5feb0-69e1-53a8-a0d0-eb8028756bfd', 'The Houston Astros and the Philadelphia Phillies are tied at one game apiece. The series is scheduled to resume Tuesday, and each remaining game will be pushed back one day.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/31/sports/baseball/world-series-astros-game-3-phillies.html', 'PHILADELPHIA — Game 3 of the World Series was postponed Monday because of rain, with the Houston Astros and the Philadelphia Phillies tied at one game apiece. The series is scheduled to resume Tuesday, and in place of eliminating the built-in travel day, each game will be pushed back one day.', 'The New York Times', '31mlb-worldseries-rainout-01-1-79a1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667265060', '1683927702'),
(1003, 4, 0, 75, 'b54435b9-a1e6-53a5-909a-58142f8ce981', 'Make some connections with Bruce Haight’s puzzle.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/31/crosswords/daily-puzzle-2022-11-01.html', 'TUESDAY PUZZLE — Rumor has it that this is the 61st puzzle constructed by Bruce Haight for The Times. That’s a lot of puzzles!', 'The New York Times', '01wordplay-milky-way-articleLarge.jpg', '1667268004', '1683927703'),
(1004, 10, 0, 37, 'e860a43e-23b4-53d5-b1b7-9c87012e6e58', 'The long-unsolved kidnapping and killing of Jonelle Matthews haunted the community of Greeley, about 50 miles north of Denver.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/31/us/steven-pankey-murder-kidnapping-id.html', 'A Colorado jury on Monday convicted an Idaho man of murder and kidnapping in the 1984 disappearance and death of a 12-year-old girl who was killed days before Christmas, a case that went unsolved for decades and haunted the tight-knit community of Greeley, Colo., where she lived.', 'The New York Times', '31xp-steve-pankey-2-articleLarge.jpg', '1667269728', '1683927704'),
(1005, 10, 5, 0, 'bb3260bb-b2a2-5e3d-96be-4a9526b1667f', 'David DePape, who is accused of breaking into the San Francisco home of Speaker Nancy Pelosi, was charged with attempting to kidnap Ms. Pelosi and with assaulting a relative of a federal official.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000008610372/pelosi-attack-suspect-charges.html', 'David DePape, who is accused of breaking into the San Francisco home of Speaker Nancy Pelosi, was charged with attempting to kidnap Ms. Pelosi and with assaulting a relative of a federal official.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667270622', '1683927705'),
(1006, 10, 5, 82, '55dccfd3-c8bb-5cf2-8fb4-8919b319fe17', 'The decision does not necessarily mean the committee will get the information it is seeking.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/10/31/us/politics/meadows-jan-6-committee-lawsuit.html', 'WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Monday dismissed a lawsuit by Mark Meadows, the final chief of staff for President Donald J. Trump, that sought to block two subpoenas from the House committee investigating the Jan. 6 attack, including one to Verizon for Mr. Meadows’s phone and text data.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667271418', '1683927705'),
(1007, 2, 0, 68, '3020b888-4589-5281-ae87-d8948c281b36', 'Countries across the continent have taken extraordinary steps to decrease energy use and ramp up supply, moving swiftly away from their longtime primary provider, Russia.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/europe-energy-crisis.html', 'A flotilla of tankers carrying liquefied natural gas have been parked in a maritime traffic jam off the coast of Spain in recent days, waiting to unload their precious cargo for Europe’s power grid. In Finland, where sweltering sauna baths are a national pastime, the government is urging friends and families to take saunas together to save energy.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215611839_bd7ee169-988a-49f9-92f9-006c1e0cf06f-articleLarge.jpg', '1667275212', '1683927706'),
(1008, 7, 0, 0, '2b9aebcb-57e6-514b-8808-b286e1a04f4d', 'Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, Nov. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/pageoneplus/corrections-nov-1-2022.html', 'An article on Saturday about Giorgia Meloni, Italy’s new prime minister, and what her ascent has meant to her far-right followers misstated when the Italian Social Movement was first formed. It was 1946, not 1948.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667277726', '1683927707'),
(1009, 13, 0, 574, '82547685-9bff-5b80-884c-833b2e6c37f4', 'Everyone’s eyes are on Benjamin Netanyahu as Israelis head back to the polls. It’s the Supreme Court they should be most worried about.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/in-israels-election-the-judiciary-is-on-trial.html', 'TEL AVIV — Israel’s election this week is being touted as a new referendum on an old leader — former Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who is standing trial on corruption charges and is attempting yet another political comeback. But the country faces a much deeper, more worrisome concern: Israel’s judicial branch is on trial and with it Israel’s best hope for democracy.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215490507_174f2e77-7606-41a9-a23a-26571b9fe884-articleLarge.jpg', '1667278806', '1683927708'),
(1010, 13, 0, 575, '7b8bead5-761d-5dea-84c3-6bec858a1ba2', 'The country has a profound story to tell.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/ukraine-war-national-identity.html', 'How did people imagine Ukraine before Feb. 24, 2022? If pressed, some might have conjured mail-order brides and shaven-head gangsters roaming one big post-Soviet Chernobyl. But most probably didn’t think even that; instead, they didn’t imagine Ukraine at all. The country popped up on most people’s radar only in connection to Western political scandals and Russian war making. Few Westerners visited it, and those who did might have concluded — as one Western journalist confessed to me recently — that “Ukraine was just like Russia but without all the crap.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_211876983_a3a9dee4-e4b2-4ab8-ac72-9660d5c01573-articleLarge.jpg', '1667278816', '1683927709'),
(1011, 8, 6, 535, 'cb1a5b86-75d3-5662-8eb9-1bed11572c50', 'Three more ships carrying grain departed from Ukraine’s Black Sea ports on Tuesday, a day after President Vladimir V. Putin signaled that Russia would no longer ensure the safety of the cargo vessels, a message that underscored the perils facing a watersh', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/europe/putin-reaffirms-russias-suspension-of-grain-deal-even-as-grain-ships-leave-ukrainian-ports.html', 'Three more ships carrying grain departed from Ukraine’s Black Sea ports on Tuesday, a day after President Vladimir V. Putin signaled that Russia would no longer ensure the safety of the cargo vessels, a message that underscored the perils facing a watershed agreement meant to help alleviate the global food crisis.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667279917', '1683927710'),
(1012, 10, 0, 170, '27c5934e-c430-5888-861d-00ac154b7865', 'The victims were attending a vigil near the city’s West Side when the shooting occurred, the police said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/chicago-shooting-halloween.html', 'Fourteen people, including a 3-year-old boy and two other children, were wounded in a drive-by shooting in Chicago on Monday night, the police said.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215816043_f574b575-2564-479b-b8a0-075fd2c14e04-articleLarge.jpg', '1667280088', '1683927711'),
(1013, 19, 0, 340, '0917f785-0608-55f1-b8f6-8c9e4e1e644a', 'Skyrocketing inflation in Europe.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/briefing/inflation-brazil-russia.html', 'Consumer prices in the 19 countries that use the euro as their currency rose at a record annual rate of 10.7 percent in October, the European Commission reported yesterday.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667280183', '1683927712'),
(1014, 20, 0, 0, 'a56e48e0-7816-5ee2-b5ad-b05693dadebd', 'This word has appeared in 49 articles on NYTimes.com in the past year. Can you use it in a sentence?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/learning/word-of-the-day-omniscient.html', 'The word omniscient has appeared in 49 articles on NYTimes.com in the past year, including on May 21 in “Who’s Playing Dungeons & Dragons These Days? The Usual Fans, and Then Some” by Amelia Diamond:', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667282402', '1683927712'),
(1015, 5, 0, 92, '40ad765a-0e76-5bd6-a8ee-0c660058904e', 'The “gemmail” — a glass mosaic — will go on the auction block with an estimate of at least $1 million.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/nyregion/picasso-notre-dame-gemmail.html', 'Good morning. It’s Tuesday. We’ll look at an unusual Picasso — it’s an all-glass image of the Notre-Dame cathedral. And with Election Day a week away, we’ll look at two races, including one for a House seat the Democrats have long dreamed of flipping.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667284570', '1683927713'),
(1016, 20, 0, 0, 'ba3cf974-038f-597c-bf05-fc078a5f10ed', 'Tell us a story, real or made up, that is inspired by this image.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/learning/red-poster.html', 'Use your imagination to write the opening of a short story or poem inspired by this illustration — or tell us about a memory from your own life that this image makes you think of.', 'The New York Times', '24Newworld-articleLarge.jpg', '1667286002', '1683927714'),
(1017, 4, 0, 0, '03712169-aed8-5021-a8dc-bfcbf182773c', 'Feeling stuck on today’s puzzle? We can help.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/crosswords/spelling-bee-forum.html', 'TUESDAY — Hi busy bees! Welcome to today’s Spelling Bee forum. There are a number of terms that appear in both this article and other online discussions of the Spelling Bee; a glossary of those terms compiled by Monicat, a Times reader, can be found below. For more Spelling Bee conversation, check out Deb Amlen’s weekly humor column, “Diary of a Spelling Bee Fanatic.”', 'The New York Times', '01bee-forum-tue-articleLarge.jpg', '1667286003', '1683927716'),
(1019, 15, 0, 576, '4330557f-6fe1-5238-ab1e-8c31d23f45f0', 'A dwindling group of professionals is tasked with navigating the often fraught passage from life to death.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/science/embalming-funerals-death.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', '31SCI-EMBALMING-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1667286018', '1683927718'),
(1020, 8, 18, 577, '19f90f78-fed8-56a0-986c-2ffd37ff0793', 'As Israelis vote on Tuesday in their fifth parliamentary election in less than four years, former Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is hoping to return to power, but polls are predicting another deadlock.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/middleeast/heres-whats-at-stake-in-the-election.html', 'As Israelis vote on Tuesday in their fifth parliamentary election in less than four years, former Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is hoping to return to power, but polls are predicting another deadlock.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667286082', '1683927719'),
(1021, 8, 18, 577, '6acee175-99ba-507a-973e-9bd0b7919e4b', 'A divided electorate and shifting alliances make for a delicate balance in the country’s voting outcomes and lawmakers’ ability to hold diverse blocs together.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/middleeast/israel-why-many-elections.html', 'Israel keeps returning to the polls primarily because voters remain evenly split on the question of whether Benjamin Netanyahu, the longest-serving Israeli prime minister, is fit to run the country while standing trial on corruption charges.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667286083', '1683927719'),
(1022, 3, 3, 93, '1be3a973-3630-525a-a465-67c8f4681a6e', 'Noah kicked off a week of taping in Atlanta on Monday ahead of next week’s big elections.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/television/trevor-noah-daily-show-georgia.html', 'Welcome to Best of Late Night, a rundown of the previous night’s highlights that lets you sleep — and lets us get paid to watch comedy. Here are the 50 best movies on Netflix right now.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667286635', '1683927720'),
(1023, 1, 41, 578, '9301ed71-fc37-569d-9da6-e72b2abeecf3', 'Billion-dollar investment funds and N.F.L. ownership groups are among those angling for a foothold in the Indian Premier League. The returns, not the sport, are the draw.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/sports/cricket/indian-cricket-us-investors.html', 'In the decade since he founded the private investment firm RedBird Capital Partners, Gerry Cardinale has acquired stakes in sports properties as varied as Fenway Sports Group, the Yankees’ YES Network and the Italian soccer team A.C. Milan. One of his partners at RedBird, Alec Scheiner, previously worked as a vice president of the N.F.L.’s Dallas Cowboys, and later ran the Cleveland Browns.', 'The New York Times', '00cricket-money1-1-9626-articleLarge.jpg', '1667291583', '1683927721'),
(1024, 13, 0, 579, 'c10df7fb-b8af-5460-94f5-6c8dddfdcc9e', 'In Northern California, the Karuk people celebrate a girl’s first period in a coming-of-age ceremony.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/video/opinion/100000008461725/long-line-of-ladies.html', 'In Northern California, the Karuk people celebrate a girl’s first period in a coming-of-age ceremony.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667292904', '1683927722'),
(1025, 8, 6, 580, 'e39e53c7-9125-5532-aa2d-1cc1156a9d17', 'With no clear coalition as of Tuesday night, the stage is set for a negotiation to form what analysts say will likely be a centrist government.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/europe/denmark-election.html', 'COPENHAGEN — Denmark on Tuesday voted in a snap general election, precipitated by anger over a government-mandated mink cull during the pandemic that led to accusations that top officials, including the prime minister, misled the public.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293154', '1683927723'),
(1026, 20, 0, 99, '3dfb2dd5-846a-58b5-a560-c3db67123a30', 'What routines, habits or practices do you do to stay grounded, happy and healthy?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/learning/what-are-the-little-rituals-that-keep-you-going.html', 'What are the little things you do regularly that make you feel good, whether physically or mentally or both?', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293206', '1683927724'),
(1027, 12, 17, 581, '52dbdf68-af29-5b7b-b341-cba48a566535', 'Jacqueline Bublitz’s debut, “Before You Knew My Name,” follows the parallel tracks of two women in New York City — one vital and vibrant, the other not so much.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/before-you-knew-my-name-jacqueline-bublitz.html', 'Should men have a curfew? A British politician, Baroness Jenny Jones, proposed one for men after the London police advised women not to go out alone at night, in the wake of a high-profile killing. Baroness Jones intended the curfew as a provocative thought experiment: Imagine if cities belonged only to women after dark. After reading “Before You Knew My Name,” though, a curfew for men might seem downright reasonable.', 'The New York Times', '01Berry-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293207', '1683927725'),
(1028, 16, 0, 582, '63cbaffa-3397-5c88-9122-2aac1d112d3f', 'In a new book, a sleep scientist offers tips for better rest — without reaching for a pill.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/well/better-sleep-tips.html', 'A good night’s sleep can make us more empathetic, more creative, better parents and better partners, according to Aric Prather, a psychologist at the University of California, San Francisco who treats insomnia and is the author of the new book “The Sleep Prescription.” Sleep can help us manage stress; it can make us competent and capable and better able to take on the day. But Dr. Prather says we too often view sleep as an afterthought — until we find ourselves frozen in the middle of the night, our thoughts racing, fumbling for rest or relief.', 'The New York Times', '31Well-SleepRX-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293207', '1683927726'),
(1029, 24, 0, 583, 'ed06cab8-9c9b-5aa2-844d-ca7e976b3aa8', 'Revithia me spanaki is a connection to his legacy that I’m passing on to my son.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/magazine/revithia-me-spanaki.html', 'Not long before he died, my father, a doctor, announced that he would write a cookbook of Greek food. The news came as a shock. In England, where he’d spent most of his life, he had shown very little interest in cooking. In Greece, where he was born and where he returned to live much later, he was now fanatical about it. Research began. Tavernas were scouted and recipes recorded. One summer when I visited him, we went together to a restaurant on the island of Paros. There he had discovered fava, a pea or bean purée, yellow and buttery, that he thought was the best he’d ever had. He felt it deserving of a page in his book. I watched him photograph the dish from above, his shirt damp with midafternoon sweat, the cotton pulled tight against his belly, the fava set against a plain white tablecloth.', 'The New York Times', '06mag-LOR-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293207', '1683927727'),
(1030, 12, 17, 584, '48eb7485-ccb9-504e-bf7e-606872479354', 'Louise Kennedy’s debut novel, “Trespasses,” considers the relationship of a Catholic woman and a Protestant man.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/trespasses-louise-kennedy.html', 'Recently, The New York Times published a photograph of children in Ukraine playing on a playground, surrounded by bombed-out buildings. I happened to see it the same week I was reading “Trespasses,” the brilliant, beautiful, heartbreaking debut novel by Louise Kennedy. I think the two will be forever linked in my mind.', 'The New York Times', '08SULLIVAN-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293208', '1683927728'),
(1031, 14, 0, 585, '13acb64c-613f-518b-b5e6-2eee9988541c', 'A big challenge for some pollsters, nonresponse bias, appears to be back.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/upshot/polling-2022-midterms.html', 'In the aftermath of the 2020 election, most pollsters concluded that the polls probably underestimated Donald J. Trump because of something called nonresponse bias. In short, Mr. Trump’s supporters were less likely to respond to surveys than Joe Biden’s supporters, even among people who had the same demographic characteristics.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293209', '1683927729'),
(1032, 10, 0, 586, '82b2c02e-5bb1-5145-a135-002f6bc9f6c3', 'Tell us how a new law in New York City that requires employers to include salaries on job posts is affecting you.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/did-your-company-just-add-salary-information-to-job-posts.html', 'Starting Tuesday, nearly all employers in New York City are required to include a salary range in their job posts, whether they advertise jobs on an online job board, in a job fair flier or on an internal bulletin board.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293209', '1683927729'),
(1033, 12, 17, 587, 'b61010d0-0d2e-5bff-9534-73ba8faacca5', 'The posthumous publication of a new novel, six years after Dunn’s death, is a chance to celebrate the bawdy originality of the author of the cult hit “Geek Love.”', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/katherine-dunn-toad-geek-love.html', 'Katherine Dunn lived the hard-core life of a character in a Katherine Dunn novel. She was born in 1945 in Garden City, Kan., one of five siblings. Her father abandoned the family when she was a toddler. Her mother, an artist, remarried a mechanic, and the couple worked as migratory fruit pickers, drifting west until they eventually settled near Portland, Ore. As a teenager, too broke to buy drugs, Dunn later joked, she would sometimes try to catch bugs in order to get high. Dunn’s mother beat her; once, she threw a screwdriver that punctured Dunn’s calf, leaving a lifelong scar. When Dunn was 17, she left home for good. After a brief stint in jail for attempting to pass a bad check, she enrolled in Reed College. She fell in love, dropped out of Reed and traveled around the world before returning to Portland to raise her son, Eli. She cobbled together jobs, wrapping candy on assembly lines and posing nude for life-drawing classes. She also waited tables and bartended at dive bars where she dodged biker-gang fights. A patron once tried to slit her throat.', 'The New York Times', '00Raphel-DUNN-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293209', '1683927731'),
(1034, 13, 0, 588, 'd30be3df-8aea-5365-aff4-f9b128e18ca3', 'How “stereotype promise” shapes Asian Americans’ educations.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/affirmative-action-asian-american-bias.html', 'Affirmative action is on trial again. This time, opponents of race-conscious college admission practices are claiming that Asian Americans are hurt by it. The plaintiffs in Students for Fair Admissions Inc. v. President & Fellows of Harvard College, which presented oral arguments before the Supreme Court on Monday, allege that Harvard holds Asian American applicants to higher academic standards and rates them lower than other students on personal characteristics, such as fit, courage and likability. The proposed solution is to abandon race as a factor in admissions decisions.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293209', '1683927731'),
(1035, 13, 0, 579, '2fb3e012-63dd-5535-9485-0fb9e14b84d8', 'In “Long Line of Ladies,” the Karuk people celebrate a girl’s first period in a coming-of-age ceremony.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/karuk-indigenous-celebration-menstruation-ceremony.html', 'When I first got my period, I shied away from having my Kinaaldá, the Navajo coming-of-age ceremony for girls. While my community encouraged me to have my ceremony, I felt conflicted. On the one hand, my family was working to help young people learn and embrace traditional knowledge; on the other, I struggled to feel proud after years of seeing my culture misrepresented or dismissed by the Western world. If I could go back and talk to my 14-year-old self, I would tell her that the choice wasn’t hers alone — generations of people had been fighting to bring back Native traditions — and participating in this ceremony could help create healing for our people.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293210', '1683927732'),
(1036, 16, 29, 589, 'ccec0255-169f-587a-b789-789e6278ad0e', 'It’s a hotly debated question in dentistry.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/well/live/brushing-teeth-breakfast.html', 'Q: Is it better to brush my teeth before or after breakfast? Some dentists say it’s better to brush before, some say after — which one is it?', 'The New York Times', '25ASKWELL-BrushBreakfast2-1-24f0-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293210', '1683927733'),
(1037, 13, 0, 590, '307badb8-b2b7-5616-8867-c12fcd4274cd', 'Americans don’t want to share a living room with one another. We prefer to live and be entertained in ideological encampments.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/decline-of-late-night-liberal-television.html', 'Trevor Noah recently surprised fans (and, according to some accounts, also Comedy Central management) when he announced plans to leave “The Daily Show.” His departure is one of many notable personnel changes in late-night television: James Corden will leave “The Late Late Show” next year, TBS canceled “Full Frontal With Samantha Bee,” and Desus and Mero broke up with each other and their hugely successful Showtime late-night show beloved by a diverse viewership of millennials.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293212', '1683927734'),
(1038, 12, 17, 591, '4789f516-723e-5365-9b65-e58e094113de', '“Art Is Life” collects the art critic’s essays, reviews, interviews and more from the past two decades.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/jerry-saltz-art-is-life.html', 'Outsiders might bash the art world for being a glitzy form of grift, a multibillion-dollar shell game or giant inside joke designed to make the uninitiated feel like rubes; but Jerry Saltz, the senior art critic for New York magazine, maintains a rosier view of the ecosystem to which he belongs. Bad actors notwithstanding, the real art world is “a great broken beautiful family of misfits,” according to one of the essays that earned him a Pulitzer Prize in 2018. “I refuse to believe that this spirit has left the art world, even though I recognize that this exquisite internal essence can be buried under loads of external bull——.” This devotional verve suffuses the articles, reviews, obits and interviews collected in “Art Is Life: Icons & Iconoclasts, Visionaries & Vigilantes, & Flashes of Hope in the Night.” Published between 1999 and 2021, they collectively form a love letter to the art that, for Saltz, makes all the wheeling and dealing worth putting up with.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_169609851_472fcb8f-794f-4fb5-8b40-265986db076d-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293212', '1683927735'),
(1039, 12, 17, 592, '95bd45d6-9416-5d4d-97a2-015ebb5ebab0', 'In her new novel, “Saha,” Cho Nam-Joo follows a group of outcasts to examine the strict enforcement of social hierarchies.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/saha-cho-nam-joo.html', 'In a world powered by hierarchies, what does it mean to not be “anyone or anything deserving of a category”? This is the question explored in “Saha,” the newest book by the Korean novelist Cho Nam-Joo.', 'The New York Times', '01MICHEL-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293212', '1683927736'),
(1040, 24, 0, 114, 'a348f833-6e8e-58ef-a944-2e92f2270613', 'The Times’s Ethicist columnist on whether people have a say in how their donations are used after a crisis.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/magazine/donation-ethics.html', 'A young couple I know from our church were displaced from their apartment by a fire. All their furnishings and effects had to be replaced, and it was expensive for them to move pending the payment of their insurance benefit. ', 'The New York Times', '06Mag-Ethicist-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293214', '1683927737'),
(1041, 12, 17, 593, '3c4efbac-7a6c-552c-b477-1c72bf5cdf4c', 'In Simon Parkin’s riveting account, a shameful chapter in British history is also a testament to creativity and hope.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/island-of-extraordinary-captives-simon-parkin.html', 'A German invasion of mainland Britain never felt closer than during that period between 1940 and 1945, when thousands of Nazi soldiers occupied the Channel Islands, holding captive the British citizens of Guernsey, Jersey and Sark in isolating and punitive conditions. But hundreds of miles farther north in the cold, gray waters of the Irish Sea, halfway between Cumbria and the coast of Northern Ireland, lies an island on which these authoritarian circumstances occurred in reverse.', 'The New York Times', '10Nicolson-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293216', '1683927738'),
(1042, 12, 17, 594, 'e352e6f7-3f61-519c-b322-adcf2314bae2', 'RJ Young’s “Requiem for the Massacre” is more coming-of-age story than reckoning.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/tulsa-massacre-rj-young.html', 'It’s not news that the United States has a long history of enslaving, torturing and killing Black people. A particular method, for lack of a better word, thrived in the late 19th and early 20th centuries — targeted efforts by white mobs to violently destroy Black communities. In 1919, there were so many attacks between May and August alone that the writer James Weldon Johnson termed it “The Red Summer.” In 1923, the community of Rosewood, Fla., was razed; and the list goes on, with far too many such tragedies to cite here. But since 2019’s HBO hit “Watchmen,” only one of these massacres has become a cultural shorthand: the Tulsa massacre of 1921, in which thousands of white people stormed the city’s Greenwood district and burned it to the ground, killing an estimated 300 African Americans and leaving thousands homeless. Say “Tulsa” now and people listen. But what happens when a massacre becomes a meme?', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_188465166_70b8e8ac-5d7b-437a-8f3a-5021effcc8dc-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293217', '1683927739'),
(1043, 5, 0, 595, '7aa7db49-4742-5da6-b4f7-4d8257f1b891', 'Senator Chuck Schumer, heavily favored to defeat his Republican challenger, Joseph Pinion, argued in a debate as much for his party as for his re-election.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/nyregion/chuck-schumer-opponent-pinion.html', 'For an hour on Sunday night, Senator Chuck Schumer endured insult after insult. He was called a liar and a failure. He was blamed for inflation, the decline of the shipbuilding industry, and death threats to Supreme Court justices. He was referred to as a modern-day Goliath, a “blind biblical giant,” a surprising description of a senator famed for both his spectacles and his slouch.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215755809_2af69170-0bad-4896-939c-c1ba05abc713-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293219', '1683927740'),
(1044, 12, 17, 596, '85f00779-5a9f-570b-aff3-a6d05d9e4ab3', '“Case Study,” by Graeme Macrae Burnet, is a novel of found documents detailing troubled lives and shifting identities.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/graeme-macrae-burnet-case-study.html', 'To get to Primrose Hill from central London, you take the Tube to Chalk Farm Station, exit to your right toward a cafe and an off-license, and climb a path to an overpass above train tracks. The path is called, rather unassumingly, Bridge Approach, and a five-minute walk leads to Primrose Hill. I happened to live in these parts for three years, and I crossed the overpass twice a day most days. Just to the south is the Pembroke Castle pub, where Liam Gallagher of Oasis was once arrested, in 1998. Another neighborhood tippler, Kingsley Amis, favored the Queen’s at the corner of St. George’s Terrace, according to his biographer Zachary Leader, who printed his monthly tab. From my balcony I could see the phone box where Sylvia Plath would desperately call Ted Hughes at his lover’s flat in her last days. It is a quiet neighborhood, but one dense with intrigue and peopled by famous, messy and tortured artistic personages.', 'The New York Times', '01burnet-review-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293220', '1683927741'),
(1045, 13, 0, 597, '0c3de279-3ce7-5b9b-babc-884f793b8813', 'How a killer’s death sentence can bring new pain to families of victims. ', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/parkland-death-penalty.html', 'This week, Nikolas Cruz, who killed 17 people in the 2018 shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Fla., will be formally sentenced to life in prison without the possibility of parole, and the families of those who were killed or injured will again have a chance to speak about the irreparable harm done to them.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215771352_278be007-5f3f-44d9-a604-2532cd562f3b-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293222', '1683927742'),
(1046, 10, 5, 598, '4d41addc-bb67-54b4-8d9c-69b3bbd56c5d', 'The ad campaigns, totaling over $6.5 million, talk about “anti-white bigotry” and transgender care for children.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/politics/radio-ads-trump-allies.html', 'One of the biggest radio ad blitzes in the final stretch of the midterm elections is a provocative package of advertisements aimed at deepening cultural divides over transgender care for children and racial tensions.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293224', '1683927743'),
(1047, 13, 0, 0, '4d89f4bc-e180-59b3-a8f3-0ba8ba04b6d6', 'The political scientist Pippa Norris explains how a ‘silent revolution in values’ is fueling the global rise of the right.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/opinion/ezra-klein-podcast-pippa-norris.html', 'As we approach the 2022 midterms, the outlook for American democracy doesn’t appear promising. An increasingly Trumpist, anti-democratic Republican Party is poised to take over at least one chamber of Congress. And the Democratic Party, facing an inflationary economy and with an unpopular president in office, looks helpless to stop them.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293226', '1683927744'),
(1048, 2, 0, 486, '55cf64a0-66da-527e-bc90-9c719eb4847d', 'Some companies and restaurants have continued to raise prices on consumers even after their own inflation-related costs have been covered.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/food-prices-profits.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', '29Food-Prices-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293227', '1683927745'),
(1049, 22, 0, 599, 'e1d2f77a-270a-5646-a4d4-f619a8b7df12', 'The restaurant hotshots have New York in their DNA and several opulent new places in Florida. But their sights are set on cities around the world.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/dining/major-food-group-carbone-global.html', 'MIAMI — Here’s something you don’t often see at a New York restaurant opening: showgirls. The old-school kind, in fishnets and stilettos, corsets and feathered headpieces. At the Oct. 18 opening party for Contessa, in the Design District, four of them squeezed through the crowd while another hung by her ankles from a high perch, pouring Prosecco from 10 feet up as guests lifted glasses to her.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215315118_866b1fdd-244f-4097-85f4-95f8b6e83f7b-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293228', '1683927746'),
(1050, 21, 0, 363, '65b5bb58-8964-5732-ae0c-36df24af6cf8', 'The right-wing social network faces two federal investigations and an uncertain financial future. But it has still managed to outpace its rivals.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/technology/truth-social-conservative-social-app.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_213536937_9d07df72-2110-4297-9356-621eb9749e6c-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293229', '1683927747'),
(1051, 10, 0, 600, '9265a7f8-34a2-5816-a22a-2a07add98b1d', 'Students missed a lot of high school instruction. Now many are behind, especially in math, and getting that degree could be harder.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/covid-college-students.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215429313_fef3387b-ffb5-4fa9-be36-234240296572-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293229', '1683927748'),
(1052, 11, 0, 173, '91d0fa83-9c40-54bf-a553-a773b8b7bfe5', 'Rampant speculation has entered the market.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/style/adidas-yeezy-nike-sneaker-market.html', 'To hear more audio stories from publications like The New York Times, download Audm for iPhone or Android.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215461428_34cbc198-b3d9-4094-bb91-6766cde2e866-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293230', '1683927750'),
(1053, 12, 17, 22, '0b4b030b-c5e9-5103-af25-843a6c892602', '“Dr. No,” which borrows its name from an early James Bond story, features a math professor who’s recruited by a supervillain.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/books/review/in-a-new-novel-percival-everett-riffs-gleefully-on-007.html', 'Was there superior technology in the 1960s for removing the smell of cigarettes from clothing or did James Bond’s tuxedo permanently reek? In rewatching “Dr. No,” the first Bond film, I couldn’t reconcile all that photogenic smoke with my strong intuition that Sean Connery always smelled fantastic.', 'The New York Times', '01everett-cover-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293231', '1683927750'),
(1054, 28, 0, 601, '7fe03b17-72af-54bb-a91c-8627ae40cb48', 'For centuries, the owners of an ancestral estate have sought to secure within its walls the worlds they lost.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/t-magazine/chateau-montalembert-france-home-design.html', 'THE ACHE OF exile has animated many great works of art. Pablo Neruda published “Canto General,” his lacerating book of poems about living underground, in the wake of his 1948 expulsion from the Chilean Senate; Oscar Wilde produced the crystalline prose of “De Profundis” while banished to England’s Reading Gaol prison for sodomy. Being forced to flee from Germany to Paris to New York as the Nazis rose to power was the catalyst for the painter George Grosz’s 1944 masterpiece, “Cain, or Hitler in Hell.”', 'The New York Times', '31tmag-chateau-slide-BWKR-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293231', '1683927752'),
(1055, 25, 0, 602, '1db501ee-fa87-5408-b056-51813549dc7e', 'With no billboards or gas stations, a fall drive along this winding, verdant All-American Road, is a head-clearing journey, offering encounters with history, nature, music and more.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/travel/natchez-park-traceway-driving.html', 'As I pulled away from the Loveless Cafe, near the northern end of the Natchez Trace Parkway, the rain clouds that had been brewing southwest of Nashville unleashed a shower over what, in the distance, looked to be tiny Bon Aqua, Tenn., where I once lived. There was a welcome touch of fall in the air, so I was willing to gamble on a little rain.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215092866_249b879a-e478-4372-8223-ef9142ff030f-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293232', '1683927753'),
(1056, 10, 0, 204, 'ee413321-d4c4-5d27-8b1b-fd5c52a8d5f5', 'Prosecutors are seeking testimony from three people who took part in the pressure campaign against the worker, Ruby Freeman, after the 2020 election.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/trump-georgia-election-ruby-freeman.html', 'ATLANTA — One is a 69-year-old Lutheran pastor from Illinois. Another is a celebrity stylist who once described herself as a publicist for Kanye West. A third is a former mixed martial-arts fighter and self-described “polo addict” who once led a group called “Black Voices for Trump.”', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_208907463_e192e6a2-9e7b-41c4-8153-4ebb42f1248c-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293232', '1683927754'),
(1057, 15, 0, 603, 'e2eae979-a102-5bf7-8bde-f458a477b1d9', 'Water competition, termites and poisons have all been credited with causing the formations in an African desert’s vegetation, but researchers say a new study discounts one of them.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/science/fairy-circles-cause-water-termites.html', 'The strange, barren spots pepper the vast Namib Desert, which stretches from southern Angola to northern South Africa. They are known as “fairy circles,” and for a natural phenomenon with such a whimsical name, scientific debates over their origins have been heated.', 'The New York Times', '01tb-fairycircles-car-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293233', '1683927755'),
(1058, 24, 0, 604, 'e9864193-3311-561b-975f-3e50ee5087ba', 'With the G.O.P. in control of a majority of statehouses, Democrats are fighting for seats in battleground states. Is it too late?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/magazine/wisconsin-democrats.html', 'Wisconsin’s 51st Assembly District lies in the southwest part of the state — part of the larger Driftless Area, so named because it was mysteriously spared the drift of the glaciers that flattened much of the Midwest during the last ice age. The resulting landscape is forested and hilly, arable but not easy to farm on an industrial scale. As a result, many of the farms in this region are still small and independently owned, which explains in part why the area is less reliably Republican than many of the state’s other rural regions. Presidential races in the 51st tend to move back and forth between the two parties. ', 'The New York Times', '06mag-Wisconsin-images-articleLarge.jpg', '1667293233', '1683927756'),
(1059, 9, 0, 0, 'nyt://slideshow/033682c0-edb7-5dc7-ab21-d1643fbae045', 'An interior designer wanted to create a home where “everything gets put away at night” — and she succeeded. Sort of.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/slideshow/2022/11/01/realestate/southern-california-minimalism-with-old-world-charm.html', 'An interior designer wanted to create a home where “everything gets put away at night” — and she succeeded. Sort of.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293240', '1683927757'),
(1060, 9, 0, 117, '52e85c81-af14-5153-ba92-e618e3146ef3', 'A Southern California designer wanted to create a home where “everything gets put away at night” — and she succeeded. Sort of.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/realestate/southern-california-minimalist-home.html', 'Nicole Heininger had long dreamed of designing a house in Manhattan Beach, Calif., where she could raise a family. So in 2017, when she and her husband, Taylor Heininger, began having children, they started hunting for a teardown close to the ocean.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667293242', '1683927757'),
(1061, 20, 0, 0, '9f9dc059-9061-5d8e-b616-fe3983816b95', 'What can we learn from the fight between an Indigenous Sami woman and a government bureaucracy?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/learning/film-club-svonni-v-the-swedish-tax-agency.html', '“Svonni v. the Swedish Tax Agency” is a five-minute Op-Doc film that touches on themes of tradition, respect, bureaucracy and discrimination. It profiles Ida-Maria Svonni, a Sami woman fighting for her right to claim a tax deduction for the purchase of a dog. Why doesn’t the Swedish Tax Agency understand that her dog, Rikke, is an essential tool for reindeer herding and not simply a pet? To answer this question, the humorous short film reveals a larger cultural clash and the struggle to practice Sami culture in today’s Sweden.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667295007', '1683927758'),
(1062, 27, 20, 257, 'b74088d5-b9ec-58bf-8f80-dfda506a0cc7', 'What comes next for the social media giant now that it’s under the stewardship of the wealthiest person in the world?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/podcasts/the-daily/elon-musk-twitter.html', 'It was long awaited, and some doubted that it would ever come to pass, but last week, the tech billionaire Elon Musk officially took over Twitter.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667296810', '1683927760');
INSERT INTO `btd_articles` (`idArticle`, `idSection`, `idSubSection`, `idAuthor`, `id`, `title`, `url`, `lead_paragraph`, `source`, `image`, `published`, `created`) VALUES
(1063, 10, 5, 81, 'e10f9116-5ab8-58d0-bcad-0cf95ec9bc6f', '“This is another major boost of momentum as we consolidate our support,” Blake Masters said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/politics/blake-masters-marc-victor-arizona.html', 'The Libertarian candidate running for Senate in Arizona — who had threatened to play spoiler in the closely watched race — is dropping out and endorsing Blake Masters, the Republican nominee.', 'The New York Times', '01pol-masters-1-000c-articleLarge.jpg', '1667296810', '1683927761'),
(1064, 17, 0, 480, 'c3ff9c4e-cab8-5ccb-9464-a9c85b8f3120', 'Around the United States, middle school science standards have minimal references to climate change and teachers on average spend just a few hours a year teaching it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/climate/middle-school-education-climate-change.html', 'In mid-October, just two weeks after Hurricane Ian struck her state, Bertha Vazquez asked her class of seventh graders to go online and search for information about climate change. Specifically, she tasked them to find sites that cast doubt on its human causes and who paid for them.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215582184_ffbc4b30-3423-4940-b45e-78abce34b4fd-articleLarge.jpg', '1667297076', '1683927762'),
(1065, 2, 0, 218, 'f3e55c22-44e9-5a6c-8cad-60d6bd7a374a', 'Bumper earnings from Aramco, the world’s largest oil company, and BP were, nonetheless, a slight decline from the previous quarter.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/saudi-aramco-oil-profit.html', 'Saudi Aramco, the world’s largest oil company, said on Tuesday that it had earned $42.4 billion in net income in the third quarter. The figure was more than double the nearly $20 billion that Exxon Mobil earned for the period.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_164235306_45b1dc72-768f-4e49-84bb-7db93ef33450-articleLarge.jpg', '1667299215', '1683927763'),
(1066, 21, 0, 524, '8710164f-73af-54cd-aa47-300da13c9e75', 'The company had strong revenue growth but lost money in part because of its investments in other ride-hailing businesses.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/technology/uber-revenue.html', 'Uber on Tuesday reported revenue growth exceeding expectations from Wall Street, suggesting that the company has continued to recover from a pandemic slump as drivers return to the platform. But it posted a net loss, in part because of its investments in other ride-hailing companies.', 'The New York Times', '01uber-pic-1-8c8e-articleLarge.jpg', '1667300470', '1683927764'),
(1067, 19, 0, 531, 'fe2f1927-2776-5d52-afb4-920eff299dee', 'The Supreme Court seems poised to end the policy.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/briefing/affirmative-action-supreme-court.html', 'Laws need support from the public or the courts to survive. Affirmative action seems to have neither.', 'The New York Times', '01themorning-lead-2-articleLarge.jpg', '1667301584', '1683927764'),
(1068, 5, 0, 605, '23cae480-c390-5c16-8b9b-b10f5a83cfd2', 'We visited a job center for day laborers on Staten Island that was planning for two big events: graduation for a construction safety course, and a ceremony marking the Mexican Day of the Dead.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/11/01/nyregion/dia-de-los-muertos.html', 'We visited a job center for day laborers on Staten Island that was planning for two big events: graduation for a construction safety course, and a ceremony marking the Mexican Day of the Dead.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667302131', '1683927765'),
(1069, 2, 24, 134, '272b461f-b6ad-55be-845e-d8b882db5525', 'Disputes over compensation and firings, and potentially over layoffs, could push both sides into fresh legal battles.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/dealbook/elon-musk-twitter-court-legal-battles-pay-layoffs.html', 'Elon Musk’s deal to buy Twitter may have closed, but his battle with the company’s board and executives seems to be barreling forward. After what DealBook hears was a bitter closing on Thursday, Musk is taunting Twitter and the law firm it worked with in its lawsuit against him, Wachtell Lipton, with the prospect of litigation, while trying to avoid paying top executives the golden parachutes they’re owed. It appears that fraught legal battles lie ahead, and it’s unclear whether Musk’s aim is to win or simply punish.', 'The New York Times', '01DB-Twitter-1-fad7-articleLarge.jpg', '1667304572', '1683927768'),
(1070, 6, 0, 0, 'e734569a-8717-5fc2-a5aa-b68e302dc453', 'Quotation of the Day for Tuesday, November 2, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/todayspaper/quotation-of-the-day-the-final-journey.html', '“It’s quite profound. Even after death claims the body, we’re going to beautify it in some way — like, death cannot win.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667306093', '1683927768'),
(1071, 31, 0, 205, '9bda4f45-0376-5dc3-b594-93eff3f25737', 'Vaccines and treatments are in trials, but the virus remains a leading killer of infants worldwide.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/health/rsv-children-vaccines.html', 'Of the three respiratory viruses Americans are grappling with this winter, two — the coronavirus and the flu — are well-known threats. The third, respiratory syncytial virus, which already has sent thousands of children to hospitals, is a mystery to many.', 'The New York Times', '01rsv-articleLarge.jpg', '1667306330', '1683927769'),
(1072, 3, 33, 606, 'cdfc713e-3f9b-588e-997d-8c7a65dec462', '“Spirited,” a revisionist “Christmas Carol,” leads with tap, thanks to the choreographer Chloé Arnold and her team, Ava Bernstine-Mitchell and Martha Nichols.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/dance/spirited-tap-dance.html', 'The trailer for “Spirited” arrives feet first. Two silhouetted bodies trade syncopated riffs in a lively tap showdown. “It’s beginning to sound a lot like Christmas,” the title cards announce, before the dancers are revealed to be the film’s stars: Will Ferrell and Ryan Reynolds.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215544774_8ca86b97-d439-4192-addc-0de43e32d1cd-articleLarge.jpg', '1667307606', '1683927770'),
(1073, 10, 0, 607, 'ba76aa46-f05a-5c6b-897b-c75a9a7ef20b', 'The trial, which began last month, is expected to last several more weeks.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/harvey-weinstein-trial-los-angeles.html', 'Every day last week during the beginning of Harvey Weinstein’s rape trial, jurors, lawyers and spectators spilled out of elevators and onto the ninth floor of the hulking Clara Shortridge Foltz courthouse in downtown Los Angeles.', 'The New York Times', '01californiatoday-1-78ab-articleLarge.jpg', '1667307608', '1683927771'),
(1074, 2, 2, 2, 'bf5d28c6-02c9-586b-95a5-467d4a822619', 'The Walt Disney Company announced that it would experiment with offering Disney+ subscribers exclusive access to themed merchandise.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/media/disney-plus-streaming-shopping.html', 'Can shopping make Disney+ even more of a must-have streaming service?', 'The New York Times', '01disney-shopping-pic-1-f75f-articleLarge.jpg', '1667307608', '1683927773'),
(1075, 10, 5, 538, '017e495b-63d2-560a-b515-579858aeeb45', 'An anonymous woman reiterated her claim that Mr. Walker, a nominee for Senate in Georgia, pressured her to have an abortion decades ago. The Times could not confirm the account.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/politics/herschel-walker-abortion-woman.html', 'An anonymous woman on Tuesday defended her claim that Herschel Walker, the Republican nominee for U.S. Senate in Georgia, pressured her to have an abortion nearly three decades ago after a yearslong extramarital relationship.', 'The New York Times', '01midterms-live-herschel-walker-topart-1-c6d0-articleLarge.jpg', '1667308092', '1683927774'),
(1076, 8, 4, 21, '8ff05581-88db-50d8-8879-b095fc0e8af4', 'Cash compensation for victims’ families will do little to make up for the life, and economic hope, of migrants among the 134 killed in India.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/asia/india-bridge-disaster.html', 'At 18, Habibul Sheikh quit school and left his home in eastern India for the promise of a better life, beckoned to a bustling industrial town on the other side of the country.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667309075', '1683927775'),
(1077, 3, 3, 608, '62d2d02c-5a93-54ed-98f6-8f3886a2511a', 'Diagnosed with multiple sclerosis during filming of the show’s final season, Applegate was determined to finish the story. She said it was the hardest thing she’s ever done.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/television/christina-applegate-dead-to-me.html', 'When Christina Applegate looks back, she can recognize the signs. Filming a dance sequence during the first season of the Netflix wine-mom dramedy “Dead to Me,” she found herself off balance. Later, her tennis game began to falter. At the time, Applegate, an actress with an aversion to special pleading, didn’t make excuses. She had to work harder, she told herself. She had to try again.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215788803_d47b9b0e-fc5d-44db-99c4-5e3ba999aa80-articleLarge.jpg', '1667311206', '1683927775'),
(1078, 3, 12, 341, '81e8bcee-a1e1-5ad2-af60-4a7c945c010d', 'Serena and Venus Williams and Ava DuVernay, and the artists who portrayed them, talk about their choices, which will be on view at the National Portrait Gallery.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/design/portrait-gallery-serena-venus-williams-ava-duvernay.html', 'Three strikingly personal and introspective new portraits of three famous women — the tennis champions Serena and Venus Williams and the filmmaker Ava DuVernay — go on view at the Smithsonian’s National Portrait Gallery in Washington on Nov. 10 as part of the institution’s Portrait of a Nation Award.', 'The New York Times', '01portraits-2-articleLarge.jpg', '1667311210', '1683927777'),
(1079, 3, 15, 476, '99f1986f-032e-58e2-bad8-6ead27e5e89a', 'The rapper was killed in a shooting at a bowling alley in Houston overnight.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/music/takeoff-migos-dead.html', 'The rapper known as Takeoff, a subtle vocal technician and one-third of the chart-topping group Migos, whose singsong flow helped define Atlanta’s ever-evolving, influential rap sound, was shot and killed overnight outside a Houston bowling alley, the authorities said. He was 28.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667312128', '1683927777'),
(1080, 8, 6, 20, '3bba653c-8073-5e30-a008-5ddc16cf4a8d', 'The commander of a Ukrainian reconnaissance unit spearheading the counterattack in the southern region of Kherson explained how his team helped breach defenses he described as frighteningly dense.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/europe/ukraine-war-kherson.html', 'KHERSON REGION, Ukraine — The explosions flashed bright red against the dimming landscape. Half a dozen mortar strikes in quick succession raised cones of lethal shrapnel and dirt. Black smoke curled above the trees.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667312694', '1683927778'),
(1081, 8, 14, 550, 'e9106702-afe5-53ec-b545-f9d64f44d894', 'Breaking his silence, President Jair Bolsonaro did not admit defeat or repeat his baseless claims about election fraud, but his administration signaled that the transfer of power would proceed.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/world/americas/bolsonaro-protest-brazil-election.html', 'BRASÍLIA — Two days after losing Brazil’s presidential election, President Jair Bolsonaro agreed to a transition of power on Tuesday, easing fears that the far-right leader would contest the results after warning for months that the only way he would lose would be if the vote were stolen.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667313438', '1683927779'),
(1082, 3, 12, 609, '1cb56b54-c1d1-5c73-bc1c-5d04582514fa', 'A major London exhibition asks viewers to put aside the details of the artist’s tumultuous life and concentrate on his paintings.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/arts/design/lucian-freud-national-gallery-london.html', 'LONDON — When the National Gallery staged a show of Gauguin portraits in 2019, it took pains to highlight aspects of the artist’s personal life: The writing on the entrance wall stated that he had “repeatedly entered into sexual relations with young girls, ‘marrying’ two of them and fathering children.” These aspects had barely been mentioned in previous Gauguin shows, and the museum was making amends.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215742294_017ac20f-9ccc-48dd-ab70-154c8ba70f83-articleLarge.jpg', '1667314454', '1683927780'),
(1083, 10, 0, 0, '7ded7c47-bc4c-5995-8603-f13f9a1c1965', 'The storm, which was moving over the central North Atlantic on Thursday, was expected to weaken over the next few days.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/article/tropical-storm-martin-hurricane.html', 'Martin became a post-tropical cyclone as it moved over the central North Atlantic Thursday, a day after strengthening into a hurricane. Forecasters said that while it was causing strong winds and hazardous seas it posed no immediate threat to land.', 'The New York Times', 'oakImage-1667312491605-articleLarge.jpg', '1667314784', '1683927782'),
(1084, 15, 0, 610, 'c82ec2e0-dc5e-507c-85b2-7f8a812507a5', 'In a study of mice, researchers worked out a neural pathway that could help researchers alleviate nausea symptoms from chemotherapy drugs.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/science/brains-neurons-vomit.html', 'Anyone who’s had a shady oyster or a mushroom soup that didn’t sit well remembers the ominous queasiness heralding impending bad times. Bacteria release toxins that start the body’s process of speedily evacuating the contents of the stomach. It’s a protective mechanism of sorts — getting rid of the invaders en masse is probably helpful in the long term, even if it’s unpleasant in the short. But it has remained something of a mystery how the brain gets the alarm signal, then sends another one to tell the stomach to initiate a technicolor yawn.', 'The New York Times', '01tb-upchuck-1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667314809', '1683927783'),
(1085, 10, 5, 492, '22bf5275-aa7a-503f-a493-1e5f0f5124cc', 'The move further delays an oversight request by the House Ways and Means Committee from 2019 as the midterm election looms.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/us/politics/trump-taxes-release-delay.html', 'WASHINGTON — Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. issued an order on Tuesday to temporarily bar the Treasury Department from giving former President Donald J. Trump’s tax returns to a House committee, the latest move in a long-running dispute over whether Congress can gain access to them.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_214572153_7e9c7d15-47ec-434f-9ac8-cd9b26739da2-articleLarge.jpg', '1667314914', '1683927784'),
(1086, 2, 11, 380, '64777dcb-82b9-5b3b-ba4a-91dbbec63f41', 'The labor market has remained stronger than expected even as the Federal Reserve has tried to get inflation under control.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/business/economy/job-openings-economy-labor.html', 'The nation’s extreme shortage of job seekers worsened in September, the Labor Department reported Tuesday, after easing the previous month.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215583219_aba3c541-587a-4823-8cfa-69047cb299dc-articleLarge.jpg', '1667314918', '1683927785'),
(1087, 8, 6, 300, '0fcc1db4-599f-570f-a0a1-1d7c94b50c2c', 'The attack knocked pumps that drive running water to homes across Kyiv offline, leaving 80 percent of the city without water.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2022/11/01/world/europe/kyiv-water-rocket-attack.html', 'The attack knocked pumps that drive running water to homes across Kyiv offline, leaving 80 percent of the city without water.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1667315339', '1683927786'),
(1088, 31, 0, 611, '84eb5507-19df-5830-a7e8-a526ece87759', 'A C.D.C. study estimates that, over five years, one in eight deaths of people ages 20 to 64 occurred because of alcohol-related injuries or illness.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/health/alcohol-deaths-working-age.html', 'An estimated one in eight deaths of Americans ages 20 to 64 in the years 2015-19 was the result of injuries or illness caused by excessive alcohol use, according to a new study from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.', 'The New York Times', '01ALCOHOL-DEATHS1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667315847', '1683927787'),
(1089, 14, 0, 612, 'ac158d74-105b-56a1-b15e-13f46f7fdb21', 'New data suggests that abortion has declined about 2 percent in the U.S. since the end of Roe, accounting for people who traveled across state lines or ordered pills online.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/upshot/abortion-pills-mail-overseas.html', 'As states banned or restricted abortion this summer, the number of American women ordering abortion pills from overseas jumped significantly — enough to offset most of the drop in legal abortions.', 'The New York Times', '01up-pills1-1-183f-articleLarge.jpg', '1667316039', '1683927788'),
(1090, 17, 0, 277, 'c2c53995-e0c5-569b-a478-52a2ca5e2bc8', 'The election is over. We talked to people on both sides of Brazil’s political divide about their expectations.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/climate/amazon-climate-lula-bolsonaro.html', 'Environmentalists in Brazil are breathing a bit more easily after Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, who made climate a cornerstone of his campaign, won the country’s presidential election on Sunday.', 'The New York Times', '01cli-newsletter-amazon-articleLarge.jpg', '1667316325', '1683927789'),
(1091, 26, 0, 533, '4162b4ec-2a68-5313-b62f-a9261974ef95', 'The Irish character actor has earned praise as a supporting player in movies like “The Banshees of Inisherin,” but he’s ready to be a star.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/movies/barry-keoghan-banshees-inisherin.html', '“The Banshees of Inisherin,” Martin McDonagh’s black comedy about longtime friends, Padraic (Colin Farrell) and Colm (Brendan Gleeson), who have a contentious falling out, has the shape of a classic two-hander. What’s strange is that its M.V.P. is neither of the leads but rather Barry Keoghan, as the slow-witted neighborhood boy Dominic, who steals every scene he’s in. Sprightly and erratic, with a hint of pathos behind an air of foolishness, he feels fully realized, and despite the limited screen time, Keoghan is vivid and moving.', 'The New York Times', '01barry-keoghan1-articleLarge.jpg', '1667317343', '1683927790'),
(1092, 22, 0, 613, 'f40c9e3b-cf98-5aad-9e69-d408c179d2d7', 'With weekly D.J.s and decent cocktails, the train station watering hole is attracting drinkers with no intentions of traveling.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/dining/new-yorks-hottest-club-is-the-penn-station-bar.html', 'Liane Emerson picked the place for her third date with Austin Bailey. She knew the Midtown bar was cool, but her date wasn’t so sure. “He thought it was weird,” she said.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215546979_1caa647f-bc35-4075-a8dc-a7788e57527b-articleLarge.jpg', '1667318393', '1683927791'),
(1093, 11, 0, 614, 'c7e277db-716f-5554-9936-0c146423e029', 'Vogue Mexico on Thursday hosted its third gala celebrating the holiday. “We want this event to be shared globally,” its top editor said.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/style/vogue-mexico-day-of-the-dead-gala.html', 'MEXICO CITY — The formula was familiar. It included invitations from Vogue, a carpet filled with celebrities, fashion designers and models dressed to the nines, and even a theme.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215608308_0f46b209-377c-4e32-94f5-97fa51e84e4a-articleLarge.jpg', '1667318419', '1683927792'),
(1094, 11, 0, 615, 'b2dc4b84-8103-5d47-972b-4146bd838d2c', 'Property tussles in the moneyed enclaves of Long Island are nothing new, but the battle to preserve the homestead of Pyrrhus Concer raises questions of whose history gets to be honored.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/style/hamptons-black-whaler.html', 'SOUTHAMPTON, N.Y. — Though summer crowds have retreated from this exclusive enclave, one fixture of its landscape has lately become a year-round constant: a large white container truck parked on an overgrown lot by Agawam Lake.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215546244_c18b27a1-4492-4eb9-8d62-6326562f60e7-articleLarge.jpg', '1667318441', '1683927793'),
(1095, 15, 0, 616, 'f8cb7e63-e872-5748-b1e2-7fc3432847bb', 'A drastic and unusually early spike in the respiratory infection is swamping pediatric units across the United States, causing long waits for treatment and worries about winter.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/science/rsv-children-hospitals.html', 'A pediatrician in Mount Zion, Ill., sent a video of a 6-month-old named Natalie to a colleague for advice: The infant’s belly was puffing and retracting with every pant as she struggled to breathe, her nostrils flaring and bubbles forming on her lips.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215786532_81017bb8-a86f-4e43-b0de-f199daf699cb-articleLarge.jpg', '1667318877', '1683927794'),
(1096, 16, 26, 617, '54d22e58-06ca-54ca-92c4-3fd418202dac', 'Beyond making tough moments a little easier, cultivating levity is good for your health.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/well/mind/humor-benefits.html', 'Wendi Aarons was writing at her local library when the sound of an angry voice made everyone look up. A patron, outraged over a book policy, vowed to take her child to another library and stormed off after berating the staff. The entire room was “so upset,” recalled Ms. Aarons, a humorist in Austin, Texas. “It was just this awful, uncomfortable silence.”', 'The New York Times', '01-Cultivating-Levity-articleLarge.jpg', '1667319022', '1683927795'),
(1097, 22, 0, 618, 'e3a71a22-3746-5ea4-8646-6b8c5d593348', 'She brought sass and sensuality to the job as a critic for New York magazine for four decades. She also helped create the charity Citymeals on Wheels.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/dining/gael-greene-dead.html', 'Gael Greene, who reinvented the art of the restaurant review with sass and sensuality in four decades as New York magazine’s restaurant critic, died on Tuesday at her home in an assisted living facility in Manhattan. She was 88.', 'The New York Times', '00Greene-Gael2-articleLarge.jpg', '1667319480', '1683927796'),
(1099, 21, 0, 619, '1c9953a4-cf0f-5834-b8ae-78f185329cdd', 'An organization that helps secure Jewish facilities across North America said Twitter had an “antisemitism problem,” and asked its new owner to fix it.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/technology/musk-twitter-antisemitism-security-group.html', 'The nonprofit organization Secure Community Network, which provides safety consulting and training for Jewish facilities across North America, wrote a letter on Monday to Elon Musk, Twitter’s new owner, imploring him to clamp down on antisemitic content that could endanger lives.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_164704512_861fe2e9-f17f-4776-9959-3cc977785f6f-articleLarge.jpg', '1667320426', '1683927798'),
(1100, 22, 0, 484, '24e51b8b-36ef-5c34-ae41-8808ba7cff46', 'Kwame Onwuachi’s restaurant debuts in David Geffen Hall; the Atoboy team unveils its Rockefeller Center spot; and more restaurant news.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/01/dining/nyc-restaurant-news.html', 'After nearly 25 years on Seventh Avenue and 55th Street, this Greek restaurant has found a new, less sprawling home at the southern edge of the theater district, in the former Esca space. “We wanted something smaller,” said Nick Livanos, who owns the restaurant with family members, “and this gave us the opportunity.” Capacity is down to 65 seats from 220, in a spacious and airy room graced with stonework and a terrace for when the weather warms again. There’s still a wall of family photos — the Livanos family is from the village of Molyvos on the island of Lesbos — and another of painted plates from the island of Rhodes. The restaurant will continue to offer home-style fare, like stuffed peppers and meatballs along with a fairly typical Greek lineup, but what will not be available for the reopening are the grilled fish and lamb specialties. Gas has yet to be connected. “We are able to provide about 75 percent of our menu as it is,” Mr. Livanos said. Added to the menu and not derailed by the lack of fuel is a new section of raw, chilled and marinated dishes like Ionian hamachi crudo with anise carrot purée, ouzo-cured salmon, marinated sardines en croute and smoked Ioanian eel with a ouzo-blood orange glaze. The various spreads, salads, spanakopita, dolmades and moussaka remain on the menu.', 'The New York Times', 'merlin_215640996_7a98a98d-9e38-4e24-b3bb-91f82cebc032-articleLarge.jpg', '1667320549', '1683927799'),
(1101, 10, 5, 83, '46975898-5717-5c56-a1f5-f5eacc5793b9', 'A 2021 state election law cut in half the runoff calendar in Georgia, which had about twice as many days of early voting before last year’s Senate runoffs.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/30/us/politics/georgia-senate-runoff-early-voting.html', 'Georgia has eclipsed its daily record for early voting twice this week in the state’s nationally watched Senate runoff election, but even if the state keeps up the pace, it appears unlikely to match early voting turnout levels from the 2021 runoffs.', 'The New York Times', '30pol-georgia-turnout-1-4fac-articleLarge.jpg', '1669852804', '1683927800'),
(1102, 8, 6, 620, 'b9c7c8b8-8c2b-5ab6-9422-1c87c8b53298', 'The idea reflects frustration with the difficulty in holding anyone accountable in the war, and actually reaching trials in a new court is likely to be very hard.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/30/world/europe/russia-ukraine-war-crimes-court.html', 'The European Union’s top official on Wednesday proposed the creation of a United Nations-backed court to investigate and prosecute possible Russian crimes in the war in Ukraine, reflecting growing calls in Kyiv and the West for holding Moscow accountable for atrocities committed since its invasion.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669852813', '1683927801'),
(1103, 2, 24, 83, '7d80cfe6-219c-52c1-a609-446bd7a38a83', 'Mr. Pence, while promoting his new book at the DealBook Summit, frowned upon the idea of the Justice Department’s taking action against his former boss.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/30/business/dealbook/mike-pence-plays-to-the-gop-base-from-a-times-stage.html', 'NEW YORK — Former Vice President Mike Pence leaned into Republican talking points on Wednesday about Elon Musk and Disney while walking a familiar fine line on his former boss, delivering a message seemingly geared toward conservatives who will decide whether he is a viable presidential contender in 2024.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669853183', '1683927801'),
