(1112, 7, 0, 0, 'ba089223-13bd-519b-b5af-a114b4f7cee9', 'Corrections that appeared in print on Thursday, Dec. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/30/pageoneplus/corrections-dec-1-2022.html', 'An article on Wednesday about China’s efforts to quash protests using surveillance and intimidation misstated the travel arrangements offered by Tsinghua University. It offered free buses from the university to railway stations and airports, not free air or rail travel.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669867140', '1683927811'),
(1113, 31, 0, 624, 'a9494924-6f57-5b71-9576-d446aff99096', 'The tech multibillionaire said his company, Neuralink, was seeking government approval to test his device in people, and predicted it could happen in six months. Others have been conducting similar tests for years, but no device has been marketed commerci', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/30/health/elon-musk-neuralink-brain-device.html', 'In a presentation showcasing the Neuralink implant that Elon Musk hopes will someday connect the human brain to a computer, two monkeys were reportedly moving computer cursors with their brains.', 'The New York Times', '30neuralink-stream-01-articleLarge.jpg', '1669868297', '1683927812'),
(1114, 1, 9, 625, '796b9e40-3a59-5d57-baf2-b2686b0d5f36', 'Kansas City and the Bengals revisit last season’s A.F.C. championship, the Commanders and Giants battle for playoff seeding, and the Dolphins offense gets its stiffest test yet against the 49ers defense.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/sports/football/nfl-week-13-picks.html', 'Week 13 features three games between first-place teams and a whole heap of matchups pivotal to playoff futures. It’s also where the punishing grind of the N.F.L. season begins to affect outcomes. Promising teams turn into M.A.S.H. units. Bubble teams face difficult choices about who to play and who to rest. Others get boosted by the return of a starter.', 'The New York Times', '01nfl-matchups-1-1-8464-articleLarge.jpg', '1669870807', '1683927813'),
(1115, 2, 0, 626, '49a217e3-ffaf-594b-ba26-e2cd2dc3fdb1', 'Garment workers in Myanmar earn less than $3 a day to produce soccer apparel for Adidas. Some say they were fired after asking factory owners for a raise.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/business/world-cup-myanmar-adidas-wages.html', 'As the World Cup in Qatar kicked off last week, millions of fans pulled on jerseys costing $90 to $150 that were sold by Nike and Adidas, the official outfitter of this year’s tournament. Players, wearing new, brightly colored uniforms, slipped into shiny cleats and shoes that can retail for more than $200.', 'The New York Times', '00garmentworkers-worldcup-1-c8ff-articleLarge.jpg', '1669870811', '1683927814'),
(1116, 7, 0, 0, 'af0cfbe5-e6e3-5914-9af5-bc0a7936eb58', 'Quotation of the Day for Thursday, Dec. 1, 2022.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/pageoneplus/quotation-of-the-day-the-baguette-250-grams-of-magic-and-perfection-earns-recognition.html', '“When a baby cuts his teeth, his parents give him a stump of baguette to chew off. When a child grows up, the first errand he runs on his own is to buy a baguette at the bakery.”', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669870860', '1683927815'),
(1117, 5, 0, 0, '70aec28b-6983-5c33-beda-04e46b49211a', 'Lithium-ion battery fires are surging in the city, but the use of the power packs is difficult to regulate, officials say.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/nyregion/lithium-ion-batteries-fires.html', 'Good morning. It’s Thursday. We’ll look at batteries that power e-bikes and scooters — and the risks that fire officials say they pose. We’ll also look at a police official who was promoted despite past disciplinary charges.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669871403', '1683927816'),
(1118, 19, 0, 90, '1e1cc8a7-4f04-5b10-af34-00b784d3ebc7', 'A torrent of protest videos is testing the limits of China’s censorship apparatus.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/briefing/china-protest-videos-ukraine-kyiv.html', 'China’s censorship apparatus — the most sophisticated of its kind in the world — has hunted down and deleted countless posts on social media showing the recent eruption of protests and anger at the government. Yet new videos of marches, rallies and other signs of dissent have continued to emerge on the chat app WeChat and the short video sharing app Douyin.', 'The New York Times', NULL, '1669873396', '1683927817'),
