(1122, 20, 0, 0, 'ac9eca20-29fd-5c30-95a5-2871e084642d', 'What are your favorite tree and home decorations for the winter holidays?', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/learning/holiday-ornaments.html', 'How do you decorate your home for the holidays, if at all? Do you prefer more traditional decorations or do you like those that are more modern and of-the-moment, perhaps ones that are even a little ironic or funny? ', 'The New York Times', '00ORNAMENTS-COMBO-articleLarge.jpg', '1669881602', '1683927820'),
(1123, 4, 0, 0, '12864e50-e97c-54c2-bfbb-187d2662a974', 'Feeling stuck on today’s puzzle? We can help.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/crosswords/spelling-bee-forum.html', 'THURSDAY — Hi busy bees! Welcome to today’s Spelling Bee forum. There are a number of terms that appear in both this article and other online discussions of the Spelling Bee; a glossary of those terms compiled by Monicat, a Times reader, can be found below. For more Spelling Bee conversation, check out Deb Amlen’s weekly humor column, “Diary of a Spelling Bee Fanatic.”', 'The New York Times', '01bee-forum-thu-articleLarge.jpg', '1669881603', '1683927821'),
(1124, 11, 0, 628, '2008bea6-3974-5cc6-bfc6-e21bc7b62b57', 'They come in a variety of lengths and weights. Here are six to covet.', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/01/style/gold-chains.html', 'I attended college before cellphones. For a brief time I had, as my answering machine message, the end of the theme song of the James Bond movie “Goldfinger.” “Ooooonly gooooold,” Shirley Bassey sang. “He loooooves gooooooold,” with all the elongated vowels. The 1990s were a weird and campy time, but I was being sincere. I do love gold!', 'The New York Times', '30monster-chains-1-1cd3-articleLarge.jpg', '1669881609', '1683927822'),
